(10590, 'No Prefix', 430000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 4, '1 Middle Pitt', 'Middle Pitt, Whitnage', 'EX16 7DU', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This stunningly Located Grade 2 listed semi-detached cottage offers 4 bedrooms and two bathrooms, one being an en-suite. Large farmhouse kitchen and sitting room with inglenook. 5 acres of land and outbuildings complete the the country lifestyle package.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Gloriously located with far reaching country views only about 6 miles from both Cullompton and Tiverton with both towns offering a useful range of shopping, schooling and transport facilities.&nbsp; The cottage is within 10 miles of Blundell''s School in Tiverton, whilst at the same time being within the catchment for the highly regarded Uffculme Secondary School.&nbsp; The nearby Tiverton Parkway Station provides a rapid link with London (Paddington) whilst the motorway allows rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The spectacular National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Heavy timber door to entrance </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> lovely slate floor, coat hooks, exposed wall timbers, ledged and braced door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> having white suite comprising enamelled cast iron bath, pedestal basin, WC, stripped timber floor, radiator, wall heater, door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility/Store Cupboard</span><span lang="en-GB"> with plumbing for washing machine, slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Farmhouse style country </span><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> with continuation of slate floor, range of pine units with cupboards and drawers, wooden work tops over, double shelved wall cupboard, Belfast sink, green oil fired rayburn for cooking and hot water, one radiator (others installed but not presently connected), twin glazed doors to front garden, window seat over looking front cottage garden, beamed ceiling, walk in larder cupboard, cottage stairs to the first floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Characterful </span><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> dual aspect with twin French doors to front garden and window with window seat over looking front cottage garden, massive inglenook fireplace with side benches and heavy bressumer beam housing wood burning stove, shelved recess, ceiling beam, five wall light points.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the First Floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">L-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> well lit by flank window, exposed cruck beams, stone fireplace with timber mantel.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> exposed beam, window overlooking cottage garden across the valley to distant hills, double fitted cupboards with fitted shelving and store cupboards below, walk in wardrobe with storage room beyond, access to loft, vaulted ceiling.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> characterful room with spectacular far reaching country views, exposed timbers, down lighting, ledged and braced door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite Shower Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with white suite comprising corner shower with curved entry, vanity wash basin set in&nbsp; travertine tiled surround, close coupled WC, down lighting, extractor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> beamed ceiling, down lighting, lovely far reaching views.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4</span><span lang="en-GB"> presently plasterboarded but in need of plaster skim and decoration, this room is plumbed for use as a family bathroom if preferred.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The property is approached off a quiet county lane through twin farm gates leading to an extensive parking area adjoining the house with small </span><span lang="en-GB">Garage/Store</span><span lang="en-GB"> adjoining, glorious front garden stocked with a vast array of traditional cottage plants and shrubs, providing a perfect back drop to the cottage.&nbsp; Part walled and hedged side garden with modern sewage treatment plant and poly tunnel, continuation of the drive through walling to the rear.&nbsp; Rear lawn interspersed with established trees and shrubs, extensive kitchen garden, aluminium framed </span><span lang="en-GB">Greenhouse</span><span lang="en-GB">.&nbsp; Useful assortment of </span><span lang="en-GB">Sheds/Stores </span><span lang="en-GB">and </span><span lang="en-GB">Former Poultry Building</span><span lang="en-GB"> (about 70ft in length). Area of </span><span lang="en-GB">Orchard</span><span lang="en-GB"> with gates leading to the two principal pasture fields being separated by a magnificent stand of ancient beech trees with the whole approaching five acres.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2552, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10649, 'No Prefix', 235000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 4, '12 St Georges View', 'St Georges View, Cullompton', 'EX15 1AB', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Spacious 4 Bedroom semi detached house in a semi rural setting on the outskirts of Cullompton. The property has been modernised and has a smart Kitchen breakfast room and stunning new bathroom. There are delightful views to the rear of the large garden and rolling hills beyond.</span></p>', '<p>A particularly delightfully located greatly extended semi detached family home constructed of brick exterior elevations beneath a tiled roof. The property has been skilfully extended with the addition of a fine family kitchen breakfast room with master bedroom over. The principal rooms are designed to take full advantage of the quite exceptional views to the rear which give this home its semi rural environment. With everyday eating now in the kitchen breakfast room the lounge diner has a particularly spacious atmosphere. An early inspection is strongly recommended to those seeking a spacious family home in an exceptional setting. <br /> <br />Nestling in the small cul-de-sac of St Georges View on the semi rural outskirts of the country town of Cullompton. The High Street with its everyday shopping facilities lies within a short walk. The town also offers two supermarkets, two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary schooling, sports centre and the highly regarded Padbrook Park golf course and leisure complex. The M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton. The surrounding countryside offers a wide variety of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty. A short way to the south the picturesque National Trust estate of Killerton provides lovely walks through its gardens and grounds. The comparatively central mid Devon location places the the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. <br /> <br />Superior and spacious semi detached home <br />Semi rural environment <br />Glorious country views <br />Gas central heating and UPVc double glazing <br />4 good bedrooms <br />Family kitchen breakfast room <br />Fine through lounge diner <br />Refitted bathroom <br />Garage <br />Hall and cloakroom <br />Large garden adjoining fields <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />Canopy Porch to UPVc double glazed front door. <br />Hall telephone point, radiator, stairs to first floor, understairs cupboard, cloaks cupboard. <br />Cloakroom having white suite comprising close coupled WC, wash basin, window. <br />Lounge/ dining room bright and airy through room with window to front overlooking garden, twin UPVc French doors commanding spectacular outlook over landscaped gardens, adjacent field and distant hillsides, two radiators, traditional marble effect fire surround and hearth housing gas coal effect fire, television aerial point. <br />Kitchen/ Breakfast room a glorious family room recently added providing a focal hub to the house with an excellent range of light ash effect fronted units comprising six base cupboards, drawer pack, integrated dishwasher, tall cupboard, marble effect roll edge work top with inset stainless steel sink, single drainer, mixer tap over, ceramic hob, double oven/ grill under, attractive ceramic tiled splashbacks, eight matching wall cupboards, corner shelving, radiator, slate effect flooring, side door to front garden and side pedestrian access, sliding UPVc patio door to raised patio and gardens, superb views, space for family dining. <br />Utility room timber effect laminate flooring, fitted shelving, space and plumbing for washing machine. <br /> <br />On the first floor <br />&lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped Landing with access to loft with retractable ladder, part boarded with gas fired boiler for central heating and hot water, linen cupboard with slatted shelving. <br />Bedroom 1 lovely dual aspect room, with stunning views over rear garden and the rolling hills beyond. <br />Bedroom 2 recess for double wardrobe, radiator, with wonderful country views over the rear garden. <br />Bedroom 3 bright and airy room with recess for double fitted wardrobe, radiator, timber effect laminate flooring, outlook over front garden. <br />Bedroom 4 radiator, Fitted double cupboard, outlook over front garden. <br />Bathroom with modern white suite comprising panelled bath with mains shower over, folding shower screen, pedestal wash basin, close coupled WC, heated towel rail, limestone style tiled floor, fully tiled walls, window with country outlook. <br /> <br />Outside <br />A tarmac drive with parking for several vehicles leads through the largely lawned front garden with established copper beach tree and leading to the single Garage 17&rsquo; x 8&rsquo;8&rdquo; with power connected, up and over door of brick construction matching the house, rear door. A wrought iron pedestrian gate leads through the brick walling to the large rear garden landscaped to provide three distinct areas, the first being a slightly raised extensive patio extending the full width of the plot and providing a superb alfresco entertaining area, whilst taking full advantage of the lovely views. Steps lead down to the central lawn which in turn leads to a hard landscaped gravelled area with decking, ornamental fish pond and timber garden shed. This large garden adjoins open fields and is ideally suited to the growing family</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2634, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10611, 'No Prefix', 425000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Sale Agreed', 4, 'Higher Claw Farm', 'Pennymoor', 'EX16 8LX', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>An extraordinary opportunity to acquire a unique lifestyle country home nestling in its own private sheltered valley setting, enjoying total privacy and tranquility whilst only being about 15 minutes from Tiverton</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Total tranquillity and seclusion yet only about 15 minutes from the country town of Tiverton is an undoubt attraction offered by this unique country home.&nbsp; Tiverton offers a useful range of high street shops and supermarkets together with easy accessibility to the M5 via the north Devon link road.&nbsp; A more extensive range of shopping and schooling facilities is to be found in the county town of Taunton and cathedral city of Exeter.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the delights of Exmoor and the north Devon Coast being within a modest drive.&nbsp; The Tiverton Parkway main line railway station places London (Paddington) within about a 2 hour train journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Oak part glazed front door to </span><span lang="en-GB">Entrance Lobby</span><span lang="en-GB"> having fitted shoe cupboard, coat hooks, ceramic tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room/Living Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> having oak strip effect flooring, radiator, night storage heater, window enjoying valley outlook with deep timber sill, exposed brick and stone walling, open tread stairs to first floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> having range of mid oak units, six base cupboards, granite effect roll edged work tops having inset gas (LPG) hob with double oven/grill beneath, inset one and half bowl Asterite single drainer sink, cooker hood/extractor, oil fired double oven Rayburn for cooking and hot water, four wall cupboards, shelving, exposed stone walling, ceramic tiled floor, two windows both enjoying wonderful views across the gardens and grounds down the valley.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> belfast sink with timber work top and cupboard beneath, space and plumbing for washing machine, three base cupboards, drawer pack, space for refrigerator and deep freeze, seven wall cupboards, ceramic tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Wet</span><span lang="en-GB">Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with fully tiled walls, mains shower, WC, window, extractor fan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> an intriguing room approached from the dining room up four steps and having lovely oak flooring, impressive stone fireplace with &lsquo;bread oven&rsquo;, slate hearth with beam over and housing woodburning stove, two wall light points. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">L-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> with flank window enjoying country outlook, shelved cupboard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> charming room with country outlook with fitted range of six wardrobes/cupboards, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> country views, exposed ceiling beam.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> exposed ceiling beam.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, country view, airing cupboard with hot water cylinder and slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> refitted with white suite comprising 4ft bath with mains shower over and shower screen, vanity basin with cupboards beneath, range of store cupboards, WC with concealed cistern, chrome&nbsp; towel rail, part tiled walls, ceramic tiled floor, window.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The house nestles on the hillside overlooking its own totally private sheltered valley.&nbsp; Adjoining the house the owners have created lovingly tended gardens with a mixture of terraced borders, raised beds, soft fruit cages and sweeping shrubberies interspersed with paths.&nbsp; Extensive wisteria clad loggia with stone paved floor created for alfresco entertaining.&nbsp; A willow and clematis clad rustic arch leads to areas of garden and natural wild life habitat.&nbsp; The south facing gardens overlook the valley with its tinkling brook.&nbsp; The entrance drive meanders down the valley to the house&nbsp; passing through the pasture fields and the dilapidated </span><span lang="en-GB">Outbuildings</span><span lang="en-GB"> constructed of a mixture of stone, block and corrugated iron arranged around a small yard with direct access to the </span><span lang="en-GB">Paddocks.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2579, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(8653, 'Asking price', 8000, 'Leasehold', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, 'UNITS C1 AT THE TANNERY, CULLOMPTON', 'Exeter Road, Cullompton', 'EX151DT', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>Warehouse premises&nbsp;to let on short term lease</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>5,230 sq.ft&nbsp;</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>Adjoining Yard available by negotiation</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">SITUATION: </span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">(of which dimensions are approximate):-<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>close to the centre of the town with access off the main arterial road.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>About half a mile from M5 junction 28 near The Old Tannery Antiques Centre and Oaks and Partners (Auctioneers) and on the opposite side of the road to Somerfield Supermakret.<!--?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" ?--></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Cullompton, population about 7,500, is an expanding town designated, together with the nearby village of Willand 2.5 miles away, as an &ldquo;Area of Major Change&rdquo; where considerable provision is made for growth by way of residential and employment land for development reflecting the policy to improve and widen the range of services and increase the capability of the town to serve a large hinterland.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">In addition Cullompton lies within the Exeter sub-region, the City being 13 miles away.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Tiverton Parkway Railway Station at M5 Junction 27 with regular services to Paddington is about 5 miles, Roscoff Ferry at Plymouth 55 miles, Taunton 18 miles, The North Devon Link Road at M5 Junction 27 gives rapid access to Barnstaple and North Devon.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">TYPE: </span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;</span>The premises are mainly of concrete block walls with some corrugated fibre cement cladding to upper parts and roof on reinforced concrete portal frame structure and with concrete floor.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">THE ACCOMMODATION: </span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;</span>comprises an open floor area approximately 26.7m x 19.7m (87ft 8 ins x 64ft 8ins) max about 3.15m (10ft 4ins) headroom and higher.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>With roller shutter door 3.82m (12ft 6ins) high x 4.6m (15ft) wide and pedestrian side door.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">There is a YARD AREA adjoining the premises of about one fifth of an acre which can be included in the negotiation.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">SERVICES: </span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Main electricity is connected.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">RATEABLE VALUE OF UNIT: </span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&pound;12,750 per annum. Business rates payable &pound;5,520.75</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">PLANNING:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>The premises have been used for many years as a warehouse and it is anticipated therefore that they have an established use for B8 use.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>However enquiries should be made of the Planning Authority, Mid Devon District Council, (01884 255255) to confirm&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">that any particular prospective use can be pursued without the need to make a planning application.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">LEASE:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>The premises are available on a short term lease and at a rent of &pound;8,000 per annum plus an amount to be negotiated for the yard if required.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">COSTS:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>The lessee will pay the Lessors legal costs in preparing the lease.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">VIEWING:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>By appointment please through <strong>Thorne &amp; Carter</strong> on (01884) 33333. 11 &amp; 13 High Street who hold a key.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">CONDITION OF PROPERTY:</span></strong><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"><span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>kindly note that for letting purposes neither the Landlord nor Thorne &amp; Carter have had a survey of the property carried out.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Consequently no warranty can be either given or implied as to the condition thereof nor of any of the appliances, equipment, fixtures or fittings.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Should assurance on condition be required, a prospective tenant is advised to obtain verification from their own independent research and enquiry.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt;"><span style="font-family: ''Helvetica'',''sans-serif''; font-size: 9pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1812, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'Per Annum', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10622, 'No Prefix', 650, 'Leasehold', 'Rental', 'Viewing', 2, '30 Raleigh Drive', 'Cullompton', 'EX15 1FZ', '<ul>\r\n<li>A well presented, spacious first floor flat with views. Approximately a quarter of a mile from the town centre and M5 motorway.</li>\r\n<li>Open plan sitting/dining room/kitchen 13ft 3 x 13ft 3</li>\r\n<li>Kitchen 11ft10 x 9ft2</li>\r\n<li>2 double bedrooms 12ft x 11ft and 11ft 9 x 9ft2</li>\r\n<li>Family bathroom</li>\r\n<li>Car port plus parking space</li>\r\n<li>Gas central heating, double glazing</li>\r\n<li>No pets, smokers, benefits</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>GENERAL CONDITIONS APPLICABLE TO MOST RESIDENTIAL LETTINGS</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">REFERENCES: References will be required from each applicant, including employers, previous landlord (if applicable) credit agency, personal and bank. There will be a charge made by the agent of &pound;96 (including VAT).&nbsp; NB. Some banks may make an additional charge for their services payable by the applicant.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;TENANCY AGREEMENT:&nbsp; The tenant will be asked to sign a Shorthold Tenancy Agreement and to pay the cost of its preparation - &pound;105.00 (inclusive of VAT). A sample agreement will be available to the prospective tenant prior to any request for signature.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">INVENTORY AND SCHEDULE OF CONDITION:&nbsp; Where required a Schedule of Condition and/or Inventory of all furnishings and effects at the property will be prepared by the Agents.&nbsp; A tenant will be responsible for one half of the cost (based on time taken) of the preparation thereof.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">RENT:&nbsp; The first months'' rent will be payable before taking up occupation and subsequent rent will be payable monthly in advance by Banker''s Order.&nbsp; Unless otherwise stated the rent will be exclusive of all utilities and Council Tax.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">MAINTENANCE RESPONSIBILITIES:&nbsp; Subject to the specific terms of the Tenancy Agreement, briefly, a tenant will be responsible for maintaining the internal decorations, fixtures and fittings and the glass in windows in good repair and condition.&nbsp; The Landlord will be responsible for the maintenance of all main structure and external decorations.&nbsp; The tenant will not be allowed to externally decorate and internal decoration is only to be carried out after consultation with and the approval of any proposed scheme by the landlords.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">DEPOSIT:&nbsp; A surety deposit of a minimum of one month''s rent will be payable by the tenant; to be held by the Deposit Protection Service, interest free, for the duration of the tenancy and for which a tenant will be charged an administration fee of &pound;42.00 (inclusive of VAT).</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">VIEWING:&nbsp; By appointment please through the Agents, Thorne &amp; Carter</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2653, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'per calendar month', 'N', 'N', 'N', '80', '81', '', ''),
(10638, 'No Prefix', 139950, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 2, '16 Park Street', 'Park Street, Willand', 'EX15 2PT', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This astonishingly spacious semi detached house nestles in a particularly large garden with plenty of parking on the outskirts of Willand. Probably constructed around the 1930&rsquo;s, improvements have included the fitting of UPVc double glazed windows and oil fired central heating.</span></p>', '<p>This astonishingly spacious semi detached house nestles in a particularly large garden with plenty of parking&nbsp; on the outskirts of Willand.&nbsp; Probably constructed around the 1930&rsquo;s, improvements have included the fitting of UPVc double glazed windows and oil fired central heating, whilst a conservatory has been added to the rear.&nbsp; The accommodation boasts a generous sitting room and kitchen/breakfast room, conservatory and cloakroom on the ground floor whilst upstairs two double bedrooms and a large bathroom are to be found.&nbsp; The 15ft master bedroom could readily be sub divided whilst the huge rear garden is a delight for the growing family.&nbsp; The drive provides plenty of parking in addition to the carport and a single garage.&nbsp; An early inspection is strongly recommended to those seeking a family home considerably larger than the modern &ldquo;semi&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Located towards the western outskirts of Willand, close to the One Stop Shop, primary school, village Post Office Stores and doctors surgery.&nbsp; A more extensive range of every day shopping, schooling and transport facilities is to be found about two miles to the south in the country town of Cullompton with its two supermarkets, secondary school, sports centre and popular Padbrook Park Golf Course and Leisure Centre.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Catheral City of Exeter and north to the County Town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The stunning National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Front door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Entrance hall </span><span lang="en-GB">with door to sitting room and stairs leading to 1st floor, radiator</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> large family sitting room with window outlook onto front garden, brick feature fireplace now used as shelving with niches housing electrical equipment and display shelving for TV, access to under stairs cupboard, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> extensive range of wood fronted units and marble effect laminate work top, nine base cupboards some with drawers over, 10 wall mounted cupboards, built in fridge freezer, electric cooker point with extractor hood over, window with outlook onto rear garden through the conservatory, door to conservatory.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">2nd hall </span><span lang="en-GB">side entrance, access to under stairs cupboard, door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">W/C </span><span lang="en-GB">ivory basin with cupboard under, W/C, window, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory </span><span lang="en-GB">good sized room that would be perfect used as either 2nd sitting room or as a dining room off the kitchen, sliding door opening onto patio area.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Small landing with window, access to loft and storage cupboard</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> huge double bedroom with outlook over the rear garden, inbuilt sliding door mirror fronted double wardrobe, radiator could be divided into 2 single rooms. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> big single room with outlook onto front garden and street scene, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">fully tiled with marble effect tiles white suite comprising of wood panelled bath, basin with storage cupboard under, W/C, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Front garden with gravel path, lawn and borders with shrubs</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Large drive with parking for 2 cars , carport leading to single garage 10x 19 with power.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Paved patio area with outside lighting making it perfect for alfresco entertaining. Extremely generous lawn area with panel fencing one side and hedged on all other sides making it very private. Area that would be perfect for vegetable patch, at the bottom of the garden there is a covered seating area and shed for storage of garden equipment/ machinery.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2607, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(5824, 'Region of', 3000, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Alexandria Industrial Estate', 'Station Road, Cullompton', 'EX151BW', '<ul>\r\n<li>1 minute from Junction M5 Motorway</li>\r\n<li>Workshop/Industrial Warehousing and Offices.</li>\r\n<li>In units of 165 to 4,000 sq ft.</li>\r\n<li>Various units available.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><strong>SITUATION:</strong>&nbsp; The Estate is in a particularly accessible situation within 200 yards of Junction 28 of the M5 Motorway on the outskirts of the expanding town of Cullompton.&nbsp; The North Devon Link Road which gives good access to the North of the County is at Junction 27 on the Motorway (4.5 miles away).&nbsp; Exeter Airport is 10 miles and the Railway Station at Tiverton Parkway at Junction 27 is 6 miles (10 minutes), Roscoff Ferry at Plymouth is 55 miles.&nbsp; The City of Exeter is 13 miles, Taunton (Somerset) is 18 miles.<!--?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" ?--></p>\r\n<p><strong>TYPE:&nbsp;</strong> The premises comprise a complex of 27 units of floor areas from 165 sq. ft. to 4,000 sq.ft., constructed mainly of concrete block walls with corrugated sheet roofs.&nbsp; With the number and various sizes of units on the estate, the facility is afforded for expanding businesses to grow by moving to other units, or taking additional units as they become available within the estate.</p>\r\n<p><strong>PARKING:</strong>&nbsp; Parking spaces are available with all units.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SERVICES:</strong>&nbsp; Main water and electricity (3 phase) are available on site, connections have been made to most units.&nbsp; Septic tank drainage.&nbsp; Central male and female toilet blocks.&nbsp; On site video security surveillance.</p>\r\n<p><strong>TERMS:</strong>&nbsp; Units are available to let on leases of three years on repairing and insuring terms.&nbsp; Tenants are to pay the cost of the preparation of the lease</p>\r\n<p><strong>RENT:</strong>&nbsp; Rent 