"black [0]" color2="white [7]"/>\r\n   <o:column v:ext="view" color="black [0]" color2="white [7]"/>\r\n  </v:stroke>\r\n  <v:shadow color="black [0]"/>\r\n  <o:extrusion v:ext="view" backdepth="0" viewpoint="0,0" viewpointorigin="0,0"/>\r\n  <v:textbox inset="2.88pt,2.88pt,2.88pt,2.88pt"/>\r\n  <o:colormenu v:ext="edit" fillcolor="blue [1]" strokecolor="black [0]"\r\n   shadowcolor="#ccc [4]"/>\r\n </o:shapedefaults><o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">\r\n  <o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1"/>\r\n </o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped landing, lit by flank window, access to loft, airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder and immersion heater, slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> south facing, deep bow window, radiator, two double fitted wardrobes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, outlook over rear garden.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, south facing, fitted cupboard with shelving. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">refitted with white suite comprising bath with mixer tap/shower attachment over, shower screen, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, radiator, fully tiled walls, electric shaver point. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Mostly lawned front garden with central border and drive leading to attached single garage with up and over door, light and power connected, extensive loft storage area.&nbsp; Well tended rear garden with lawn and ballustraded terrace adjoining the conservatory.&nbsp; Additional areas of paved patio for barbeques/entertaining etc, excellent garden Shed/Workshop.&nbsp; The whole being fully enclosed with established hedging, walling and fencing.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none;"><span style="language: en-GB; mso-ligatures: none;" lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2637, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10665, 'No Prefix', 183500, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 3, '9 Hawthorn Close', 'Hawthorn Close, Cullompton', 'Ex15 1SL', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Immaculately presented modern end of terrace family home has been comprehensively updated and refitted recently by the present owner. A large lounge, Kitchen/diner, three bedrooms two of which are good doubles and a brand new bathroom make for a great home for the growing family.</span></p>', '<p>This immaculately presented modern end of terrace family home has been comprehensively updated and refitted recently by the present owner. Constructed by Crest the property lies at the end of the small cul-de-sac in a sought after setting close to the highly regarded Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centre. New UPVc double glazed windows have recently been installed and this well insulated home is warmed by gas fired central heating. Tasteful contemporary decorations and new natural coloured carpet combine to make this a particularly appealing home for the growing family. On the ground floor the generous sitting room leads to a family kitchen/breakfast room and there is also a downstairs cloakroom. On the first floor three bright and airy bedrooms combined with a superbly appointed new bathroom complete the picture. An early inspection of this ready to move into home is strongly recommended. <br /> <br />Tucked away at the end of a small cul-de-sac towards the southern outskirts of Cullompton with its high street shops, two supermarkets, two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, sports centre and library. The town centre is within about a third of a mile and a frequent bus service (three buses an hour) combine with the nearby motorway to facilitate rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty. The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. <br /> <br />Superbly appointed modern end terrace home <br />New UPVc double glazing <br />Gas central heating <br />Hall <br />Cloakroom <br />Sitting room <br />Stylish kitchen/breakfast room <br />Three bedrooms <br />Contemporary refitted bathroom with shower <br />Fully fenced garden <br />Single garage and parking <br />15 miles Exeter, 18 miles Taunton <br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles <br />Exeter International Airport 15 miles <br />Main electricity, water, gas and drainage <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />Canopy entrance porch with tiled roof to part glazed front door. <br />Hall radiator, coat hooks, timber effect laminate flooring. <br />Cloakroom close coupled WC and vanity wash basin with cupboard beneath, radiator, timber effect laminate flooring <br />Sitting Room lovely bright and airy south facing room, radiator, understairs cupboard, turning staircase to first floor. <br />Kitchen/Breakfast Room well appointed with range of pine effect units comprising four base cupboards, integrated dish washer, integrated Hoover washing machine, tall cupboard housing integrated fridge and freezer, marble effect roll edge worktop having inset stainless steel single drainer sink with mixer tap, inset brushed stainless steel four ring gas hob with electric oven under and foldaway cookerhood/extractor over. Seven wall cupboards, one housing wall mounted gas fired boiler. Lovely bevelled edge ceramic wall tiling, slate tile effect laminate flooring extending through to the eating area, radiator, spot lighting, twin UPVc front doors to rear garden. <br /> <br /> <br />On the First Floor <br />Landing with access to insulated loft with boarding for storage, airing cupboard having lagged hot water cylinder, slatted shelving. <br />Bedroom 1 radiator, outlook over cul de sac to Bradninch Hill and golf course. <br />Bedroom 2 radiator, outlook over rear garden. <br />Bedroom 3 radiator. <br />Bathroom newly refitted with white suite, comprising panelled bath with mixer tap and Mira electric shower over, shower screen, close coupled WC, wash basin, chrome ladder style radiator/towel rail, down lighting, timber effect flooring. <br /> <br />Outside <br />Fully fenced rear garden with side gate, having lawns and raised area of decking immediately adjoining the house and extending the full width of the plot. Single garage of brick and tiled construction matching the house, up and over door, parking space immediately in front.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2631, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10602, 'No Prefix', 209950, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 4, '12 Court Drive', 'Court Drive, Cullompton', 'EX15 1AX', '<ul>\r\n<li><span style="line-height: 100%; text-indent: -14.15pt;">First time on the market Semi-Detached family home for updating</span></li>\r\n<li>Gas heating and UPVc double glazing</li>\r\n<li>Sitting room</li>\r\n<li>Dining room</li>\r\n<li>Kitchen</li>\r\n<li>3 first floor Bedrooms</li>\r\n<li>Ground floor Bedroom 4/Office</li>\r\n<li>Bathroom, 2 WC&rsquo;s</li>\r\n<li>Garage</li>\r\n<li>Large mature gardens</li>\r\n<li>Main electricity, water, gas and drainage</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>Court Drive is a highly sought after avenue towards the outskirts of Cullompton with older semi-detached homes set well back in generous plots.&nbsp; Cullompton high street with its range of shops and two supermarkets is within about half a mile.&nbsp; The country town of Cullompton also offers two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, community centre, new library and sport centre.&nbsp; Whilst the nearby M5 facilitates commuting to Exeter, Taunton,&nbsp; and beyond.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The nearby&nbsp; National Trusts Country estates of Killerton and Knightshayes provide spectacular walks through gardens and grounds.&nbsp; The National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;On the ground floor</p>\r\n<p>Recessed entrance porch to glazed front door.</p>\r\n<p>L-shaped Hall radiator, walk in understair cupboard with coat hooks.</p>\r\n<p>Sitting Room wide picture window with outlook over front garden, gas fire with back boiler for central heating, low cupboard to alcove, TV point, twin sliding glazed doors to</p>\r\n<p>Dining Room radiator, patio door to rear garden.</p>\r\n<p>Kitchen four base cupboards, drawer pack, roll edged work top with inset stainless steel twin bowl sink, free standing electric cooker with cooker hood over, five wall cupboards, open shelving, space and plumbing for washing machine, walk in larder, half glazed back door to long covered passage way having doors to front and rear garden, shelving.</p>\r\n<p>Bedroom 4/Office pleasant outlook over rear garden and with access independent of the house making it ideal for working from home.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>WC with white suite, shelving.</p>\r\n<p>On the First Floor</p>\r\n<p>L-shaped Landing well lit by flank window, access to loft and airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder and immersion heater, slatted shelving.</p>\r\n<p>Bedroom 1 radiator, two built in wardrobes.</p>\r\n<p>Bedroom 2 radiator, built in wardrobe, lovely outlook over rear garden.</p>\r\n<p>Bedroom 3 radiator, shelving.</p>\r\n<p>Bathroom coloured suite comprising panelled bath with mixer tap/shower attachment over, shower curtain and rail, pedestal basin, heated towel rail.</p>\r\n<p>Separate WC with coloured suite.</p>\r\n<p><!--[if !supportEmptyParas]-->&nbsp;<!--[endif]--></p>\r\n<p>Outside</p>\r\n<p>Concrete driveway and adjoining car standing to single Garage having up and over door, power connected, personal door.&nbsp; Lawned front garden with rose bed and established shrubs.&nbsp; Delightful rear garden having been created and enjoyed over many years by the present owner and now offering a generous outdoor space to be enjoyed by the whole family.&nbsp; Wide paved terracing ideal for alfresco entertaining, leading to landscaped area of raised rockery with water feature and established shrubs to path leading through rose clad rustic arch to areas of lawn flanked by shrubberies, established fruit trees, timber garden Shed.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2571, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '