"46"\r\n   Name="List Table 1 Light Accent 6"/>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="47" Name="List Table 2 Accent 6"/>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="48" Name="List Table 3 Accent 6"/>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="49" Name="List Table 4 Accent 6"/>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="50" Name="List Table 5 Dark Accent 6"/>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="51"\r\n   Name="List Table 6 Colorful Accent 6"/>\r\n  <w:LsdException Locked="false" Priority="52"\r\n   Name="List Table 7 Colorful Accent 6"/>\r\n </w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n /* Style Definitions */\r\n table.MsoNormalTable\r\n	{mso-style-name:"Table Normal";\r\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\r\n	mso-style-priority:99;\r\n	mso-style-parent:"";\r\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\r\n	mso-para-margin:0cm;\r\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\n	font-size:11.0pt;\r\n	font-family:"Calibri",sans-serif;\r\n	mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\r\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\n	mso-fareast-language:EN-US;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]-->''Lying high on the West facing slope of the Blackdown hills, Blackborough offers panoramic views, miles of woodland tracks and a thriving community. The Blackdown hills are themselves a designated area of outstanding natural beauty. This small village hosts a surprising variety of clubs, activities and social events, many of which have become much anticipated annual traditions which all ages enjoy.&nbsp;At the foot of the hill lies the village of Kentisbeare with its post office stores, thriving primary school, pub and pretty village square from where the school bus ferries children to and from the highly regarded Uffculme School. A more extensive range of facilities is to found in Cullompton (about 5 miles) and where the M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton. The comparatively central mid devon location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; <span style="font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; color: #333333; mso-ansi-language: EN-GB; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On the ground floor</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UPVc half glazed door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory/Garden Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with one wall of masonry construction and one with lower walling, two sides being picture windows enjoying astonishing far reaching views across the Culm Valley and distant Devon countryside towards Dartmoor, twin French doors to patio, radiator, ceramic tiled floor, part glazed inner door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with lovely stone tiled floor and range of white fronted units comprising eight base cupboards, drawer pack, integrated fridge, work tops with inset stainless steel one and a half bowl single drainer sink, mixer tap, inset Bosch four ring halogen hob with double oven/grill beneath, lovely stone tiled splashbacks, six wall cupboards, shelved unit with willow basket storage, downlighting, boiler cupboard housing Grant oil fired boiler for hot water and central heating, radiator, dual aspect, ceiling beam.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> extending the full width of the cottage having two windows again enjoying spectacular far reaching outlook, beamed ceiling, radiator, fireplace with beam and slate hearth housing multi fuel stove with adjoining log storage, downlighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with continuation of stone tiled floor from kitchen, double base unit with L-shaped work top over, space and plumbing for washing machine, three wall cupboards, radiator, ceiling beam, space for fridge/freezer.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> refitted with modern P-shaped bath having shower over, shower curtain and rail, extractor, fabulous stone sink with mixer tap and cupboard beneath, close coupled corner WC, stone tiled walls and travertine work top, travertine floor, window, downlighting, chrome ladder style towel rail/radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The concealed cottage staircase leads from the sitting room to the L-shaped landing, lit by flank window, radiator, boarded loft with retractable ladder and light, exposed cruck beam.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, exposed cruck beams, two windows again with magnificent country views.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, garden outlook, downlighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> fitted linen cupboard and adjoining double wardrobe with hanging rail and shelving, fitted computer desk with shelving, garden outlook, downlighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom 1 </span><span lang="en-GB">short bath with mains shower over, shower curtain and rail, travertine tiled surround, close coupled WC, vitreous enamel washbasin with cupboard beneath, chrome ladder style towel rail/radiator, extractor, window over looking garden.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Timber gate with stone steps leading to front door.&nbsp; The gardens lie mainly to the side with large river stone paved patio adjoining the conservatory ideal for alfresco entertaining, extensive lawn flanked by established shrub borders and laurel hedging beyond.&nbsp; Useful garden store accessible from both garden and conservatory.&nbsp; Grassy bank having stone steps rising up to rear gate providing direct access to country paths leading through the adjoining Blackborough woods.&nbsp; A single </span><span lang="en-GB">Garage</span><span lang="en-GB"> with up and over door is to be found on the other side of the lane.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2593, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10626, 'No Prefix', 216000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 3, '3 Beare Cottages', 'Beare Cottages, Beare', 'EX5 3JZ ', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Located in the small hamlet of Beare between Cullompton and Exeter this period cottage was probably originally a workers cottage for the nearby mill. It offers centrally heated and double glazed accommodation comprising two reception rooms, kitchen/breakfast room, two bathrooms and three bedrooms.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Located a short way down a no through lane in the small hamlet of Beare with the country town of Cullompton and its excellent every day shopping, schooling and transport facilities being a short way to the north.&nbsp; The cottage is ideally located for those wishing to commute to Exeter with its wealth of business opportunities, major stores, high street shops, Princesshay shopping mall and picturesque riverside.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The spectacular National Trust Country Estate of Killerton provides glorious walks through its gardens, grounds and arboretums. The spectacular National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Canopy entrance porch with slate roof to timber panelled front door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> with quarry tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with brick and stone fireplace housing solid fuel stove, slate hearth, beam over, radiator, wood effect laminate flooring.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Inner hall with continuation of flooring, understair cupboard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> dual aspect, window overlooking garden, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> having double base cupboard with light ash doors, work top over with inset stainless steel single bowl sink, space and plumbing for washing machine, wall cupboard, downlighting, cupboard housing Aztec electric boiler providing central heating and hot water.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> extensive range of light ash effect units comprising five base cupboards, drawer pack, fridge and freezer, work tops with inset stainless steel single drainer sink, mixer tap, inset four ring electric hob with electric oven under, two wall cupboards, downlighting, shelving, breakfast bar, radiator, timber effect laminate flooring, half glazed back door to garden</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Ground floor </span><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> modern white suite comprising panelled bath with mixer tap and Triton electric shower over, shower screen, close coupled WC, radiator, downlighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cottage stairs to </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, pretty Victorian basket grate in timber surround.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder with immersion heater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Large</span><span lang="en-GB"> Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> modern white suite, bath with mixer taps and electric shower over, shower curtain and rail, WC with concealed cistern, washbasin, downlighting, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Gravelled area to the front providing parking.&nbsp; Timber side gate to fully fenced garden with raised area of decking, two garden </span><span lang="en-GB">Sheds</span><span lang="en-GB">. Lawn.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2594, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', '');
