(10588, 'No Prefix', 249950, 'Freehold', 'Bungalow', 'Sale Agreed', 3, 'Kestor, Burlescombe', 'Burlescombe', 'EX16 7JW', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Burlescombe village in the catchment for Uffculme Secondary School. This detached bungalow is ripe for updating and offers well proportioned accommodation, three bedrooms, fine lounge, family kitchen/breakfast room and bathroom. Large mature Gardens and great views make for the complete package</span></p>', '<p>Set well back off the lane on the outskirts of the small village of Burlescombe.&nbsp; The village has its own thriving primary school with the nearby country towns of Cullompton and Tiverton providing an excellent range of everyday shopping, schooling and transport facilities.&nbsp; The nearby Tiverton Parkway station provides a rapid link with London (Paddington).&nbsp; The M5 facilitates easy commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty.&nbsp; The stunning national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.</p>\r\n<p>On the ground floor</p>\r\n<p>Sliding aluminium door to&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Entrance Porch leading to part glazed inner front door, long hallway, night storage heater, access to loft, airing cupboard housing lagged hot water cylinder with immersion heater.</p>\r\n<p>Sitting Room fine dual aspect room enjoying far reaching country views, reformite stone feature fireplace having open hearth, two wall light points, television point, night storage heater.</p>\r\n<p>Kitchen/Breakfast Room dual aspect, fine country views over front garden to distant hills, six base cupboards, drawer pack, roll edged work tops, inset stainless steel sink unit, space for electric cooker, cooker hood/extractor, eight wall cupboards, part glazed UPVc back door to</p>\r\n<p>Conservatory/Rear Porch sliding patio door to rear garden, personal door to garage.</p>\r\n<p>Bedroom 1 night storage heater, twin double fitted wardrobes with drawers and shelving between.</p>\r\n<p>Bedroom 2 night storage heater.</p>\r\n<p>Bedroom 3 night storage heater, fitted wardrobe with shelving and hanging rail.</p>\r\n<p>Bathroom coloured suite, comprising disability bath with door facilitating easy access, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, part tiled walls, electric fan heater, electric shaver point, electric shower over bath.</p>\r\n<p>Outside</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The property is approached from the quiet lane through twin timber gates to tarmac drive and parking and turning area adjoining which lies the Single Garage, with light and power, powered up and over door.&nbsp; Well stocked mature gardens surround the property with sweeping lawns interspersed with a wide variety of mature trees and shrubs.&nbsp; Fenced and hedged providing a high degree of privacy.</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2551, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10583, 'No Prefix', 275000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 4, '17 Caumont Close', 'Caumont Close, Uffculme', 'EX15 3XT', '<ul>\r\n<li>Stylishly updated modern detached family home.</li>\r\n<li>Tucked away cul-de-sac setting.</li>\r\n<li>Uffculme school catchment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Gas central heating and UPVc double glazing.</li>\r\n<li>Two reception.</li>\r\n<li>Four bedrooms (one with ensuite).</li>\r\n<li>Refitted kitchen, utility.</li>\r\n<li>Garage.</li>\r\n<li>Unusually secluded and secured large garden.</li>\r\n<li>Exeter 20 Miles, Taunton 19 miles</li>\r\n<li>Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles</li>\r\n<li>Mains electricity, water, gas and drainage</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none; text-align: justify; text-justify: newspaper; text-kashida-space: 50%;"><span style="font-family: Arial; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; language: en-GB; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB">Nestling at the end of the small cul-de-sac of Caumont Close within easy reach of the highly regarded Uffculme secondary school, primary school, village stores and frequent bus services.&nbsp; A more extensive range of facilities is to be found in the nearby town of Cullompton where there is also a sports centre, golf course and leisure centre and M5 intersection facilitating rapid commuting to Exeter and Taunton and more distant parts of the country.&nbsp; Uffculme lies at the foot of the Blackdown Hills an area of outstanding natural beauty where delightful walks and driving may be enjoyed.&nbsp; The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoBodyText2"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial;" lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none; text-align: justify; text-justify: newspaper; text-kashida-space: 50%;"><span style="font-family: Arial; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; language: en-GB; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB">Part glazed front door to </span><span style="font-family: Arial;" lang="en-GB">Hall </span><span style="font-family: Arial; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; language: en-GB; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB">radiator, timber effect laminate flooring, understair recess, </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none; text-align: justify; text-justify: newspaper; text-kashida-space: 50%;"><span style="font-family: Arial;" lang="en-GB">Cloakroom</span><span style="font-family: Arial; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; language: en-GB; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB"> with continuation of wood laminate floor, white close coupled WC and corner basin, radiator, window.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none; text-align: justify; text-justify: newspaper; text-kashida-space: 50%;"><span style="font-famil