(10627, 'No Prefix', 146950, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 2, '93 Headweir Road', 'Head Weir Road, Cullompton', 'EX15 1NN ', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This stylish coach house represents an ideal first purchase or buy-to-let investment with the added benefit of extensive parking and courtyard garden. This home benefits from high levels of insulation and UPVc double glazing combined with modern gas fired central heating to minimise running costs.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Located on this popular recently completed Persimmon development towards the eastern outskirts of Cullompton with its range of High Street shops, two supermarkets, two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, library, community centre and Padbrook Park golf and leisure centre.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside provides a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Canopy entrance porch to part glazed front door</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> wood effect floor, coat hooks, radiator, door to Car Port.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Large &lsquo;U&rsquo;-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, access to loft, boiler cupboard/airing cupboard with gas fired boiler.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Super open plan </span><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Living Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> having timber effect flooring throughout.&nbsp; The kitchen area with range of light ash effect units comprising five base cupboards, drawer pack, matching ash effect work tops with inset stainless steel single drainer sink, mixer tap, inset four ring gas hob with electric oven&nbsp; under and cooker hood over.&nbsp; Space and plumbing for washing machine, two spot light clusters, space for upright fridge freezer, two radiators, window and twin French doors having Juliette balcony.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, fitted wardrobe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">with white panelled bath having mixer tap and mains shower over with shower curtain and rail, close coupled WC, wash basin, radiator, part tiled walls, spot lights, extractor fan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Car Port </span><span lang="en-GB">with twin timber doors to the rear, providing access to rear garden/courtyard, thus facilitating additional parking if required.&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2596, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10614, 'No Prefix', 289950, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Sale Agreed', 4, '6 Sanders Way', 'Sanders Way, Ashill', 'EX15 3NY', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Merrivale Lodge was skilfully created by the original builder/owner for his own occupation with traditional exterior appearance, fine oak double glazed windows and sumptuous interior.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Sanders way is a tiny cul-de-sac on the outskirts of the small village of Ashill.&nbsp; The village offers a popular public house whilst being within the catchment for the highly regarded Uffculme secondary school.&nbsp; The nearby country town of Cullompton provides useful everyday shopping facilities including two supermarkets, whilst Junction 28 of the M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty.&nbsp; The picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Canopy </span><span lang="en-GB">entrance porch </span><span lang="en-GB">with slate roof and twin oak pillars, outside light, heavy oak front door with leaded double glazed central pane to hall, &lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped radiator, understairs recess,</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom </span><span lang="en-GB">close coupled WC, wash basin, ceramic tiled floor, radiator, extractor,&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Stylish contemporary </span><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with modern remote controlled living flame electric fire, display niches, radiator, TV point, two wall light points, village outlook. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p