ther fully shelved, two recessed cupboards, loft access.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4 </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, two fitted cupboards, one being fully shelved and the other with hanging rails, country outlook.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Superb Family Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">lavishly appointed with suite in white comprising panelled bath with centrally located mixer tap and hand spray, close coupled WC, wash basin, ceramic tiled floor,&nbsp; half tiled walls, down lighting, extractor, chrome ladder style heated towel rail, shaver point,.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The property is approached off a tarmac drive leading to the timber outbuilding providing secure storage for garden machinery, bikes etc.&nbsp; Front garden having two areas of lawn bisected by brick paved path, leading to the front door.&nbsp; Fully fenced rear garden with two pedestrian gates leading to parking, central lawn with brick paved patio and decking area at the end of the garden providing an ideal space for alfresco entertaining, having fitted solar lighting, large timber shed on concrete base providing storage and workshop facility with power connected, water tap, outside lighting and power socket.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2581, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10513, 'No Prefix', 125000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 2, '6B PIPPINS FIELD, UFFCULME', 'Pippins Field, Uffculme', 'EX15 3BS', '<ul>\r\n<li>Family home in Uffculme School catchment</li>\r\n<li>2 bed semi-detached starter home</li>\r\n<li>Lobby</li>\r\n<li>L shaped sitting/dining room</li>\r\n<li>Bathroom</li>\r\n<li>Gas central heating, UPVc double glazing</li>\r\n<li>Garage</li>\r\n<li>Workshop</li>\r\n<li>Small yard with double gates and storage area</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Pleasantly located a short way down the popular cul-de-sac of Pippins Field backing onto the historic Coldharbour Mill Museum about about </span><span lang="en-GB">&frac12;</span><span lang="en-GB"> mile from the village centre, which offers the highly regarded Uffculme secondary school together with primary school, doctor&rsquo;s surgery, One Stop shop and Post Office stores.&nbsp; Frequent bus services serve Tiverton, Cullompton and Exeter.&nbsp; Nearby Cullompton offers a more extensive range of shopping facilities.&nbsp; The surrounding area provides a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">This</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><span lang="en-GB">SEMI DETACHED STARTER HOME OR BUY TO LET INVESTMENT</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">The compact home is warmed by gas fired central heating having recently had the boiler replaced.&nbsp; UPVc double glazing ensures a warm economically run village home.&nbsp; Unusually for a property in this price range there is an established garden, garage, workshop and even an enclosed yard ideal for storage.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2441, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(7778, 'No Prefix', 200, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Jaffa House', '15 Pound Square, Cullompton', 'EX151DN', '<ul>\r\n<li>Period Offices of Character</li>\r\n<li>Extending in all to 172 square metres (1850 square feet) net floor area.</li>\r\n<li>70 metres from main street in Cullompton.</li>\r\n<li>M5 Motorway junction 28 is approx a quarter of a mile away.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>SITUATION AND AMENITIES: </strong>(please note that distances are approximate)<strong>&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n<p align="justify">Just 70 metres from the main street of the town yet occupying a quiet location in the busy country town of Cullompton which has expanded in recent years and is planned, together with the nearby village of Willand, to grow further in the near future.&nbsp; The M5 Motorway junction 28 is approximately a quarter of a mile distant.&nbsp; There are public car parks in the town and good facilities including an extensive range of shops, banks and post office.&nbsp; Tiverton Parkway Station with its mainline rail services to London (Paddington) is 5 &frac12; miles.&nbsp; Tiverton town is 6 miles and Exeter 13 miles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A particularly attractive listed former town house now</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>TOWN CENTRE OFFICES</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align="justify">of traditional Devon construction of stone and cob walls rendered to elevations with drip mouldings, portico entrance and slate roof and suitable for office use.&nbsp; The accommodation, which is light and airy throughout, affords space of character and standing in a quiet area just yards from the main street of the town.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It comprises:-</p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">On the Ground Floor:-</span></p>\r\n<p>Portico ENTRANCE PORCH with pillars.</p>\r\n<p>HALL with tessellated tile floor, panelled dado, balustraded staircase off.</p>\r\n<p>REAR LOBBY 7.5m (24''6") x 1.05m (3''6").</p>\r\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">SUITE 1</span></p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 1, 5.4m (17''9") x 4.9m (16'') excluding panelled deep window bay and attractive recess.&nbsp; Dressed stone lined open hearth fireplace and tiled inset and oak surround, door to</p>\r\n<p>STORE ROOM 3.85m (12''7") x1.25m (4''2").</p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 2, 5.20m (17'') x 5.0m (16''5") excluding panelled deep window bay, night storage heater point, fluorescent lighting.</p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 3, 4.3m (14''1") x 5.10m (16''10") fluorescent lighting, fireplace.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">On the First Floor:-</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Spacious LANDING and PASSAGE.</p>\r\n<p>SMALL OFFICE 4 1.85m (6''2") x 2.7m (8''10") excluding deep recess.</p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 5 5.30m (17''5") x 4.0m (13''2") max, excluding window recess.&nbsp; Walk-in cupboard, two other cupboards.</p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 6 3.7m (12''2") x 3/4m (11''2") cupboard.</p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 7 4.33m (14''2") x 4.45m (14''8") excluding window recess.</p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 8 4.60m (15''1") x 4.4m (14''8") cupboard, fireplace.</p>\r\n<p>OFFICE 9 3.88m (12''9") x 3.45m (11''5") average, excluding door recess.</p>\r\n<p>TOILET with suite, wash basin and water heater over.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">OUTSIDE:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Two WCs and a Store</p>\r\n<p>Small courtyard at rear.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>PARKING</strong>:&nbsp; The lessee of the premises will have the right to park up to four cars on a parking area in the Old Tannery estate on the west of Exeter Road and which is about 150 metres away.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>BUSINESS RATES</strong>:&nbsp; Rateable Value &pound;7,800.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>USE:</strong>&nbsp; Prior to refurbishment the building has been used as offices and for electronics assembly.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The first floor accommodation could also, subject to Local Authority consent, be converted into a totally self contained spacious flat.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>CONDITION:</strong>&nbsp; The landlord will carry out repairs and redecoration prior to commencement of the lease.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>RENT:</strong>&nbsp; Based on &pound;200 per week.&nbsp; However a discount may be available by negotiation for an intital period and to accommodate any improvements the tenant wishes to carry out and which benefit the property.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>TO VIEW:&nbsp; </strong>By appointment please by arrangement with Messrs <strong>Thorne + Carter.</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2171, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'per week', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10632, 'No Prefix', 167500, 'Freehold', 'Flat', 'Sale Agreed', 2, '32 Clarks Court', 'Clarks Court, Cullompton', 'EX15 1FB', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>An exceptionally rare find is this modern McCarthy and Stone retirement flat offering two bedroomed accommodation set back from Cullompton High Street behind its gated entrance. Not only does the flat have 2 bedrooms but also enjoys a dining area off the sitting room overlooking the grounds.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">An exceptionally rare find is this modern McCarthy and Stone retirement flat offering two bedroomed accommodation set back from Cullompton High Street behind its gated entrance. Not only does the flat have 2 bedrooms but also enjoys a dining area off the sitting room overlooking the grounds. Owners also enjoy the use of a residents lounge, laundry room and visitors flat. An early inspection of what is probably the best flat in the entire block is strongly recommended.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Right in the heart of town, just back from the High Street in a gated community offering great convenience combined with privacy and security.&nbsp; The country town of Cullompton provides a useful range of everyday shopping, schooling and transport facilities including a bus service to Exeter every 20 minutes.&nbsp; The nearby M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The property enjoys distant views towards the Blackdown Hills an area designated as Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; For those wishing to enjoy the delights of Devon the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; The stunning National Trust estate at Killerton with its fine country house, gardens, grounds and arboretum lies about five miles to the south.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Security coded gated entrance leads to Clarks Court main entrance with internal hallways leading to front door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hallway</span><span lang="en-GB"> two deep storage cupboards, Tunstall emergency on call device, deep airing cupboard with hotwater system, shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room/ dining room </span><span lang="en-GB">a lovely bright and airy room with dual aspect looking out onto the grounds of the complex. Two windows, stone effect fireplace housing electric coal fire, two night storage heaters, telephone and television points.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> excellently thought out and well equipped with range of light ash effect units having brushed stainless steel handles and comprising five base cupboards with drawers over, integrated fridge and freezer, marble effect roll edge working surfaces with inset stainless steel single drainer sink, inset AEG ceramic hob and eye level AEG electric oven, cooker hood/extractor, eight matching wall cupboards, fan heater, windows with views over the established gardens, spot lighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1,</span><span lang="en-GB"> excellent dual aspect double bedroom, night storage heater, range of mirror fronted wardrobes, telephone point, view over garden.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2 </span><span lang="en-GB">another double room with window outlook over garden, night storage heater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Shower Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> recently refitted walk in shower/ wet room area, close coupled WC, pedestal basin with mirror cupboard over, electric towel rail, window, extractor, wall mounted fan heater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">This gated complex is approached through security pedestrian and vehicular gates leading to a parking area with delightful grounds beyond comprising extensive areas of lawn, pergola with patio and a charming lake, the maintenance for which is included in the service charge.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2604, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10548, 'No Prefix', 579500, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 4, 'Oakford', 'Oakford, Uffculme', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A rural edge of village location is the setting for this stunning individual home with pony paddock and stables. Oakford was a skilfully designed and built &ldquo;period country home&rdquo; constructed by the present owners for their own occupation about fifteen years ago.</p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Nestling in a rural edge of village setting at the foot of the Blackdown Hills an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty yet being within the catchment for the highly regarded Uffculme School.&nbsp; Uffculme also provides a Post Office stores, One Stop shop and frequent bus services down the Culm Valley to Exeter and to Tiverton.&nbsp; A more extensive range of everyday shopping facilities are to be found in the nearby country town of Cullompton with its supermarket, sports centre, doctors and M5 intersection facilitating rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the stunning north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Heavy timber front door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Enclosed entrance</span><span lang="en-GB"> Porch </span><span lang="en-GB">with two windows and terracotta tiled floor, panelled inner front door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Large T shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall </span><span lang="en-GB">two radiators, heavily beamed ceiling, walk in understairs cupboard, cloaks cupboard with hanging rail and shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom </span><span lang="en-GB">suite in white comprising close coupled WC, vanity wash basin with cupboards beneath, window, radiator, quarry tiled floor, extractor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Fine </span><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room/Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> having three windows enjoying country views towards Blackdown Hills, three radiators, stone and brick inglenook with slate hearth, heavy Bressumer beam over, concealed lighting, housing wood burning stove, beamed ceiling.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Farmhouse style </span><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> well appointed with extensive range of mid oak units comprising base cupboards with granite effect roll edge working surfaces over, inset Asterite single drainer sink, six wall cupboards, shelving, oil fired Stanley cooker providing cooking, domestic hot water and central heating, three windows enjoying outlook over gardens towards stable block, beamed ceiling, central island unit with hardwood top, cupboards, radiator, down lighting, space and plumbing for dishwasher, terracotta tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room </span><span lang="en-GB">with continuation of terracotta tiled floor, half glazed back door, base unit with worktop and inset stainless steel sink, plumbing and space for washing machine, wall cupboard, radiator, larder, archway to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Laundry Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with L shaped base unit, </span><span lang="en-GB">WC</span><span lang="en-GB"> with extractor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Study</span><span lang="en-GB"> outlook over gardens, radiator, beamed ceiling.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Wide elegant staircase leading to part vaulted L shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> two radiators, two windows with outlook towards Blackdown Hills, exposed wall timbers, airing cupboard with hot water cylinder and slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Master Bedroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> with floor to ceiling arched feature window with outlook over farmland to Blackdowns, vaulted ceiling with exposed timbers, range of two double and one single fitted wardrobes, radiator, door to</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite Shower Room </span><span lang="en-GB">tiled shower with mains mixer, pedestal wash basin, close coupled WC, dressing table with cupboard and drawers, part tiled walls, radiator, window.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2 </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, exposed timbers, double and single fitted wardrobe, access to loft.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3 </span><span lang="en-GB">two windows, radiator, exposed timbers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4 </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, exposed timbers, feature curved wall, outlook over stable block to adjoining countryside.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Family </span><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">with white suite comprising panelled bath, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, tiled shower with mains mixer, part tiled walls, radiator, window, extractor, down lighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span>Outside</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The property is approached through twin wooden gates with side pedestrian gate leading to an extensive gravelled driveway terminating in a parking area and concreted yard flanked by outbuildings comprising open fronted double garage 17&rsquo;6&rdquo; x 15&rsquo;6&rdquo; with light and power, workshop 33&rsquo; x 17&rsquo; light and power, concrete floor, up and over door.&nbsp; Adjoining the workshop lies the stable yard comprising tack room, feed store and three loose boxes each about 12&rsquo; x 12&rsquo; with concrete floor and kicking boards.&nbsp; From the entrance drive a separate lane leads to the paddocks, a gravelled path leads through the front cottage garden with extensive herbaceous borders interspersed with established shrubs, extensive south facing patio for alfresco entertaining with timber door leading through garden wall to the back door and continuation of gravelled pathway leading to the back garden with areas of lawn and a variety of established shrubs enjoying an outlook towards Uffculme village and the Blackdown Hills.&nbsp; Wrought iron gate leading to the main area of formal gardens with large ornamental fish pond and sweeping lawns interspersed with a wide assortment of established trees and shrubs.&nbsp; Extensive outdoor entertaining area comprising paved terracing flanked by brick walling with lighting and power and leading to extensive wisteria clad pergola and semi covered paved terrace.&nbsp; Two further timber store sheds with post and rail fencing flanking the gardens on two sides with gate and stile leading to the pony paddock in two enclosures post and rail fenced on three sides, traditional mixed hedging, field shelter.&nbsp; The paddocks amounting to about 1</span><span lang="en-GB">&frac12;</span><span lang="en-GB"> acres.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2481, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10022, 'No Prefix', 9500, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Under offer', 0, '4 High Street', '4 High Street, Cullompton, Devon', 'EX15 1AA', '<ul>\r\n<li>Lock up shop 69 sq m (744 sq ft) plus upper parts 34 sq m (366 sq ft) further 39.5 sq m (425 sq ft) may also be available.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent location in the wide tree lined High Street of the busy town of Cullompotn.</li>\r\n<li>Planning consent for change of use to A3/A5 (restaurant/cafe, hot food takeaways).</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION &amp; AMENITIES: </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">( please note distances are approximate).</span></p>\r\n<p>Situated in a prime location close to the Junction of Fore Street the main shopping street and High Street the wide tree lined former Bullring adjoining on one side bank premises (vacant) and on the other an estate agents office with limited on street parking nearby.&nbsp; Cullompton is an active shopping centre with a wide range of retail and service outlets and lies adjacent to M5 Junction 28.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">ACCOMMODATION:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; Access by covered side entrance to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SHOP 14.3m average x 3.8m average with large shop window to the High Street frontage where there is a wide pavement.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Stairs off to </span></p>\r\n<p>First Floor</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>REAR OFFICE</strong> approximately&nbsp; 3.32m average by 2.56m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>REAR ENTRANCE</strong> LOBBY 2.6m x 2.075m average.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">On the First Floor</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Approached by the staircase from the shop area.-</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Landing.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TWO ROOMS 4.7m x 4.1m and 3.7m x 1.9m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WC with wash basin.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">In addition to the premises referred to above there is further ground floor storage accommodation of approximately </span><span lang="en-GB">39.5sq m (425sq ft) which may be included in the premises by negotiation.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Mains water, electricity, drainage and gas are connected.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">PLANNING: </span></strong></p>\r\n<p>The premises have been used as retail shop for many years.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Planning consent was granted Reference 08/01192/4 FULL (to extend a time limit) for change of use of the premises from A1 (retail) to A3/A5 (use for restaurant/cafe hot food takeaways).</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">LEASES:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises are available on a medium to long term lease.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The tenant will pay the landlord&rsquo;s legal expenses in drawing up the lease.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">RENT</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &pound;9,500 per annum.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>VIEWING:</strong> </span><span lang="en-GB">By appointment through the agents Thorne &amp; Carter, 01884 33333</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none;">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2597, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'per annum', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', '');
