(10567, 'No Prefix', 325000, 'Freehold', 'Bungalow', 'Viewing', 4, 'BORDHAY', 'Church Lane, Sheldon', 'EX14 4QU', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This individually designed detached country bungalow enjoys a glorious rural setting on the outskirts of Sheldon village. An early inspection is recommended to those seeking a country lifestyle with a comparatively modern property offering scope for improvement.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Enjoying a glorious rural setting high in the Blackdown Hills on the outskirts of the small village of Sheldon.&nbsp; A school bus serves the highly regarded Uffculme Secondary School and everyday shopping, schooling and transport facilities are to be found in the nearby country towns of Cullompton and Honiton.&nbsp; The M5 intersection at Cullompton facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter or north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The Blackdown Hills are designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty and provide a wealth of rural pursuits.&nbsp; The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Recessed entrance </span><span lang="en-GB">porch</span><span lang="en-GB"> to heavy hand made oak front door to</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Large T shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> with wide section ideal for computer, desk etc, airing cupboard with hot water cylinder having immersion heater and cupboards over, double cupboard, top cupboards, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting room </span><span lang="en-GB">bright and airy dual aspect room with sliding patio door enjoying outlook over garden and surrounding countryside, Much Wenlock (Aga) multi fuel stove having back boiler providing central heating, set in quarry tiled fireplace with oak mantel over.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/breakfast room </span><span lang="en-GB">having L shaped range of hessian effect pale laminate units with timber trim, seven base units, two drawer packs, matching work top having inset 1</span><span lang="en-GB">&frac12;</span><span lang="en-GB"> bowl stainless steel sink, mixer tap, five wall units, tiled fireplace with solid fuel Rayburn Royal providing domestic hot water, radiator, dual aspect, delightful country views, inset ceramic hob.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility room/dairy </span><span lang="en-GB">ideal as additional reception room having double base unit with stainless steel sink, tall cupboard, lovely country views, plumbing for washing machine, half glazed back to rear porch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1&nbsp; </span></span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect, radiator, double fitted wardrobe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2 </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3 </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect, radiator, country views, double fitted wardrobe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">with ample space for separate shower and having coloured suite comprising panelled bath, close coupled WC, wash basin, radiator, light/shaver fitment, Dimplex wall heater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The property is approached off the lane through wide five bar gate leading to an extensive tarmac drive and turning area leading to the attached extra large garage with up and over door, utility/storage area, WC with white suite, extensive loft storage area.&nbsp; Generous gardens ready for cultivation and landscaping provide a blank canvas for the gardening enthusiast and surround the bungalow on four sides.&nbsp; Traditional Devon bank to the front and post and rail fencing on the remaining three sides.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2513, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10508, 'No Prefix', 60, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Crown Works Office', 'Office at 37 Higher Street', '', '<ul>\r\n<li>To let</li>\r\n<li>Office 368 sq ft</li>\r\n<li>In a prominent location</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION AND AMENITIES:&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">(of which distance are approximate):- </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">With frontage to the main arterial road through the town of Cullompton which is on junction 28 of the M5 Motorway.&nbsp; Exeter is 15 miles, Taunton is 18 miles and Tiverton 6 miles. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ACCOMMODATION: </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">FRONT OFFICE 24&rsquo;9&rdquo; av x 14&rsquo; 9&rdquo;overall approximately, divided into two workspaces and with toilet.&nbsp; This office is on the ground floor and the external wall is in a prominent position to traffic through the main street of the town and therefore lends itself to marketing subject to planning</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">OUTSIDE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Two parking spaces will be made available with the office.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES: </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main electricity, water and drainage.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">RATES:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office &pound;1,500.&nbsp; If the tenants business qualifies (as most do) for small business relief then concessions of up to 100% of the rates will be made.&nbsp; Interested parties should assume eligibility with the Council. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PLANNING:&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises have been used as offices for many years.&nbsp; Enquiries should be made of the Planning Authority, which is Mid Devon District Council 01884 255255, to confirm that any particular prospective use can be pursued without the need to make a planning application. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">EPC: </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">An Energy Performance Assessment is being arranged by the owner. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">LEASE:</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The offices are available on a short to medium term lease at &pound;60 per week. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The tenant will be asked to pay the landlord&rsquo;s lawyers costs in drawing up this lease, likely to be in the order of &pound;500.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A WORKSHOP ALSO AVAILABLE: </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A workshop of 2,357 square feet is also currently available at Crown Works. - please contact Thorne &amp; Carter for details.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">VIEWING: </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">By appointment please with Messrs </span><span lang="en-GB">Thorne &amp; Carter. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none;"><span style="language: en-GB; mso-ligatures: none;" lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2505, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'pw', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10220, 'No Prefix', 270, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Unit Q', 'Unit Q Langlands Bus Park', '', '<ul>\r\n<li>Workshop/storage unit of 3550 sq ft (1082 square metres) of about 0.06 acres.</li>\r\n<li>On a large rural estate of similar units just outside Uffculme.</li>\r\n<li>M5 junction 27 to the north and Junction 28 4.5 miles south</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>SITUATION:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On a popular large rural estate of units of a similar type just outside the village of Uffculme and with excellent access with M5 junction 27 to the north with a branch to the north Devon link road 2 miles and junction 28 of the M5 motorway at Cullompton to the south 4.5 miles.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The unit is located at the entrance to the estate and approached over its own forecourt.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>TYPE:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The unit is constructed of concrete block with freshly lined and insulated sheeted roof, comprising LOADING BAY 34&rsquo; x 17&rsquo;1&rdquo; (10.38m x 5.21m) with entrance doors to opening 12&rsquo;8&rdquo; (3.9m) wide x 8&rsquo;5&rdquo; (2.6m) high and including OFFICE 15&rsquo;7&rdquo; (4.78m)&nbsp; x 10&rsquo;11&rdquo; (3.32m) and WC.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">MAIN WORKSHOP/STORAGE AREA 64&rsquo; (19.5m) approximately x 34&rsquo; (10.37m) including enclosed area 18&rsquo; (5.48m) x 16&rsquo; (4.88m) with ample lighting and power points.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">STORAGE BAY 64&rsquo; (19.6m) x 12&rsquo; (3.67m) with external loading door 9&rsquo;4&rdquo; (2.82m) x 8&rsquo;11&rdquo; (2.7m) high.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>OUTSIDE:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Forecourt/parking area.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>EPC:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">An energy performance certificate has been applied for. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>SERVICES:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main electricity (3 phase) and mains water.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Private drainage.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>TERMS OF OCCUPATION:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Occupation of the unit will be on the basis of an agreement on negotiated flexible terms.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>VIEWING:</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">By appointment please with Messrs Thorne &amp; Carter.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2674, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'per week', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10557, 'No Prefix', 159950, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Hidden', 2, '16 HELE ROAD, BRADNINCH', 'Hele Road, Bradninch', 'EX5 4QX', '<ul>\r\n<li>Semi detached village cottage</li>\r\n<li>2 reception rooms</li>\r\n<li>2 double bedrooms</li>\r\n<li>Fitted kitchen</li>\r\n<li>Ground floor bathroom</li>\r\n<li>Generous gardens</li>\r\n<li>Garage and brick outbuilding</li>\r\n<li>Extensive parking/caravan/boat storage</li>\r\n<li>Economy 7 heating, UPVc double glazing</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">This charming semi detached village cottage is set well back from Hele Road and enjoys generous gardens together with garage, former outbuilding and ample space for caravan/boat storage.&nbsp; The electric heating and hot water is supplied by means of Economy 7 tariff and double glazing is incorporated.&nbsp; The ground floor accommodation provides two reception rooms, kitchen and bathroom whilst on the first floor two double bedrooms are to be found.&nbsp; An early inspection of this semi detached non estate village home with immense potential for extension subject to planning consents.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>On the ground floor</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Double glazed front door to entrance </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> with stairs to first floor.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Sitting room </span><span lang="en-GB">charming room with traditional marble effect fireplace and hearth having inset electric fire, (original open grate presently blocked off), pleasant outlook over front garden towards Bithywind and Ashclyst Forest, part glazed door to front garden, night storage heater.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Dining room </span><span lang="en-GB">outlook over side garden, night storage heater, fireplace (presently blocked off), understairs cupboard with power point for freezer, airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder, slatted shelving, timer for electric immersion on Economy 7 tariff, sliding door to</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> range of hessian effect units with timber trim comprising five base cupboards with roll top work surfaces over and inset Asterite 1</span><span lang="en-GB">&frac12;</span><span lang="en-GB"> bowl single drainer sink, integrated fridge, inset ceramic hob with oven beneath and cooker hood/extractor over, six wall cupboards, space and plumbing for washing machine, two with glazed doors, part tiled walls, dual aspect.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> having coloured suite comprising panelled bath with electric shower over, shower screen, close coupled WC, corner vanity basin with cupboard beneath, ceramic tiled floor, part tiled walls, electric heater, extractor fan, window.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">On the first floor</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Cottage stairs to </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB">.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1 </span><span lang="en-GB">electric panel radiator, views to Ashclyst Forest and Paradise Copse.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> electric panel radiator, deep fitted cupboard.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">Outside</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">To the front the property is approached through a pedestrian gate passing the front garden with path leading to front and side doors, two principle areas of lawn to the side with flower beds, gravelled areas of hard landscaping and flanked by brick and stone walling with path leading to the rear garden.&nbsp; Vehicular access is provided off Townlands with a concrete drive leading to the detached single garage with up and over door, power connected and adjoining which is a further paved and gravelled area with clothes line and useful traditional brick outbuilding providing storage or workshop facility.&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">Ample space for additional car, caravan or boat storage.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2493, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10650, 'No Prefix', 225000, 'Freehold', 'Terrace', 'Viewing', 2, '10 Longmeadow, Broadclyst', 'Longmeadow, Broadclyst', 'EX5 3JF', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>An absolutely stunning 2 bedroom property in this delightful cul de sac within the grounds of Hay House. The house has been recently renovated to the highest of standards with a fablous new Kitchen and two exquisite bathrooms having been fitted</span></p>', '<p>Absolutely stunning best describes this completely renovated comparatively modern semi detached home in a wonderful rural setting on this tiny development in the grounds of a former country mansion. 10 Longmeadow offers the best of both worlds with its generously proportioned rooms, brand new kitchen and newly refitted bathroom and shower room. This versatile property offers stylish living with country walks on the doorstep whilst being within easy reach of all that the bustling city of Exeter has to offer. An early interior viewing is strongly recommended. <br /> <br />Gloriously located in the grounds of Hay House about half a mile from the popular village of Broadclyst which in turn is only about 15 minutes from Exeter centre. The Cathedral City of Exeter offers a wonderful range of high street shops together with the renowned Princesshay Shopping Mall with its mix of major retailers and eating haunts. Broadclyst offers both secondary and primary education with a further range of state and independent education being provided in Exeter. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with glorious walks being enjoyed through the gardens, grounds and arboretum of the famous National Trust Killerton Estate. The comparatively central Mid Devon Location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. <br /> <br />Fabulously refitted semi detached home <br />UPVc double glazing and new electric heating <br />Hall <br />Lounge/dining room <br />Ultra modern refitted kitchen <br />Refitted ground floor shower room <br />Ground floor bedroom 2 <br />Master bedroom with dressing area and walk-in wardrobe <br />Stunning family bathroom <br />Small decked &ldquo;Japanese style&rdquo; garden <br />Garage <br />Mains water, private sewerage plant <br />Maintenance charge &pound;75 per month to include grounds maintenance, water and shared private sewage plant <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />UPVc part glazed front door to <br />Entrance Lobby fitted floor mat. <br />Lounge/Dining Room superb through room with window overlooking front garden and sliding double glazed patio doors to rear garden, two electric panel radiators, wide archway to Inner Hall. <br />Kitchen newly refitted with superb range of ultra modern white high gloss units having brushed stainless steel handles comprising base cupboards, double pan drawer unit, integrated Whirlpool dishwasher, integrated Whirlpool washing machine, timber effect roll edged worktops having inset touch controlled ceramic hob with oven under and brushed stainless steel cooker hood/extractor over, stylish corner stainless steel one and a half single drainer sink, mixer tap, spotlighting, under pelmet worktop illumination, &ldquo;pop-up&rdquo; power point unit, electric panel radiator, space for fridge-freezer, pleasant out look to the front, marble tile effect flooring. <br />Inner Hall with fitted shelved cupboard, electric panel radiator, turning stairs to first floor. <br /> <br />Shower Room newly refitted with stylish white suite comprising walk in shower with 5ft 6in shower tray and Triton electric shower, frameless shower screen, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, electric panel radiator with towel rail, fully tiled marble effect walls, window. <br />Bedroom 2 currently used as a sitting room with bed settee for visitors, electric panel radiator, outlook over rear garden. <br />Pretty turning staircase to L-shaped Landing fitted shelved cupboard, airing cupboard housing lagged hot water cylinder with dual immersion, access to loft. <br /> <br />On the first floor <br />Master Bedroom lovely bright and airy room enjoying southerly outlook over the cul-de-sac to farmland and hills beyond, Dessing Area with electric panel radiator, twin doors to vast walk in wardrobe with three hanging rails. <br />Family Bathroom again newly refitted with white suite comprising P-shaped bath with central mixer tap and folding frameless shower screen, Mira electric shower, close coupled WC, wash basin, electric panel radiator with towel rail, door to extensive under eaves storage, part tiled walls, extractor. <br /> <br />Outside <br />Area of lawn with path leading to front door, small rear garden approached from the lounge/dining room and with rear pedestrian door, entirely decked with Japanese style translucent panels ensuring privacy. A driveway leads behind the property to the single Garage of rendered construction beneath a tiled roof matching the house, extensive loft storage area, up and over door.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2618, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10652, 'No Prefix', 175000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Sale Agreed', 4, 'Barn 1 Goodiford', 'Goodiford, Kentisbeare', 'Ex152AS', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>A fabulous GRAND DESIGNS opportunity. Detached agricultural barn with planning permission to created 4 bedroomed country home. Glorious rural setting about half a mile from Kentisbeare village. Useful outbuilding and set in gardens, grounds and paddocks of approximately 0.9 acres.</span></p>', '<p>A fabulous &lsquo;Grand Designs&rsquo; opportunity is offered by this gloriously located detached barn in a rural setting only half a mile from Kentisbeare village at the foot of the Blackdown Hills. This agricultural building has planning permission for the creation of a detached family home comprising 4/5 bedrooms, two bathrooms, sitting room, study/bedroom 5 and country kitchen/dining room. Outside a useful outbuilding provides store/workshop/garage. From the established gardens a bridge leads over the small stream to the level southfacing paddock and in all the property extends to about 0.9 acre subject to survey. <br /> <br />The tiny hamlet of Goodiford lies about a quarter of a mile west of the picturesque village of Kentisbeare nestling at the foot of the Blackdown Hills an area designated as being of outstanding Natural Beauty. Glorious walks abound in the village whilst the nearby Goodiford Mill fishery is a delight for local anglers. The village offers a post office stores, thriving primary school, public house, church and modern village hall with a more extensive range of shopping facilities being available in the nearby country town of Cullompton. The property lies within the catchment for the highly regarded Uffculme secondary school with the school bus picking up in the lane outside. The M5 at Cullompton facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton. The comparatively central Mid Devon location place the 