(9138, 'No Prefix', 170, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, 'First Floor Period Offices, Ingleby, ', '42 High Street, Cullompton', 'EX151AE', '<ul>\r\n<li>Two period&nbsp;offices on first floor level, refurbished with gas central heating.</li>\r\n<li>12.5 sq m and 15.6 sq m. (135 sq ft and 165 sq ft).</li>\r\n<li>Excellent location in the wide part of the High Street in Cullompton.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p align="justify"><strong>SITUATION AND AMENITIES:</strong> (please note that distances are&nbsp;approximate)&nbsp; Occupying an excellent office location in the wide part of High Street amongst Dentists and other health practitioners, solicitors, estate agents and retail uses, prominently situated for those entering the town from the M5 motorway and with limited streetside public parking in front and longer term parking within easy walking distance.&nbsp; Cullompton has expanded considerably in recent years (population of over 7,500) and is an active town with production and distribution industries and at the centre of a wide agricultural district.</p>\r\n<p align="justify">The town offers a comprehensive selection of shops, sporting and recreational clubs and communications are excellent with Junction 28 on the M5 being on the outskirts of the town and which gives easy access to Exeter 13 miles and Taunton 18 miles and the north.&nbsp; Tiverton Parkway station with its daily&nbsp;services to Paddington is 5 miles.</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><strong>DESCRIPTION:</strong>&nbsp; The offices are two of three first floor rooms of an early Victorian Georgian style town house which has been refurbished and has gas-fired central heating by radiators.&nbsp; Carpets are fitted.&nbsp; The accommodation is particularly attractive.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align="justify">Approached through an attractive common entrance hall by a staircase which is lit by a tall Victorian style window to spacious landing affording access to:</p>\r\n<p align="justify"><strong>OFFICE 1</strong>: 4.5m x 2.79m 