(10645, 'No Prefix', 160000, 'Leasehold', 'Flat', 'Viewing', 2, '10 Clarks Court', 'Cullompton', 'EX15 1FB', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Very well presented retirement flat, having two bedrooms, sitting room, kitchen and shower room. Located on the same floor as the main entrance, access is easy. An early viewing is recommended!</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Security coded gated entrance leads to Clarks Court main entrance with internal hallways leading to front door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hallway</span><span lang="en-GB"> deep storage cupboard, Tunstall emergency on call device, deep airing cupboard with hotwater system, shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room/ Dining room </span><span lang="en-GB">slightly L shaped with night storage heater, UPVc double glazed patio door to small paved patio and shrubbery, television aerial point, night storage heater, telephone point, Tunstall alarm system, twin glass panelled doors to</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen </span><span lang="en-GB">extensively fitted with range of light ash effect units comprising six base cupboards, integrated fridge, intergrated freezer, marble effect roll edge worktop with inset stainless steel single drainer sink unit having mixer tap over, inset AEG ceramic hob, AEG cooker hood over, AEG electric oven, eight matching wall cupboards, window with distant views to Blackdown hills, spot light cluster.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1 </span><span lang="en-GB">excellent double room with night storage heater, fitted double wardrobe with bi-fold mirror fronted doors, hanging rail and shelving, dual aspect, telephone point, views to distant Blackdown Hills.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2 </span><span lang="en-GB">electric panel radiator, views to distant Blackdown hills.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">walk in shower with mains shower, glass shower screen, close coupled WC, vanity wash basin with cupboard beneath, fully tiled walls, light/ shaver fitment, extractor fan, Creda wall mounted fan heater, electic towel rail.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">This gated complex is approached through security pedestrian and vehicular gates leading to a parking area with delightful grounds beyond comprising extensive areas of lawn, pergola with patio and a charming lake, the maintenance for which is included in the service charge. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2614, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '79', '81', '69', '74'),
(10671, 'No Prefix', 324995, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 3, '21 Worcester Crescent', 'Worcester Crescent, Willand', 'EX15 2TA', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>A quite stunning three bedroom bungalow situated in what has to be one of the most desireable cul-de-sac''s in Willand. The property has been superbly updated by the current owners making this home a very rare find</span></p>', '<p>To Follow</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2635, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10667, 'No Prefix', 165000, 'Freehold', 'Terrace', 'Sale Agreed', 3, '3 Wishcroft Terrace', 'Wishcroft Terrace, Cullompton', 'EX15 1AL', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>An Incredibly Spacious three bedroom family home set well back from the Willand road going out of Cullompton. The property offers light and airy accomodation with a remarkably large rear garden as well as a lawned frontage.</span></p>', '<p>Wishcroft Terrace now comprises four houses and is believed to have originally been a period farmhouse with a Victorian extension and fa&ccedil;ade along the front. The spacious and characterful accommodation exhibits the high ceilings and character associated with the era. UPVc double glazed windows and storage heating have been incorporated and the accommodation extends to two reception rooms, a modern kitchen, ground floor bathroom and three bedrooms (one with ensuite WC) on the first floor. The west facing garden offers space ideal for al fresco entertaining and also offers a useful shed. This characterful home will surely appeal to those seeking a centrally located home close to Cullompton&rsquo;s amenities whilst being well set back from the road. <br /> <br />Set well back from Higher Street the property is well placed to take advantage of the High Street shops, two supermarkets, doctors surgeries, primary schools and secondary school. Cullompton also offers a library, sports centre, Padbrook golf course and leisure centre and the recently completed community centre. The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty. The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Exmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. <br /> <br />Remarkably spacious period town house <br />Characterful accommodation <br />UPVc double glazing <br />Night storage heating <br />Lounge with open fire <br />Dining room <br />Modern kitchen <br />Ground floor bathroom <br />3 bedrooms one with ensuite WC <br />Gardens front and rear <br />15 miles Exeter, 18 miles Taunton <br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles <br />Main electricity, water and drainage <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />Attractive Victorian Porch with wrought iron pillars and decorative features with slate roof, heavy timber front door, glazed panel to <br />Entrance Lobby Victorian inner front door with stained glass panels and panel over, long Hall stairs to first floor. <br />Sitting Room spacious room, typical of the period with bay window, tall ceilings, picture rail, lovely Victorian fireplace with tiled inserts and hearth, mantel over, open grate, night storage heater. <br />Dining Room lovely characterful room with massive brick fireplace housing cast iron woodburning stove (flue not presently connected). Original floor to ceiling china cupboard to alcove with glazed doors above and cupboards beneath, door to walk in understair cupboard with fitted shelving and coat hooks, recess with shelving, beamed ceiling, night storage heater, wide archway to <br />Kitchen well appointed with modern range of white units, comprising seven base cupboards, drawer pack, marble effect worktops with inset ceramic hob and brushed stainless steel electric oven under, inset stainless steel single drainer sink, space and plumbing for washing machine, six wall cupboards, part tiled walls, tile effect flooring, spot lighting, UPVc double glazed door to rear garden. <br />Bathroom with suite in grey comprising bath with electric shower over, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, fully tiled walls, fan heater, window, extractor, airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder and immersion heater, slatted shelving. <br /> <br /> <br />On the First Floor <br />Elegant staircase to Landing linen cupboard with shelving. <br />Bedroom 1 access to loft, storage heater. <br />Bedroom 2 storage heater, ensuite WC with washbasin and low level suite. <br />Bedroom 3 wardrobe with hanging rail and shelving, curtain to front, storage heater. <br /> <br /> <br />Outside <br />Tucked away behind a low wall and mature laurel hedge the property is approached through a lawned front garden leading to the Victorian veranda/porch. A pedestrian access leads off Higher Orchard Lane, to serve the rear garden being west facing with raised area of paved patio and lawn beyond. Shrubs and &ldquo;stepping stones&rdquo; to timber garden shed with covered lean-to behind.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2636, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10630, 'No Prefix', 249950, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 3, '10 Elmside Willand', 'Elmside, Willand Old Village', 'EX15 2RN ', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Tucked away at the end of a small cul-de-sac on the outskirts of Willand Old Village this detached bungalow nestles in a particularly generous well tended plot with distant views of the Blackdown Hills.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Tucked away at the end of a small cul-de-sac on the outskirts of Willand Old Village this detached bungalow nestles in a particularly generous well tended plot with distant views of the Blackdown Hills.&nbsp; The present owner has installed gas fired central heating and UPVc double glazing together with a kitchen extension allowing two separate reception rooms.&nbsp; Three bedrooms and a bathroom with electric shower complete the accommodation.&nbsp; An early inspection is recommended to those seeking a detached bungalow on the outskirts of the village.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Pleasantly tucked away only about a quarter of a mile from the village post office stores and with a frequent bus service to Exeter and Tiverton.&nbsp; Willand also offers a primary school, one stop shop and doctors surgery, whilst only two miles to the south the country town of Cullompton provides high street shopping and two supermarkets.&nbsp; A sports centre and golf course with leisure centre are also available in Cullompton. The nearby M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; Willand lies at the foot of the Blackdown Hills an area designated as being of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The spectacular National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Part glazed front door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, one wall entirely mirror fronted fitted cupboards with hanging rail and shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom </span><span lang="en-GB">with white WC and vanity washbasin with cupboards beneath, wall mounted gas fired boiler, tiled floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Part glazed inner door to </span><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room </span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;lovely bright and airy room with vast picture window enjoying views to distant Blackdown Hills, radiator, Portland stone feature fireplace and hearth, two wall light points, archway to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, UPVc sliding patio doors to rear garden.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> well appointed with extensive range of white fronted units with natural timber trim and comprising eight base cupboards, many with drawers over, two tall cupboards, tall housing with eye level oven, timber effect worktops with inset stainless steel one and half bowl single drainer sink, inset four ring electric hob with cooker hood over, </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">seven wall cupboards, breakfast bar, dual aspect, pleasant out look over rear garden, door to garage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Inner Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> linen cupboard with shelving, storage cupboard, access to loft.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> double wardrobe with storage cupboards over, radiator, views to distant Blackdown Hills.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, double wardrobe with storage cupboards over, outlook over rear gardens.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3 </span><span lang="en-GB">fitted double wardrobe with cupboards over, radiator, outlook over rear garden.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Driveway leading to small recessed </span><span lang="en-GB">carport/storage area</span><span lang="en-GB"> with </span><span lang="en-GB">garage</span><span lang="en-GB"> beyond, extensive front lawn flanked by well stocked and tended perennial borders.&nbsp; Side pedestrian access to large fully fenced and remarkably private rear garden with large central lawn flanked by well stocked borders. Kitchen garden with soft fruit, cooking and eating apples, extensive paved patio with climber clad pergola over part the whole providing a safe environment for children and pets.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2602, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10574, 'No Prefix', 249000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Hidden', 3, 'Old Brooke', 'Fore Street, Kentisbeare', 'EX15 2AD', '<ul>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Major portion of historic Grade II listed period farmhouse</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Recently replaced handmade windows</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Oil central heating</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Hall with cloakroom</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Fine lounge with massive inglenook</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Dining room</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">3 Bedrooms</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Wet room</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Cottage gardens front and rear</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">17 miles Exeter, 24 miles Taunton</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 4 miles</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Exeter International Airport 15 miles</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Mains electricity, water and drainage</span>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Kentisbeare lies at the foot of the Blackdown Hills, an area designated as being of Outstanding Natural Beauty and where glorious walks may be enjoyed.&nbsp; The village boasts a Post Office stores, public house, primary school and church, whilst a more extensive range of facilities are to be found in the nearby country town of Cullompton with its High Street shops and supermarkets.&nbsp; The M5 intersection at Cullompton facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the historic National Trust country estates at Killerton and Knightshayes being readily accessible.&nbsp; The glorious National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Half glazed front door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Oak framed </span><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory</span><span lang="en-GB"> with staging, shelving a</span><span lang="en-GB">light, door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> having close coupled suite, wash basin, extractor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> fine characterful room, two radiators, window overlooking rear garden, ceiling beam, massive stone inglenook with fire basket and iron fire back, canopy, heavy Bressumer beam over.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Inner</span><span lang="en-GB">Hall </span><span lang="en-GB">with understairs cupboard door to front porch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, beamed ceiling, stone fireplace and hearth, timber mantel, exposed Bressumer beam.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> range of mid oak units comprising eight base cupboards, roll edged worktops with inset stainless steel single drainer sink, six wall cupboards, plate rack, space and plumbing for washing machine, free standing electric cooker, quarry tiled floor, stable door to rear garden, wide staircase to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">U-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> well lit by flank window, access to loft.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> view up Fore Street towards the Village Square, pretty Victorian cast iron basket fireplace with timber surround, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, lovely outlook over the River Kenn towards Bridge House and open countryside, fitted wardrobe with shelf and hanging rail.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, views over the River Kenn towards open countryside.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Wet Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with Mira Advance electric shower, close coupled WC, wash basin, radiator, airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder and immersion heater, slatted shelving, extractor fan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The property is approached from Fore Street through a wrought iron gate in the ancient stone garden wall with path leading through the cottage gardens with creeper clad rustic arbour leading to the front door.&nbsp; Rear garden principally lawned with some shrubs and fruit trees, timber garden </span><span lang="en-GB">Shed</span><span lang="en-GB"> 12&rsquo; x 10&rsquo; power connected, oil fired boiler providing hot water and central heating. Two parking spaces, enclosure for oil storage tank.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none; text-align: justify; text-justify: newspaper; text-kashida-space: 50%;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2548, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10640, 'No Prefix', 325000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Sale Agreed', 3, 'Clyst Lea, Clyst Hydon', 'Clyst Hydon', 'EX15 2ND', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This fine detached country home was designed and built by the present owners for their own occupation on the rural outskirts of ever popular Clyst Hydon village. Oil fired central heating and double glazing combine with high levels of insulation to provide an economically run village home.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">This fine detached country home was designed and built by the present owners for their own occupation on the rural outskirts of ever popular Clyst Hydon village.&nbsp; Oil fired central heating and double glazing combine with high levels of insulation to provide an economically run village home.&nbsp; The versatile accommodation offers on the ground floor, a sitting room, a dining room, kitchen/breakfast room and a master bedroom with en-suite shower whilst on the first floor two double bedrooms and family bathroom are to be found.&nbsp; The property was built in the grounds of the old manor house and in consequence the gardens are of a generous size with the &ldquo;instant maturity&rdquo; offered by such a site.&nbsp; An early inspection is recommended to those seeking an individual modern country home. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Constructed in the grounds of a fine country home in the tiny village of Clyst Hydon with its thriving primary school and popular Five Bells Public House.&nbsp; A useful range of everyday shopping facilities is to be found in nearby Cullompton with its High Street shops and two supermarkets together with two doctors surgeries, sports centre and Padbrook Golf Course and Leisure Centre.&nbsp; Junction 28 of the M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton and beyond. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as being an area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The Cathedral city of Exeter offers a superb range of shops, independent schooling and culture with its picturesque quayside developments.&nbsp; The spectacular National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Canopy entrance porch to timber panelled front door</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&lsquo;T&rsquo;shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">hall, </span><span lang="en-GB">coat cupboard with hanging rail.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Airing cupboard </span><span lang="en-GB">with lagged hot water cylinder and immersion heater, shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting room</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; charming triple aspect room enjoying glorious views over mature grounds, radiator, French door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect with bay window, radiator, shelved recess, wide archway to </span><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/breakfast room&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">range of laminate fronted units with timber trim comprising ten base cupboards, drawer pack, roll edged worktop, stainless steel single bowl twin drainer sink unit, five wall cupboards, freestanding Tricity electric cooker, wide window enjoying lovely rural outlook, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room </span><span lang="en-GB">base unit with single drainer sink, worktop adjoining, space and plumbing for washing machine, oil fire boiler, radiator, glazed door to loggia.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Master bedroom </span><span lang="en-GB">another bright and airy dual aspect room with bay window, lovely outlook, two fitted wardrobes with shelving and hanging rail, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite shower room&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">fully tiled shower with Mira mains shower, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, extractor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Charming fully returning staircase with half landing, well lit by flank window</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Landing, </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, shelved cupboard</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2 </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect enjoying lovely outlook, radiator, two fitted wardrobes with shelving and hanging rail, door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Extensive loft storage area </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3 </span><span lang="en-GB">another bright and airy dual aspect room, radiator</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Family bathroom with ivory suite comprising panelled bath, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, radiator, loft access, part tiled walls</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Five bar gate leading to gravelled drive and parking area with adjoining carport, gravelled drive leading to front door, continuing through the front garden to the rear with sweeping lawns running down to the village brook. Having a variety of magnificent specimen trees, two ornamental ponds linked by waterfall, clematis and wisteria clad pergola, extensive paved terracing, timber shed, the whole being flanked by post and rail fencing and hedging.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2610, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(1050, 'No Prefix', 115, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, 'Crown Works Workshop', '37 Higher Street, Cullompton ', 'EX15 1AJ', '<ul>\r\n<li>Workshop 2,357 sq ft</li>\r\n<li>With access off the main arterial road through the town of Cullompton.</li>\r\n<li>Parking nearby.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>SITUATION AND AMENITIES:</strong>&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">(of which distances are approximate):- </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">With access off the main arterial road through the town of Cullompton which is on junction 28 of the M5 Motorway.&nbsp; Exeter is 15 miles, Taunton is 18 miles and Tiverton 6 miles. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>ACCOMMODATION:</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WORKSHOP 86&rsquo;3&rdquo; X 27&rsquo;4&rdquo;&nbsp; roller shutter entrance door 9&rsquo; x 10&rsquo; high, excellent natural lighting.&nbsp; Toilets of two WC&rsquo;s and wash room lobby, gas space heater. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">OUTSIDE:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Parking nearby for three cars.</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>SERVICES:</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main electricity (3 phase), water, drainage and gas.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>RATES:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The workshop is not yet separately assessed but combined with Unit 4 (1650 sq ft the two units are currently assessed at &pound;12,500. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>PLANNING:&nbsp;</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises were granted planning consent for use for car and van body repairs. Mid Devon District Council Reference 4/21/96/0687.&nbsp; Enquiries should be made of the Council on 01884 255255, to confirm that any particular prospective use can be pursued without the need to make a planning application. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>EPC:</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises of which the workshop forms part has an Energy Performance Asset rating of D. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">LEASE:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>&nbsp;</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The workshop is available on a short to medium term lease at &pound;115 pw.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The tenant will be asked to pay the Landlord&rsquo;s lawyers costs in drawing up the lease, it is likely to be in the order of &pound;500.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>OFFICE ALSO AVAILABLE:</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">An office of 368 sq ft floor area which adjoins the road, is available to let also at Crown Works.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">VIEWING: </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">By appointment please with Messrs </span><span lang="en-GB">Thorne &amp; Carter. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2641, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'pw', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'D', '', '', ''),
