(10575, 'No Prefix', 395000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 5, 'Pugham Farm', 'Westleigh', 'EX16 7HL', '<ul>\r\n<li>Spacious and versatile detached period farmhouse.</li>\r\n<li>LPG central heating and UPVc double glazing.</li>\r\n<li>2 Kitchens.</li>\r\n<li>4/5 Reception Rooms.</li>\r\n<li>5/6 Bedrooms.</li>\r\n<li>2 Bathrooms.</li>\r\n<li>Gardens.</li>\r\n<li>Paddocks.</li>\r\n<li>Brick built summer house.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Location&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Pugham Farm lies close to the Grand Western Canal on the country lane between Sampford Peverell and Westleigh being only about one and a half miles from junction 27 of the M5, with its adjacent Parkway main line railway station providing a rapid link with London (Paddington). The nearby village of Sampford Peverell offers a post office stores, primary school and is situated within the catchment area for the highly regarded Uffculme school. The larger country towns of Cullompton and Tiverton provide a more extensive range of shopping, schooling and transport facilities with the M5 providing a rapid link with Exeter to the south and Taunton to the north. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth or rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty. The stunning national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Ground Floor&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Canopy entrance porch with slated roof to part glazed front door to Dinning hall radiator, door to Sitting room outlook over garden, brick feature fireplace with timber mantel housing wood burning stove, three wall light points. Kitchen 2 range of light ash effect units, comprising seven base cupboards, drawer pack, marble effect worktops with inset single drainer sink unit with mixer tap, free standing cooker with four LPG rings and electric fan assisted oven, cooker hood/ extractor over, six wall cupboards, space and plumbing for washing machine and dishwasher, dual aspect, built in larder cupboard, ceiling beam, quarry tiled floor, space for breakfast table, radiator, half glazed door to Porch/ Utility with appliance space. Dining Room outlook over front garden, radiator, massive stone inglenook housing woodburning stove, Bressumer beam, concealed second staircase. Kitchen 1 fitted with extensive modern range of high gloss white units comprising seven base cupboards, two wall cupboards, stainless steel cooker hood/ extractor, space and plumbing for dishwasher, washing machine, dual aspect outlook. Cloakroom with WC and washbasin. Garden Room electric panel radiator, walk in wine storage cupboard, twin UPVc double glazed French doors to covered porch. Study/ Office currently used as a ground floor bedroom, radiator, walk in wardrobe with shelving and twin hanging rails.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">1st Floor&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Bedroom 1 fitted wardrobe, radiator, two windows overlooking garden, WC with white suite, radiator.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Bedroom 2 Radiator, rear stairs leading down to dinning room.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Bedroom 3 with radiator, window overlooking garden, fitted wardrobe.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Bedroom 4 radiator, loft access, outlook over gardens.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Bedroom 5 outlook over gardens, radiator, dressing room with radiator.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Bathroom 1 with white suite comprising corner bath, pedestal basin, curved shower with electric shower unit, radiator, window, separate WC with close coupled suite, vanity was basin, radiator, two windows, second staircase to main landing. Connecting door to rear landing. Radiator.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Bathroom 2 white suite comprising bath with electric shower over, pedestal basin, window, radiator.&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">Outside&nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><br style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;" /><span style="font-family: Arial, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 11.818181991577148px; line-height: 18.01799964904785px;">The property is approached off the small country lane over its own private drive leading through the pasture fields to an extensive turning and parking area, adjoining which is situated the mobile home ideal for letting or as children&rsquo;s playroom/ sleepover facility. A formal garden adjoins the front of the property and overlooks the front paddock with timber gate leading to rear drive. Adjoining the paring area lies the more recently constructed stone and brick summer house with veranda over a raise decking area. To the rear and rising gently lies the larger paddock, the whole being ideal for a variety of equestrian or horticultural uses.&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2527, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10678, 'No Prefix', 134500, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 1, '33 Clarks Court', 'Clarks Court, Cullompton', 'EX15 1FB', '<p>A spacious and well appointed 1 bedroom retirement flat in this popular Mcarthy and Stone development, the property benifits from being south facing and having windows on three sides.</p>', '<p>This modern south facing first floor flat enjoys an excellent position in this popular McCarthy and Stone development with its Tunstall on call security system and set within this gated community only a few yards from the bustling high street.&nbsp; The flat has windows on three sides ensuring a particularly light interior whilst the view of the high street provides a considerable source of interest.&nbsp; Owners also enjoy the use of lovely professionally maintained grounds together with a residents lounge, laundry room and visitors flat. <br /><br />Right in the heart of town, just back from the High Street in a gated community offering great convenience combined with privacy and security.&nbsp; The country town of Cullompton provides a useful range of everyday shopping, schooling and transport facilities including a bus service to Exeter every 20 minutes.&nbsp; The nearby M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The property enjoys distant views towards the Blackdown Hills an area designated as Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; For those wishing to enjoy the delights of Devon the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; The stunning National Trust estate at Killerton with its fine country house, gardens, grounds and arboretum lies about five miles to the south.<br /><br />Highly regarded McCarthy and Stone retirement flat<br />Convenient High Street setting&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />24 hour Tunstall on call service<br />Hall<br />Sitting room<br />Bedroom<br />Bathroom with window<br />Well appointed kitchen<br />Visitors suite available to rent<br />Laundry room and residents lounge<br />Landscaped grounds<br />Convenient for local shops and frequent bus services<br />Service charge &pound;45.66 per week<br />Residue of 125 year lease<br />15 miles Exeter, 19 miles Taunton<br />Main electricity, water and drainage<br /><br />Heavy panelled front door to <br />L-shaped Hall night storage heater, access to loft, walk in cloaks cupboard/store room, walk in cupboard with hot water system and slatted shelving.<br />Sitting Room lovely bright and airy dual aspect room, two south facing windows and French doors with Juliette balcony having outlook towards the high street, night storage heater, twin glazed doors to<br />Kitchen well appointed range of light ash effect units comprising three base cupboards, integrated refridgerator, space for deep freeze, marble effect work tops with inset stainless single drainer sink, wall cupboards and open shelving, inset ceramic hob with cooker hood/extractor over, tall unit providing cupboard and housing for electric cooker, lighting, outlook towards the high street, wall mounted electric fan heater.<br /><br /><br />Bedroom 1 another bright and airy dual aspect room, night storage heater, fitted wardrobe with twin mirror fronted folding doors.<br />Bathroom with window and modern suite comprising panelled bath with mains shower over, shower curtain and rail, close coupled WC, vanity washbasin with cupboards beneath, fully tiled walls, extractor, fan heater, electric towel rail, night storage heater.<br /><br />Outside<br />This gated complex is approached through security pedestrian and vehicular gates leading to a parking area with delightful grounds beyond comprising extensive areas of lawn, pergola with patio and a charming lake, the maintenance for which is included in the service charge.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2675, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10648, 'No Prefix', 10000, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, '24 Fore Street', 'Fore Street, Cullompton ', 'EX15 1jh', '<ul>\r\n<li>Spacious retail lock-up shop with kitchen in attractive refurbished building in the centre of Cullompton.</li>\r\n<li>In all approximately 1,400 sq ft net floor area.</li>\r\n<li>Occupying a prominent position in the main shopping street of the busy town of Cullompton.</li>\r\n<li>Well suited for large retail, restaurant (subject to planning).</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION &amp; AMENITIES: </span><span lang="en-GB">( please note distances are approximate).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Situated in a prime location in the busy shopping street in Cullompton.&nbsp; Cullompton is an active shopping centre with a wide range of retail and service outlets and lies adjacent to the M5 Junction 28.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ACCOMMODATION:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">DOUBLE FRONTED SHOP 7.62m x an overall depth of approximately 14.31m max with two large shop windows flanking the entrance door.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Feature fireplace, deep moulded ceiling beams.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Side access doors to passageway.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Storage Area 3.16m x 2.77m plus 1.47m x 4.2m with further side entrance door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Washroom</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Lobby</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WC</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen 5.2m x 5m </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">NOTE&nbsp; a prominent and attractive premises with an unusually large floor area.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Mains water, electricity and drainage are connected.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PLANNING: </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises have been used as retail shop for many years.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">LEASES: </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises are available on a medium to long term lease.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;R<span lang="en-GB">ENT</span><span lang="en-GB">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Offers are invited.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none;">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2623, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '- 12500 offers invited', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10383, 'No Prefix', 5000, 'Leasehold', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, '12 - 14 Fore Street, Cullompton', '12 - 14 Fore Street, Cullompton', 'EX151JL', '<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>Lock up shops.</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>A double fronted shope of character with double frontage.</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>Two characterful interconnecting small shops - to be amalgamated.</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>Parking can be made available.</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div>Rent &pound;5,000 Per annum.</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p>&nbsp;<strong><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION</span><span lang="en-GB"> &amp; AMENITIES</span></strong></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-justify: newspaper; text-align: justify; text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">In a prime trading</span><span lang="en-GB"> position in the centre of the retailing area of the town with the frontage to the main street of this busy growing town (population 8,500</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;approximately) in which considerable&nbsp; residential and commercial development is proposed.&nbsp; The town is conveniently located just off M5 motorway Junction 28, the city of Exeter is 13 miles and Taunton 19 miles, Tiverton is 6 miles.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-justify: newspaper; text-align: justify; text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">A double fronted shop of character with overall frontage of 9.54m (31&rsquo; 4&rdquo;) and a depth of 3.3m to 6m and overall retail area of approximately 80sq m (858sq ft).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Two characterful interconnecting&nbsp; small shops&mdash;to be amalgamated and with </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WC / Kitchenette</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">PARKING</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>:</strong>&nbsp; Parking can be made available.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB"><strong>PLANNING:</strong> </span><span lang="en-GB">The premises have a retail use not yet assessed (it is most likely that the premises will be chargeable to business rates if the occupier qualifies for small business relief.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">LEASE: </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">The premises are available to let on a medium to long term basis at a rent of &pound;5,000 per annum.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong><span lang="en-GB">VIEWING: </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">By arrangement through the Agents, Thorne &amp; Carter. Who hold the key.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB"><strong>CONDITION&nbsp; OF PROPERTY</strong>: </span><span lang="en-GB">Kindly note that for lease purposes neither the seller nor Thorne &amp; Carter have had a survey of the property carried out.&nbsp; Consequently no warranty can be either given or implied as to&nbsp; the condition thereof nor of any of the&nbsp;&nbsp; appliances, equipment, fixtures or fittings.&nbsp; Should&nbsp; assurance on condition be required, a prospective tenant is advised to obtain verification from their own independent research and enquiry.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB"><strong>MISREPRESENTATION DISCLAIMER</strong>: </span><span lang="en-GB">Any representation made either by the landlord or their Agents whether orally or in writing and wither made prior hereto or contained herein, is believed to be correct but its accuracy is not&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; guaranteed.&nbsp; A tenant is deemed to have satisfied himself by inspection,&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; measurement, search otherwise that he has entered into this contract in reliance upon his own researches and not in reliance upon any such representation made by the landlord or his Agents.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2407, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'p.a', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(11, 'No Prefix', 875000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 6, 'The Old Manor & Clyst Lea', 'Clyst Hydon, Cullompton', 'EX15 2ND', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>An Incredible opportunity to aquire a 6 Bedroom grade 2 listed country house complete with a purpose built 3 bedroom deteached cottage in the grounds of over an acre.</span></p>', '<p>An extremely rare opportunity to purchase a fine Grade II listed country home with purpose built detached house making the whole ideal for completely independent twin generation occupation. Enjoying a village edge setting the Manor House offers immensely characterful six bedroom and four reception room accommodation whilst the modern detached house, constructed in the grounds by the present owners for parents occupation comprises three bedrooms and two reception rooms. Gardens and grounds in excess of an acre surround the properties and the Manor House also offers a small range of traditional farm buildings. Clyst Hydon is within easy reach of Exeter and the property is ideal for two generations combining resources who wish to enjoy a thriving village community. <br /> <br />An extremely rare opportunity to purchase a fine Grade II listed country home with purpose built detached house making the whole ideal for completely independent twin generation occupation. Enjoying a village edge setting the Manor House offers immensely characterful six bedroom and four reception room accommodation whilst the modern detached house, constructed in the grounds by the present owners for parents occupation comprises three bedrooms and two reception rooms. Gardens and grounds in excess of an acre surround the properties and the Manor House also offers a small range of traditional farm buildings. Clyst Hydon is within easy reach of Exeter and the property is ideal for two generations combining resources who wish to enjoy a thriving village community.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2632, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10661, 'No Prefix', 550000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 6, 'The Old Manor', 'Clyst Hydon, Cullompton', 'EX15 2ND', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This stunning period village home nestles in extensive mature grounds on the outskirts of highly popular Clyst Hydon village. This spacious characterful home is ideally suited to the growing family wishing to enjoy a semi-rural environment whilst being remarkably conveniently placed for Exeter</span></p>', '<p>This stunning period village home nestles in extensive mature grounds in the highly popular Clyst Hydon village. First time on the market for thirty years this spacious characterful home is ideally suited to the growing family wishing to enjoy a semi-rural environment whilst being remarkably conveniently placed for Exeter. Linked at one corner this extensive property offers four reception rooms and country kitchen/breakfast on the ground floor together with six bedrooms, a box room, shower room and bathroom on the first floor. Oil fired central heating is installed and an interior inspection is essential to appreciate the charm and character contained therein. The extensive grounds and traditional outbuilding complete this fine country home. <br /> <br />Delightfully located in the small village of Clyst Hydon with its local primary school, church and popular Five Bells public house. Every day shopping facilities are to be found in nearby Cullompton with its range of high street shops, two supermarkets, two doctors surgeries, library, sports centre and Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centre. The cathedral city of Exeter lies to the south with its modern shopping mall, high street shops and cultural activities. The nearby M5 at Cullompton, and Tiverton Parkway station at Junction 27, facilitate easy commuting to the north with London (Paddington) being little more than two hours distant. The nearby Blackdown Hills provide glorious woodland walks and a wealth of rural pursuits whilst being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty. The spectacular National Trust estate of Killerton provides walks through its gardens, grounds and arboretum in addition to its fine country house. The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlilnes all within a modest car journey. <br /> <br />Spacious and characterful grade II listed country home <br />Village Centre setting <br />Convenient for thriving city of Exeter <br />Vast hall, cloakroom <br />4 reception rooms <br />Country kitchen/breakfast room <br />6 bedrooms, box room <br />Bathroom, shower room <br />Small range of traditional farm buildings <br />Extensive gardens and grounds, adjoining stream <br />Small area of woodland <br />12 miles Exeter <br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 12 miles <br />Mains electricity and water, private drainage <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />Impressive canopy entrance Porch to massive oak panelled front door, magnificent &rsquo;L&rsquo; shaped Hall with glorious tessellated tiled floor, two radiators, elegant turning stairs to first floor, oak dado panelling, understair cupboard with hanging rail. <br />Drawing Room lovely dual aspect south east facing room, three windows one being a bay, radiator, heavy ceiling beam, corner fireplace with quarry tiled hearth housing woodburning stove, lovely views over the grounds. <br />Dining Room a spectacular fully panelled room with all walls oak panelled, stone fireplace with woodburner on stone hearth set in magnificent carved fireplace and with additional ancient heavily carved panels believed to be of Jacobean origin and imported to the property, dual aspect with bay window enjoying outlook over front garden and farmland. <br />Sitting Room cosy &rsquo;L&rsquo; shaped room with two radiators, extensive fitted bookshelving, doors to principal hall and back hall, stone fireplace with quarry tiled hearth, two radiators, bay window with lovely rural outlook. <br />Kitchen/Breakfast Room enjoys a lovely outlook over the established grounds, light ash units comprising ten base cupboards, drawer pack, tall larder cupboard, pale laminate worktops with ash trim, inset one and a half bowl single drainer sink, space and plumbing for washing machine and tumble dryer, floor mounted oil fired boiler, radiator, down lighting, original fireplace which would have undoubtebly housed a range cooker, presently with cupboards and space for freestanding electric cooker, tiled surround, fitted cupboard to alcove. <br />Study two radiators, three wall light points, French doors to extensive rear garden. <br /> <br />Rear Hall with quarry tiled floor, half glazed back door, Cloakroom with white WC and washbasin, radiator, quarry tiled floor. <br />Walk-in larder with window, shelving and continuation of tessellated floor. <br /> <br />On the first floor <br />Long landing, radiator, walk in airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder and shelving. <br />Bedroom 1 radiator, built in cupboard with hanging rail and shelving, double fitted wardrobe, vanity basin with cupboard beneath, light/shaver point, lovely rural outlook. <br />Bedroom 2 radiator, fitted double wardrobe, wash basin in vanity surround with cupboard beneath, fitted dressing table, country outlook. <br />Bedroom 3 radiator, fitted double wardrobe, vanity basin with cupboard beneath, fitted dressing table and drawers, access to loft, lovely outlook over the rear garden. <br />Bedroom 4 radiator, fitted double wardrobe, vanity basin with cupboard beneath, lovely outlook over partly wooded rear garden. <br />Bedroom 5 vanity wash basin with cupboard beneath, built in double wardrobe with cupboards over, outlook over rear garden. <br />Bedroom 6 radiator, country views to the front, vanity basin with cupboards beneath, dressing table, fitted double wardrobe <br />Family Bathroom having white suite, comprising panelled bath, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, tiled shower with electric shower unit, radiator, spot lighting. <br />Shower room close coupled WC, shower with mains mixer tap, pedestal basin, radiator, light storage shaver point. <br />Box room with fitted double wardrobe. <br /> <br />Outside <br />The property is approached just off the village lane, over a partly brick paved drive leading to the house on one side and the outbuildings on the other. Small range of traditional farm buildings, mostly of brick, stone and cob construction with tiled roofs comprising <br />Store Room 15&rsquo; x 13&rsquo; with stairs to workshop over, <br />Machinery Store/Workshop 13&rsquo; x 12&rsquo;, work benches, shelving. <br />Open fronted Garage 13&rsquo;8&rdquo; x 15&rsquo;, oil storage tank. <br />Store room 16&rsquo; x 16&rsquo;, twin timber doors. <br />Largely lawned front garden with wrought iron entrance gate leading between twin pillars to path leading to front door. The grounds extend primarily to the rear of the property with sweeping lawns interspersed with a wealth of mature trees and shrub borders. Perennial borders, ornamental fish pond with waterfall to lower pond. Beyond the lawn lies the kitchen garden with soft fruit section and small orchard. An area of woodland leads down to the river bank.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2633, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10670, 'No Prefix', 299950, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Viewing', 3, 'Fig Tree Barn', 'Uffculme', 'EX15 3BX', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A delightful light and airy barn conversion on the outskirts of Uffculme village, the property boasts very large living space downstairs with a stylish contemporary kitchen with an aga. The property is in Uffculme school catchment and has no chain.</p>', '<p>Highly individual barn conversion in a semi rural setting about 2 miles north of Cullompton and being within the catchment for highly regarded Uffculme school. This unique property offers an unusual blend of traditional with some highly individual contemporary twists including part clear glazed double glazed roofs to both the kitchen and sitting room. The kitchen/breakfast room with its four oven Aga is a real feature, as is the adjoining sitting room with its extensive natural light by virtue of the expansive glazed roof at one end. A separate dining room and useful study/occasional bedroom combine with three bedrooms (one ensuite and a family bathroom on the first floor) to create an unusual home of character. <br /> <br />Nestling at the end of a private lane in a semi-rural location between Willand and Sampford Peverell within the Uffculme school catchment. High street shops and supermarkets are to be found in the nearby towns of Cullompton and Tiverton with the nearby M5 facilitating rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton. Cullompton also offers two doctors surgeries, a sports centre, library and Padbrook golf course and leisure centre, the surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty. The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. <br /> <br />Attached barn conversion, semi rural location