oor <br />Landing access to loft, exposed roof timbers, wall lights, airing cupboard with megaflow hot water system, shelving with cupboard over. <br />Bedroom 1 with oak flooring, radiator, fitted triple wardrobe, exposed roof timbers, country outlook over rear garden, <br />Ensuite Shower Room with extra wide shower, rain head shower, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, part tiled walls, window, tiled floor. <br />Bedroom 2 radiator, exposed roof timbers, fitted double wardrobe. <br />Bedroom 3 radiator, exposed ceiling timbers, downlighting, country outlook. <br />Family bathroom oak flooring, panelled bath with mixer tap/shower attachment over, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, window, chrome ladder style towel rail, radiator, extractor, downlighting.. <br /> <br />Outside <br />The property is approached off the small farm lane leading to massive twin timber doors providing access to paved covered area. Rear garden, grassed with extensive paved patio, perimeter hedging, timber garden shed, oil storage tank and oil fired boiler.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2643, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10646, 'No Prefix', 155000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Hidden', 2, '48 Raleigh Drive', 'Cullompton', 'EX15 1FZ', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>A superbly presented coach house enjoying one of the best locations. This freehold property is ideally suited to a first purchaser or buy to let.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Part glazed panelled front door to e</span><span lang="en-GB">ntrance </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Integral Garage,</span><span lang="en-GB"> light and power connected, roller door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Door to understair storage cupboard with light and shelving. Wide easy rising staircase to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">U-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, window overlooking open grassed area with small brook, boiler cupboard with gas fired boiler, shelving, access to loft. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Stylish open plan </span><span lang="en-GB">Living Area </span><span lang="en-GB">providing a contemporary triple aspect Dining/Living/Kitchen. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The </span><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen </span><span lang="en-GB">area with light oak effect units comprising five base cupboards, drawer pack, timber effect roll edged work tops having inset stainless steel single drainer sink, mixer tap, inset brushed stainless steel four ring gas hob with brushed stainless steel oven beneath and cooker hood over, two spot light clusters, space for fridge/freezer.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2615, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '77', '78', '', ''),
(10635, 'No Prefix', 112000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Sale Agreed', 2, '92a St Andrews Estate', 'St Andrews Estate, Cullompton', 'EX15 1JA', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Once being the ground floor of an ex local authority home, now converted and boasting a fine extension which adjoins its west facing garden. Offering good value for money the property will surely be very appealing for an investor or as a first time purchase.</span></p>', '<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">Spacious ground floor flat</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Once being the ground floor of an ex local authority home, now converted and boasting a fine extension which adjoins its west facing garden. Offering good value for money the property will surely be very appealing for an investor or as a first time purchase. This two bedroom flat has a large kitchen/dining room and sitting room benefitting from recently installed gas central heating.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Located on the lower slope of St Andrews Estate, the property is within about 200m of Cullompton High Street with its assorted every day shopping facilities.&nbsp; Cullompton also offers two supermarkets, two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, sports centre, new library, stunning community centre and the highly regarded Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centre.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The glorious National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">Accommodation</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Half Glaze