(10572, 'No Prefix', 229000, 'Freehold', 'Bungalow', 'Viewing', 3, 'KOGGALA, GABLES ROAD', 'Gables Road, Willand', 'EX15 2PL', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Spacious and versatile detached bungalow, enjoying a generous plot in a non estate setting set well back from Gables Road and convenient to local amenities.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Enjoying a non estate setting conveniently close for Willand Primary School, tennis courts, Village Hall, Post Office Stores and One Stop Shop.&nbsp; Frequent bus services link with the country town of Cullompton with its range of everyday shopping, schooling, sports centre and highly regarded Padbrook Park golf and leisure centre.&nbsp; The nearby M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp;&nbsp; The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Recessed entrance porch</span><span lang="en-GB">with quarry tiled floor and light to UPVC part glazed front door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hall </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, access to loft.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room </span><span lang="en-GB">bright and airy dual aspect room, radiator, tiled open fireplace and hearth, recess with television aerial point.&nbsp; This room could readily become a third bedroom if required with the dining room becoming the sitting room.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room </span><span lang="en-GB">tiled open fireplace, radiator, recess, linen cupboard with slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> another