(10629, 'No Prefix', 325000, 'Freehold', 'Terrace', 'Viewing', 3, 'Dobbins, Yondercott Farm', 'Yondercott Farm, Uffculme', 'EX15 3DR', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>A Stunning Barn Conversion, set on the outskirts of the incredibly popular Village of Uffculme, the property offers luxurious 3 bedroom family accommodation</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Located on the outskirts of the popular Culm Valley village of Uffculme with its local post office stores, one stop shop, primary school and the ever popular Uffculme secondary school.&nbsp; Glorious walks are to be found beside the nearby river Culm offering a picturesque waterside walk north to Culmstock.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty.&nbsp; A more extensive range of shopping facilities are to be found in the nearby country town of Cullompton, with its two supermarkets, sports centre and Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centres.&nbsp; The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Shared sewage treatment system, standing charge of &pound;45&nbsp;</span>per month in respect of maintenance of the treatment plant and common parts.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;&nbsp; (Greatly reduced payment of water rate to South West Water).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Canopy entrance porch with slated roof, half glazed stable front door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall </span><span lang="en-GB">with slated floor, beamed ceiling, radiator, central heating thermostat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloak Room </span><span lang="en-GB">with continuation of slate floor, white close coupled suite and pedestal basin, radiator, extractor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Fine</span><span lang="en-GB"> Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB">, ceiling beam, fireplace with heavy Bressumer beam and brick hearth housing Villager log burning stove, radiator, three wall light points.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> superbly appointed range of modern cream high gloss units with soft closures, range of base units including cupboard, drawers, integrated refrigerator, integrated dishwasher, six wall cupboards, two with glazed doors, lovely granite worktop with inset stainless steel sink, mixer tap, inset Bosch induction hob having Bosch self cleaning oven beneath and foldaway extractor/cookerhood over, worktop illumination, downlighting, beamed ceiling, Rhino timber effect flooring, radiator, twin French doors to garden and decking, deep understairs cupboard. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room </span><span lang="en-GB">slate floor, range of Shaker style cream units, base cupboards, tall cupboards, eight wall cupboards, work tops with inset stainless steel single drainer sink, space and plumbing for&nbsp; washing machine, space for refrigerator, Worcester oil fired boiler, extractor, down lighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Charming fully returning cottage staircase with flank window overlooking fields.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Landing, </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, loft access, walk-in linen cupboard with shelving and hanging rail, light. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> delightful room extending the full width of the barn being dual aspect, lovely reclaimed tongued and grooved flooring, radiator, range of fitted wardrobes and hanging rail,&nbsp; ceiling beams, second Loft Access, </span><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">white suite comprising panelled bath with Mira Sport electric shower over, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, ladder style towel rail/radiator, extractor, downlighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Guest Bedroom </span><span lang="en-GB">charming &lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped room with ceiling beam, radiator, </span><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite Shower </span><span lang="en-GB">with white suite comprising tiled shower cubicle with Mira mains shower, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, extractor, down lighting. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, outlook across the barnyard to the adjoining fields.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A gravelled drive serves the entire barnyard development with Dobbins owning a gravelled parking area for 1/2 vehicles leading to the attached </span><span lang="en-GB">Garage</span><span lang="en-GB">, twin timber doors, shelving, light and power, oil tank.&nbsp; A timber gate leads to the west facing rear garden, being fully fenced and having two areas of Astroturf bisected by paved paths and leading to paved sitting out area with adjoining water feature.&nbsp; Raised </span><span lang="en-GB">Decking </span><span lang="en-GB">adjoining the kitchen being ideal for alfresco entertaining.&nbsp; The whole being fully fenced.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2600, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10628, 'No Prefix', 239950, 'Freehold', 'Terrace', 'Sale Agreed', 3, '11 Silver Street', 'Silver Street, Kentisbeare', 'EX15 2BH ', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>A charming Village cottage which offers very comfortable and well appointed accommodation.The cottages boasts a wealth of original features with 3 bedrooms and a large mature garden to the rear.</span></p>', '<p>A superb chance to acquire a lovely period cottage in this particularly sought after village nestling at the foot of the Blackdown Hills, itself an area designated as being of outstanding natural beauty.&nbsp; The characterful accommodation provides two reception rooms, three bedrooms and a modern bathroom whilst having oil central heating and double glazed windows.&nbsp; Exposed timbers and ceiling beams combine with a massive fireplace with bread oven and woodburner whilst two of the bedrooms have glorious vaulted ceilings all of which add to the character of this charming home.&nbsp; The large lovingly tended cottage garden will delight the gardener and an early inspection is recommended.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Pleasantly located in a short terrace of similar cottages, close to the post office stores, public house, primary school and church. The Uffculme school bus departs from the village square.&nbsp; Kentisbeare lies at the foot of the Blackdown Hills an area designated of being outstanding natural beauty.&nbsp; A more extensive range of shopping, schooling and transport facilities is to be found in the nearby country town of Cullompton with its two doctors, two supermarkets, sports centre and Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centres.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Heavy timber front door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> charming room with heavy ceiling beam, stone fireplace with Bressumer beam and ancient tiled hearth housing woodburning stove, brick domed bread oven forming display niche, radiator, four wall light points, wide timber arch to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator .</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> range of light grey fronted units comprising six base cupboards with stone tiled work tops, space and plumbing for automatic washing machine, Worcester oil fired boiler, space for refrigerator, tall housing for double oven/grill, inset four ring electric hob, two wall cupboards, spot lighting, quarry tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> approached by pretty returning staircase well lit by flank window overlooking rear garden, exposed ceiling timbers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> lovely vaulted room, radiator, exposed ceiling beams.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> another fine vaulted bedroom, exposed roof timbers, access to loft, built in range of triple wardrobes with storage above, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, outlook over rear gardens towards woodland and the river Ken.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">with white suite comprising panelled bath, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, electric shower, part tiled walls, exposed roof timbers, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="en-GB">The long glorious cottage garden is a delight, having been lovingly created over a number of years by the owner.&nbsp; Immediately to the rear of the cottage, the former brick &ldquo;privy&rdquo; has been renovated to provide a useful gardener&rsquo;s WC with a step leading to a gravelled sitting out area, ideal for barbeques etc.&nbsp; The serpentine lawn is flanked by established herbaceous and perennial borders providing a profusion of colour through the seasons and with stepping stones leading through a rose clad rustic arch to a further lawned area where the garden path leads through a low beech hedge to the kitchen garden with soft fruit, beyond which lies an area of &ldquo;wildlife garden&rdquo; flanked by traditional Devon Bank, willow and ash trees, the whole backing onto the Silver wood with its glorious walks.&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2599, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10595, 'No Prefix', 360000, 'Freehold', 'Bungalow', 'Hidden', 3, 'Badgers Holt', 'Crownhill, Halberton', 'EX16 7AY', '<ul>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Stunning canal side setting</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Far reaching views.</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Updated detached country bungalow</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Gas central heating and double glazing</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Sitting room</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">3 Bedrooms</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Refitted kitchen</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Superbly appointed bathroom</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Large stunning waterside grounds</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Garage</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Mains water, electricity and private drainage</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Conveniently located in Crownhill on the outskirts of Halberton village between the country towns of Tiverton and Cullompton.&nbsp; Badgers Holt lies within easy reach of the excellent shopping, schooling and transport facilities offered by both towns, whilst the nearby M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wide variety of rural pursuits with the country park of the Grand Western canal actually adjoining the property.&nbsp; The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Part glazed front door to &lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped Hall, radiator, timber effect laminate floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> bright and airy dual aspect room, brick feature fireplace with slate tiled hearth having woodburning stove and timber mantel over, two wall light points, two radiators, wide square archway to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory</span><span lang="en-GB"> with brick lower walls and double glazed picture windows, enjoying outlook over gardens and Grand Western canal, twin French doors to patio and garden, radiator. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen</span><span lang="en-GB"> well appointed with range of cream painted units comprising six base cupboards, drawer pack, space and plumbing for dishwasher, marble effect work tops inset stainless steel one and a half bowl single drainer sink unit, brushed stainless steel, five ring gas hob, including wok ring with oven under and foldaway extractor fan/cooker hood over, seven further wall cupboards, open ended shelving, outlook towards the lane and canal, timber effect floor, radiator, downlighting, half glazed door to rear lobby with glazed back door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room </span><span lang="en-GB">quarry tiled floor, space and plumbing for washing machine, space for upright fridge freezer. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom </span><span lang="en-GB">having close coupled WC, pedestal basin, gas fired boiler, coat hooks</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> recently refitted with stylish white suite comprising &lsquo;P&rsquo; shaped spa bath with mains shower over and curved shower screen, close coupled WC, corner basin, chrome ladder style towel rail, radiator, extractor fan, window, lovely marble style wall and floor tiling, shaver point.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> two radiators.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> glorious outlook over the patio and down the long gardens to the Grand Western canal, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3 </span><span lang="en-GB">currently used as a dining room, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The property is approached off the quiet country lane adjacent to its bridge over the Grand Western canal through twin five bar gates to extensive gravelled turning and parking area adjoining which lies the detached single garage with up-and-over door, power connected, personal door, of rendered and slate construction matching the bungalow.&nbsp; Small area of front garden with additional gravelled area and raised shrub border.&nbsp; Immediately to the rear of the bungalow a paved patio extends the full width of the property with step leading to the sweeping lawns interspersed with a wide variety of established ornamental shrubs including many acres.&nbsp; Well stocked perennial border with a wide range of traditional cottage garden plants, ornamental pond, aluminium framed greenhouse, timber garden shed with adjoining kitchen/garden and fruit cage, two strategically placed arbours one being roofed and enjoying a peaceful outlook directly across the Grand Western canal with farmland and distant hills beyond.&nbsp; Additional shrubberies and perennial borders together with many fine specimen trees.&nbsp; A creeper clad rustic arch leads along a grass path to a flight of steps giving access to the canal.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2555, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(8653, 'No Prefix', 175, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, 'Units C, The Tannery', 'Exeter Road, Cullompton', 'EX15 1DT', '<ul>\r\n<li>Large Town Centre Warehouse/Auction Premises 90ft x 75ft, approx</li>\r\n<li>With 1/2 acre parking.</li>\r\n<li>Rent &pound;175 - &pound;400 per week</li>\r\n<li>Premises are close to the centre of town with access directly off the main road, half a mile from the M5 Junction 28.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION &amp; AMENITIES: </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">( please note distances are approximate).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises are close to the centre of the town with access directly off the main arterial road, about half a mile from the M5 Junction 28 close to The Old Tannery Antique Centre and opposite premises to be fitted out as Aldi Supermarket in 2014.</span></p>\r\n<p>Cullompton, population about 8000 is an expanding town designated, together with the nearby village of Willand 2.5 miles away as an area of major change where considerable provision is made for growth&nbsp; by way of residential and employment land for development reflecting the policy to improve and widen the range of services and increase the capability of the town to serve a large hinterland.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">In addition Cullompton lies within the Exeter sub-region, the City being 13 miles away.</span></p>\r\n<p>Tiverton Parkway Railway Station at M5 Junction 27 with regular services to Paddington is about 5 miles, Roscoff Ferry at Plymouth 55 miles, Taunton 18 miles, Taunton 18 miles, the North Devon Link Road at M5 Junction 27 gives rapid access to Barnstaple and North Devon.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>TYPE:</strong>&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">The premises comprise an early twentieth century building of block work and with sheeted roof incorporating good&nbsp; provision for natural lighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">THE ACCOMMODATION:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Unit C</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Comprises a mainly clear floor area approximately 90ft x 75ft average with good head room, and in which the landlord is prepared to fit a roller shutter door to allow vehicle entry.&nbsp; KITCHEN 11ft 10ins x 11ft 6ins.&nbsp; Three WC&rsquo;s.&nbsp; STOREROOM 14ft x 13ft average.</span></p>\r\n<p>Unit C1 (TEMPORARILY LET)</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Comprises an open floor area approximately 26.7m x 19.7m (87ft 8 ins x 64ft 8 ins) max x about 3.15m (10ft 4 ins) headroom and higher.&nbsp; With roller shutter door 3.92m (12ft 6 ins) high x 4.6m (15ft) wide and pedestrian side door. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong>OUTSIDE:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">There is a hard core surfaced yard of about half an acre which is available if required. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:&nbsp; </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">Main water electricity (3 phase) and drainage are connected.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>RATEABLE VALUES:</strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>UNIT C:</strong>&nbsp; &pound;13,250.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>UNIT C1</strong> &pound;12,750.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong><span lang="en-GB">PLANNING:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; The premises have been used for many years as warehousing and covered auction premises.&nbsp; However enquiries should be made at the planning authority, the Mid Devon District Council (01884 255255) to confirm that any prospective use can be pursued without the need to make a planning application.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">LEASE:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>&nbsp;</strong> The premises are available on a short term lease at a rent of &pound;400 per week as a whole i.e. C and C1 or at &pound;175 per week for unit C1 (5230 sq ft) only.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">COST:&nbsp; </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">The lessee will pay the lessors legal costs in preparing the lease.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">VIEWING:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"> Interested parties may view the premises by appointment through the agents, Thorne &amp; Carter, 01884 33333</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2468, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '- Â£400 pw', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10453, 'No Prefix', 170000, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'TUSCAN WORKS, KENTISBEARE', 'Tuscan Works, Kentisbeare', 'EX15 2BQ', '<ul>\r\n<li>New&nbsp;Business Unit&nbsp;in a Delightful Rural Location</li>\r\n<li>190 SQ M (2050 SQ FT) on a site extending to 0.36 acres.</li>\r\n<li>For sale/freehold.</li>\r\n<li>Situated just outside the village of Kentisbeare in a quiet location.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong>DESCRIPTION:&nbsp; </strong>Situated just outside the village of Kentisbeare in a quite location.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>An attractive steel portal frame building with steel cladding and timber boarded elevations to most sides, extending in all to approximately 190 sq m (2050 sq ft) slightly irregular in shape but approximately 12.8m max x 15.9m to the main portion with a ridge height of 5.5m and eaves at 2.35m and including two roller shutter entrance doors, 3.5m wide x 3m high and 3.5m x 1.97m high and window openings to allow the easy formation of offices required, ample roof light sheets.&nbsp; Reinforced concrete floor, disabled WC cubicle.</p>\r\n<p><strong>OUTSIDE: </strong>The premises are approached from Machine Lane by an entrance splay and gate to the open yard which surrounds the building on three sides and has a recently laid hardcore stone surface.&nbsp; This area provides an excellent facility for those needing external yard space.&nbsp; In all the site extends to 0.36 acre or thereabouts.</p>\r\n<p><strong>SERVICES:&nbsp; </strong>Main electricity (3 phase also available nearby)</p>\r\n<p>Drainage to recently installed small treatment plant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Water, mains to site.</p>\r\n<p><strong>RATEABLE VALUE: </strong>&nbsp;Not yet assessed.</p>\r\n<p><strong>PLANNING: </strong>Planning permission was granted by Mid Devon District Council for the erection of building for B1 (light industrial use).&nbsp; Reference 05/01735/FULL.&nbsp; Copies of the planning consent can be obtained from the agents.&nbsp; An application has been submitted for B2 use.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A completion certificate for building regulations'' purposes has been issued</p>\r\n<p><strong>ENERGY PERFORMANCE CERTIFICATE: </strong></p>\r\n<p>The premises have an energy performance asset rating of G.</p>\r\n<p><strong>PRICE:&nbsp; &pound;170,000 </strong>(It is understood that there has been no election to tax the property for Value Added Tax purposes).</p>\r\n<p><strong>VIEWING: </strong>By appointment please with Messrs <strong>Thorne + Carter </strong>who hold keys</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2281, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '395', '', '', ''),
(10413, 'No Prefix', 13000, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, 'Unit D5 Devon Business Park', 'Saunders Way, Cullompton', 'EX151BS', '<ul>\r\n<li>Concessionary initial rent of &pound;13,000 for the first year and then rising to &pound;14,000 for second year and &pound;15,000 for the third.</li>\r\n<li>Modern Unit of 286 square metres (3085 square feet).</li>\r\n<li>On an attractive modern Devon Business Park, Cullompton.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-justify: newspaper; text-align: justify; text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #111111; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; language: en-GB; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB">SITUATION: </span><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #111111; font-size: 11pt; language: en-GB; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB">On the attractive modern Devon Business park at the entrance of Saunders Way, Kingsmill Industrial Estate and occupying a particularly<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>accessible position 300 metres from Junction 28 on the M5 Motorway and about half a mile from the centre of the expanding town of Cullompton (population 8,000).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span>Exeter is 13 miles, Taunton 18 miles, Tiverton 7 miles, the North Devon Link Road and Tiverton Parkway Rail Station 4.5 miles, Exeter Airport 10 miles and the Roscoff Ferry at Plymouth 55miles.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp; </span><!--?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" ?--></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-justify: newspaper; text-align: justify; text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-justify: newspaper; text-align: justify; text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #111111; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; language: en-GB; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB">TYPE: </span><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #111111; font-size: 11pt; language: en-GB; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-family: Arial; mso-greek-font-family: Arial; mso-cyrillic-font-family: Arial; mso-hebrew-font-family: Arial; mso-arabic-font-family: Arial; mso-latinext-font-family: Arial; mso-ansi-language: en-GB;" lang="en-GB">The unit is in a terrace of six on an estate of nine modern units of clear span steel portal frame type with brick faced cavity front walls to about 2.4<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>metres and other elevations and roofs of profiled PVC coated steel cladding<span style="mso-spacerun: yes;">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>incorporating roof lights internal block built perimeter walls to 2 metres. </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-justify: newspaper; text-align: justify; text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-justify: newspaper; text-align: justify; text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #111111; font-size: 11pt; font-weight: bold; language: en-GB; mso-default-font-family: Arial; mso-ascii-font-family: Arial; mso-latin-font-fam