Normal" style="mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">A deceptively spacious terraced village cottage conveniently located at the top of popular</span><span lang="en-GB"> Coldharbour only a short walk to the village centre and the highly regarded Uffculme </span><span lang="en-GB">secondary school. </span></p>', '<p>A deceptively spacious terraced village cottage conveniently located at the top of popular Coldharbour only a short walk to the village centre and the highly regarded Uffculme secondary school.&nbsp; The characterful accommodation is warmed by gas central heating and comprises a generous sitting room and dining room with kitchen on the ground floor and three good bedrooms and modern white bathroom on the first floor.&nbsp; An early interior inspection of this charming village home is strongly recommended. <br /><br />Located a short way down Coldharbour with parking available immediately outside the cottage.&nbsp; The village post office stores and Co-op being within about a quarter of a mile.&nbsp; Uffculme Village offers both secondary and primary schooling and a frequent bus service combines with the nearby M5 to facilitate rapid connections with the cathedral city of Exeter to the south and the county town of Taunton to the north.&nbsp; The nearby Tiverton Parkway mainline railway station provides a rapid link with London (Paddington).&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty.&nbsp; The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.<br /><br />Charming period town house<br />Characterful gas centrally heated accommodation<br />Hall<br />Sitting room<br />Dining room<br />Fitted kitchen<br />Three bedrooms<br />Modern white bathroom with shower<br />Small courtyard garden<br />20 miles Exeter, 16 miles Taunton<br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 3.5 miles<br />Exeter International Airport 15 miles<br />Mains electricity, water, gas and drainage<br /><br />On the ground floor<br />Heavy timber front door with glazed panel to Entrance Hall cupboard with coathooks and electricity consumer unit, ceiling beam, radiator, cottage stairs to first floor.<br />Sitting Room charming room with two windows, ceiling beam, massive inglenook with basket grate on brick hearth, mantel shelf, shelving to alcove, shelved recess, radiator, three wall light points <br />Dining Room radiator, cupboard understairs, exposed ceiling beams, attractive arch to <br />Kitchen with range of light ash effect units comprising four base cupboards, with drawers over, granite effect roll edge work tops having inset stainless steel one and a half bowl single drainer sink, mixer tap, inset ceramic hob with brushed stainless steel double oven/grill beneath, foldaway cookerhood/extractor over, three wall cupboards, space and plumbing for washing machine, additional appliance space, ceramic tiled floor, radiator, dual aspect with pretty arched window overlooking rear courtyard, downlighting, half glazed back door.<br /><br />On the first floor<br />Cottage stairs to Landing access to loft.<br />Bedroom 1 radiator.<br />Bedroom 2 radiator.<br />Bedroom 3 radiator, one wall entirely fitted wardrobes and boiler cupboard, dual aspect, outlook towards garden and Blackdown Hills to the rear,<br />Bathroom refitted with white suite comprising panelled bath, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, fully tiled walls, mains shower and shower screen, downlighting, extractor, chrome ladder style towel rail/radiator.<br /><br />Outside<br />Rear courtyard, largely walled with tiled coping, ideal for alfresco entertaining and assorted container grown plants and shrubs. <br /><br /></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2648, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10584, 'No Prefix', 100, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, 'Chestnut Barn', 'Broadclyst, Exeter', 'EX5 3JL', '<ul>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">WORKSHOP STORAGE UNIT 145sq m (1,558 sq ft)</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Excellent head room, accessible rural site just off B3181 road</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Broadclyst half a mile,&nbsp;Exeter centre&nbsp;6 miles</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">M5&nbsp; Junction 29 </span><span lang="en-GB">4 miles and Cullompton and M5 Junction 28 is 6.5 miles</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">An end unit&nbsp;in a steel frame building with corrugated steel cladding.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT&mdash;16.32m x 8.87m x5.69m to eaves.&nbsp; A clear span area with concrete floor and good natural roof lighting.&nbsp; Entrance doors 4.4m wide x 3.5m high overall.&nbsp; Electric lighting and power point. .Water point.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>SECURITY:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A security camera will be installed on site.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>OUTSIDE:</strong>&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">At the front of the unit there is a large hardcore surface, communal turning and parking area.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>TOILETS:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Communal toilet block on site. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:&nbsp; </span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main water is laid on to the premises.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Mains electricity</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">BUSINESS RATES</span><span lang="en-GB">:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Not yet assessed.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">In view of the current concessions any business able to qualify as a &lsquo;small business&rsquo; will be able to benefit from very low chargeable rates if indeed rates are payable at all.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>PLANNING:</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The Unit has in effect planning consent for Use Classes B1 (light industrial) and B8 (storage and distribution)&mdash;a notification having been submitted to the East Devon District Council</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">RENT</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>:</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&pound;100.00&nbsp; per week </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">AGREEMENT:</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>&nbsp;</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises are available on flexible terms for periods anticipated to be 1-3 years.&nbsp; The tenant will be responsible for the cost of the tenancy agreement of &pound;250 plus VAT.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">ENERGY PERFORMANCE CERTIFICATE:&nbsp;</span></strong><span lang="en-GB"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">As the premises are not heated no Energy Performance Assessment has been carried out.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2546, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'per week', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10553, 'No Prefix', 173, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Unit 8, Beare Works', 'Broadclyst, Exeter, ', 'EX5 3JX', '<ul>\r\n<li>To Let &pound;173 pw&nbsp;or For Sale</li>\r\n<li>(Particularly good value for internet trading)</li>\r\n<li>Updated&nbsp;Business Unit with Parking.</li>\r\n<li>361 sq metres (3,890 sq ft) including mezznine 126 sq metres</li>\r\n<li>On a small well presented industrial estate in predominantly rural location adjoining the B3181 road from Exeter&nbsp;to Cullompton</li>\r\n<li>The M5 motorway junction 28 is 5.5 miles at Cullompton. Exeter (7 miles).</li>\r\n<li>A refurbished unit with insulated profile steel sheet, external elevations and roof.</li>\r\n<li>Adjoins M5 motorway</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">ACCOMMODATION</span><span lang="en-GB">:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Production/Storage Area</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">14m x 12.7m with entrance doors&mdash;1.94m x 2.12m eaves height of about 4.26m, extensive roof lights affording natural lighting, entrance door 1.94m x 2.12m (could be enlarged if required).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A mezzanine approx 12.7m x 10.7m is currently fitted but could if required be removed.&nbsp; It has a fireboard soffit below leaving a headroom of 2.2m and minimum headroom above of 1.8m approx minimum at roof trusses but rising between.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office Accommodation </span><span lang="en-GB">Comprisiing:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 1&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.47m x 2.01m, double doors to production area.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 2&nbsp; 4.66m x 2.33 m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 3&nbsp; 4.38m x 2.89m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 4&nbsp; 2.81m x 2.79m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 5/store 4m x 3.07m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen 2.75m x 1.47 m with working surface, cupboards, stainless steel sink, water heater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WC suitable for disabled. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">OUTSIDE:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">4 parking spaces (more available if required). </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">ADDITIONAL:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">An adjoining fenced and concrete surfaced compound of approx 600 sq m may also be available if required by negotiation and in which case the landlord would be prepared to consider installing a roller shutter door in the unit.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Electricity, water (metered), private drainage. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">BUSINESS RATES: </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">(Obtained by telephone enquiry of East Devon District Council)</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rateable Value: &pound;11,000.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>&nbsp;TERMS</strong>:&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">The premises are available on a new medium to long term lease at a rent of &pound;173 per&nbsp;week plus VAT. </span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;VIEWING: </span></strong><span lang="en-GB">By appointment through the sole joint agents&mdash;Thorne &amp; Carter 01884 33333 (Mr Clive Madge, cmadge@thorneandcarter.co.uk) or Stratton Creber, 01392 202203 (Andrew Hoskin, Andrew@sccexeter.co.uk).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2508, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'pw plus VAT', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10598, 'No Prefix', 212000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 3, '3 Linnet Dene', 'Linnet Dene, Cullompton', 'EX15 1UF', '<ul>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Modern detached three bedroom home</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Gas central heating and UPVc double glazing</span></li>\r\n<li>Sitting room</li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Superbly appointed family Kitchen/breakfast room</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Updated bathroom</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Garage and parking</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Hard landscaped gardens</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">15 miles Exeter, 18 miles Taunton</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Main electricity, water, gas and drainage</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Nestling in a tiny cul-de-sac in this sought after setting close to Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centre towards the western outskirts of town.&nbsp; Cullompton provides a useful range of high street shops and two supermarkets whilst also being well placed for the two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school and sports centre.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The spectacular National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Half glazed front door to entrance </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> with side window, radiator, coat hook, timber effect laminate flooring.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> fireplace with marble effect hearth housing electric living flame effect fire, continuation of timber effect laminate flooring, television aerial point.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> superb family room having been refitted with extensive range of pale ash coloured units comprising five base cupboards most with drawers over, integrated Zanussi washing machine, integrated refrigerator, roll edged granite effect work tops having lovely natural stone tiled splashback, nine matching eye level wall cabinets with work top down lighting, inset four ring brushed stainless steel gas hob with brush stainless steel double oven beneath, stainless steel cooker hood over, inset one and half bowl stainless steel single drainer sink, slate flooring, radiator, down lighting, outlook over rear garden, sliding patio door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory</span><span lang="en-GB"> with brick lower walling and UPVc picture windows on three sides, sliding patio door to garden, timber effect laminate flooring, radiator, vertical blinds, spotlighting.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Inner </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> with back door leading to side access and rear garden, radiator, stairs to the first floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> white suite comprising close coupled WC, washbasin, radiator, window.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the First Floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">L-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> with window, access to loft, airing cupboard with factory lagged hot water cylinder, slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> outlook over rear garden, radiator, range of his and hers fitted double wardrobe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite Shower Room </span><span lang="en-GB">with corner entry shower, mains mixer, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, extractor, window.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, range of triple fitted wardrobes.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, fitted triple wardrobe.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Family </span><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> recently updated, panelled bath with mains shower over, shower curtain and rail, low level WC with concealed cistern, vanity wash basin with cupboards beneath, part tiled walls, window, extractor, chrome ladder style towel rail/radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p>Outside</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The property is approached off a small cul-de-sac over an extended drive providing parking for two vehicles and leading to the semi integral </span><span lang="en-GB">Garage</span><span lang="en-GB"> with light and power, wall mounted gas fired boiler, up and over door, communicating door to inner hall.&nbsp; Lawned front garden with shrubbery, side pedestrian access with timber gate leading to back door and rear garden, being partially hard landscaped with extensive paved patio and raised gravel areas ideal for alfresco entertaining. Garden </span><span lang="en-GB">Shed</span><span lang="en-GB">.&nbsp; Fully fenced, outside water tap.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2561, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', '');
