:ext="view" color="black [0]" color2="white [7]"/>\r\n   <o:column v:ext="view" color="black [0]" color2="white [7]"/>\r\n  </v:stroke>\r\n  <v:shadow color="black [0]"/>\r\n  <o:extrusion v:ext="view" backdepth="0" viewpoint="0,0" viewpointorigin="0,0"/>\r\n  <v:textbox inset="2.88pt,2.88pt,2.88pt,2.88pt"/>\r\n  <o:colormenu v:ext="edit" fillcolor="blue [1]" strokecolor="black [0]"\r\n   shadowcolor="#ccc [4]"/>\r\n </o:shapedefaults><o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">\r\n  <o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1"/>\r\n </o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Clover Drive lies towards the southern outskirts of town with views towards Padbrook Golf Course and Bradninch Hill.&nbsp; Cullompton offers a range of high street shops together with two supermarkets, two doctor surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, community centre, library, sports centre and golf course with leisure centre.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the County Town of Taunton.&nbsp; The stunning National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Individual extended family home</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Gas central heating and UPVc double glazing</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Hall with cloakroom</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Fine sitting room with woodburner</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Spacious family kitchen/dining room</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Master bedroom with ensuite</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Three further bedrooms</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Family bathroom</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Double width drive</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">South facing rear garden</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">15 miles Exeter, 18 miles Taunton</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Exeter International Airport 15 miles</span></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;<span lang="en-GB">Main electricity, water, gas and drainage</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Canopy entrance porch with tiled roof to glazed hardwood front door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> with radiator, timber floor, understairs cupboard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> timber effect flooring, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, window.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> a fine south facing room being considerably extended, dual aspect, outlook over rear garden, patio door, continuation of timber flooring, three radiators, Esse woodburing stove set on slate plinth, built in cupboard, wall light point.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room </span><span lang="en-GB">glorious family room with ceramic tiled floor, the kitchen end being well appointed with range of cream shaker style units comprising eight base cupboards most with drawers over, drawer pack, timber effect work tops having inset stainless steel one and half bowl single drainer sink, mixer tap, ceramic hob with cooker hood/extractor over, tall housing with eye level double oven/grill, eleven wall cupboards, two with glazed doors, sliding patio door, breakfast bar, spacious dining area currently easily accommodating refectory style table with seating for TEN, continuation of ceramic tiled floor, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room </span><span lang="en-GB">with three base cupboards, work tops, six wall cupboards, timber effect flooring, space for deep freeze.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Play Room/Laundry Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> this room comprises the front section of the original garage, plumbing for washing machine, wall mounted gas boiler.</span></p>\r\n<p><!--[if !mso]>\r\n<style>\r\nv\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\no\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\nb\\:* {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\n.shape {behavior:url(#default#VML);}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--></p>\r\n<p><!--[if pub]><xml>\r\n <b:Publication type="OplPub" oty="68" oh="256">\r\n  <b:OhPrintBlock priv="30E">281</b:OhPrintBlock>\r\n  <b:NuDefaultUnits priv="1004">1</b:NuDefaultUnits>\r\n  <b:DptlPageDimensions type="OplPt" priv="1211">\r\n   <b:Xl priv="104">7560000</b:Xl>\r\n   <b:Yl priv="204">10692000</b:Yl>\r\n  </b:DptlPageDimensions>\r\n  <b:DxlDefaultTab priv="1504">359410</b:DxlDefaultTab>\r\n  <b:OhGallery priv="180E">259</b:OhGallery>\r\n  <b:OhFancyBorders priv="190E">261</b:OhFancyBorders>\r\n  <b:OhCaptions priv="1A0E">257</b:OhCaptions>\r\n  <b:OhQuillDoc priv="200E">276</b:OhQuillDoc>\r\n  <b:OhMailMergeData priv="210E">262</b:OhMailMergeData>\r\n  <b:OhColorScheme priv="220E">279</b:OhColorScheme>\r\n  <b:DwNextUniqueOid priv="2304">1</b:DwNextUniqueOid>\r\n  <b:IdentGUID priv="2A07">0``````````````````````</b:IdentGUID>\r\n  <b:DpgSpecial priv="2C03">5</b:DpgSpecial>\r\n  <b:FWorkpaneVisible priv="3900">False</b:FWorkpaneVisible>\r\n  <b:CTimesEdited priv="3C04">1</b:CTimesEdited>\r\n  <b:NuDefaultUnitsEx priv="4104">1</b:NuDefaultUnitsEx>\r\n  <b:OhImpositionEngine priv="440E">285</b:OhImpositionEngine>\r\n </b:Publication>\r\n <b:PrinterInfo type="OplPrb" oty="75" oh="281">\r\n  <b:OhColorSepBlock priv="30E">282</b:OhColorSepBlock>\r\n  <b:FKOBlackFills priv="A00">True</b:FKOBlackFills>\r\n  <b:OpmOutsidePrintMode priv="B04