it" fillcolor="blue [1]" strokecolor="black [0]"\r\n   shadowcolor="#ccc [4]"/>\r\n </o:shapedefaults><o:shapelayout v:ext="edit">\r\n  <o:idmap v:ext="edit" data="1"/>\r\n </o:shapelayout></xml><![endif]--></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">L-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> with access to loft, airing cupboard housing Megaflow hot water tank with slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, fitted wardrobe with hanging rail and shelving, fitted double wardrobe again with hanging rail and extensive shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite Shower Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> spacious room originally having been a bedroom, fitted with extra large shower having mains mixer, vanity washbasin with cupboards beneath, close coupled WC, part tiled walls, radiator, extractor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, range of triple fitted wardrobes with sliding doors.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, pedestal basin.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, dual aspect, fitted cupboard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Family Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> white suite, bath with mixer tap and mains shower over, shower curtain and rail, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, ladder style radiator/towel rail, shaver point, extractor, window, timber effect flooring.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Double width drive with gravel area adjoining having central lawn with specimen weeping crab apple, side pedestrian access to south facing rear garden, workshop having work bench, shelving and adjoining log store, covered storage area and wheelie bin store, two paved areas ideal for alfresco entertaining, water feature, ash tree, fully fenced and providing a safe environment for children and pets.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2660, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10643, 'No Prefix', 194000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 3, '6 Chapel Hill', 'Chapel Hill, Uffculme', 'EX15 3AD', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>This charming double fronted stone cottage is pleasantly situated just off the village square within a few hundred yards of thriving Uffculme School. The cottage boasts very spacious and open plan living downstairs with 3/4 bedrooms and everything having been updated in a contemporary style.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">This charming double fronted stone cottage is pleasantly situated just off the village square within a few hundred yards of thriving Uffculme School.&nbsp;&nbsp; The cottage benefits from UPVc double glazed windows and the oil fired Rayburn cooker in the kitchen runs a number of radiators in addition to providing hot water and cooking, whilst at the same time making the kitchen/breakfast room the social hub of this period home.&nbsp; On the first floor two double bedrooms, a child&rsquo;s nursery and the excellent refitted bathroom are to be found, whilst a concealed cottage staircase provides access to the second floor attic bedroom with its wealth of exposed timbers and store room off.&nbsp; The gardens to the rear offer an entertaining area in addition to a kitchen garden and an early inspection is recommended to those seeking a deceptively spacious cottage in this sought after Culm Valley Village.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Located a short way up Chapel Hill about 200 metres from the village centre with its One Stop Shop, post office stores, pub and both secondary and primary schooling.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; A more extensive range of shopping, schooling and transport facilities is to be found in the nearby towns of Cullompton and Wellington whilst the M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Timber panelled front door to entrance </span><span lang="en-GB">Lobby </span><span lang="en-GB">coat hooks, electric consumer unit, twin part glazed inner front doors to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Lounge/Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> two windows both, with window seats, exposed wall timbers with built in desk, open tread stairs to first floor, beamed ceiling traditional fireplace with marble hearth and inset gas coal effect fire, floor to ceiling shelved recess, ancient traditional ledged door with Suffolk catch to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with extensive range of traditional Shaker style units comprising four base cupboards, drawer pack, tall cupboard, timber effect roll edged work tops with matching up stand, three wall cupboards, inset Asterite single drainer sink, mixer tap, space and plumbing for dishwasher and washing machine, fireplace recess housing twin oven Rayburn Royal oil fired cooker, providing hot water and radiators, walk in larder/store, fitted larder cupboard, shelved recess, ceiling beam, half glazed UPVc back door, delightful exposed stone walling and brick arch.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with work top and more exposed stone walling, space for fridge freezer and refrigerator.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">L-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, door leading to continuation of staircase to second floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1, </span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;lovely south facing room enjoying a village outlook to Gaddon Woods, radiator, fitted double wardrobe with hanging rail and cupboards over.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2,</span><span lang="en-GB"> south facing with village views, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Nursery/Bedroom 3, </span><span lang="en-GB">exposed wall timbers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> particularly spacious with exposed timber flooring, P-shaped bath with Triton electric shower over, folding shower screen, mixer tap/shower attachment, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, window, airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder, shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4, </span><span lang="en-GB">glorious attic room with a wealth of exposed trusses, rafters and purlins, window enjoying fabulous outlook over the roof tops across the valley to Blackdown Hills, door to store room.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rear courtyard with steps to extensive paved terrace with built in BBQ ideal for alfresco entertaining.&nbsp; Kitchen garden, beyond which lies the </span><span lang="en-GB">Greenhouse </span><span lang="en-GB">and garden </span><span lang="en-GB">Shed.</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; Oil tank.&nbsp; Perimeter hedging and fencing offering a surprising degree of privacy and enjoying far reaching country views.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2611, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10502, 'No Prefix', 179950, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Sale Agreed', 4, 'HOLCON HOUSE, 44 HIGH STREET, CULLOMPTON', 'High Street, Cullompton', 'ex151ae', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Deligthfully restored Georgian town house, grade II listed, gas c/heating, hall, dining room, drawing room, study, well appointed kitchen, 26'' summer sitting room, 4 bedrooms, luxury bathroom with separate shower, courtyard garden, shed.</span></p>', '<p>A rare opportunity to acquire a fine</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>GEORGIAN PERIOD TOWN HOUSE</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">which by virtue of its very central setting and previous use as a hairdressing business and popular restaurant is well suited to other business enterprises or it may simply be enjoyed as a spacious period home.&nbsp; The elegant accommodation exhibits many period features associated with a Grade II listed home of this age.&nbsp; The rooms are particularly well proportioned with high elegant 10ft ceilings.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">On the Ground Floor:-</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Heavy timber front door with original pretty fanlight over to</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Gracious HALLWAY long with tiled floor, dado panelling, decorative wall panels, twin glass paned doors with fanlight over to INNER HALL.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">STUDY with part glazed door, traditional fireplace surround, twin tall arched recesses to either side, tiled floor, dado panelling, concealed radiator, telephone point, sash window with shutters, window seat.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">DRAWING ROOM shuttered sash window, window seat, large fireplace housing multi fuel cast iron stove, traditional timber fire surround, dado panelling, concealed radiator, coved ceiling, wide archway to</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">DINING ROOM traditional timber fireplace with multi fuel stove, tiled hearth, twin doors to conservatory.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">INNER STAIRCASE HALL with elegant easy rising stairs having storage beneath, radiator, twin glass paned doors to conservatory, arch to</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">KITCHEN pale maple effect range of units, five base cupboards, integrated refrigerator, freezer and dishwasher, granite working surfaces and curved solid beech work top, curved granite work top to alcove with inset four ring gas hob, double oven under, extractor fan over, large vitreous white double drainer sink unit with mixer tap over, twelve wall cupboards, gas boiler, radiator, tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">CONSERVATORY/SUMMER SITTING ROOM delightful bright and airy room with masonry lower walls and timber double glazed picture windows above, clear glass roof, twin doors to courtyard garden, useful UTILITY AREA with space and plumbing for washing machine, tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">On the First Floor:-</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Elegant easy rising turning staircase with half landing well lit by flank window to</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">LARGE LANDING radiator, loft access.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">BEDROOM 1 sash window, window seat, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">BEDROOM 2 radiator, hot water cylinder.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">BEDROOM 3 radiator, pretty cast iron Victorian basket fire and surround, shelved recess.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">BEDROOM 4 radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">BATHROOM superbly appointed room with much handcrafted timber joinery including large white corner Jacuzzi bath with timber panelling and granite surround, white WC with concealed cistern, vanity washbasin with cupboard beneath in granite work top, large tiled shower cubicle, shelved recess with cupboards under, feature stained glass mirror, radiator, half tiled walls.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span><span lang="en-GB">:-</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">Rear pedestrian access leads to the walled landscaped rear garden with pedestrian access having door leading down three brick steps to a paved area with additional second paved seating area with garden lighting and power point ideal for barbecues etc, stone and slate garden store with light and power connected, covered bin storage area, outside tap, the whole offering a surprising degree of privacy.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; Main electricity, water, drainage and gas.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span lang="en-GB">FIXTURES AND FITTINGS:&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">The floor coverings are included in the sale price.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2426, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', '');
