ang="en-GB">and </span><span lang="en-GB">Storage Facilities</span><span lang="en-GB"> having light and power,&nbsp; Vokera gas boiler, doors to garden and twin double doors to the garage end approached by shared driveway with adjoining property.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2601, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10560, 'No Prefix', 275000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Hidden', 4, '6 Lower Town, Sampford Peverell', 'Lower Town, Sampford Peverell', 'EX16 7BJ', '<ul>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Well proportioned double fronted period village home</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">4/5 bedrooms</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">2/3 reception rooms</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Family kitchen/breakfast room</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Cobbled courtyard</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Outbuilding</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Large surprisingly private gardens</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Gas central heating, UPVc double glazing</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">20 miles Exeter, 19 miles Taunton</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 1 miles</span></li>\r\n<li><span lang="en-GB">Main electricity, water, gas and drainage</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Enjoying a setting in the older part of the sought after village of Sampford Peverell with its primary school, village stores and two pubs whilst being within the catchment for the highly regarded Uffculme school.&nbsp; The nearby towns of Cullompton and Tiverton provide a more extensive range of shopping, schooling and transport facilities.&nbsp; The M5 intersection provides rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; Lovely walks are to be enjoyed along the towpath of the Grand Western Canal which actually adjoins the garden and cobbled courtyard of the property with a door providing direct access.&nbsp; The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Part glazed front door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Entrance hall </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, lovely original tiled floor, understairs cupboard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting room </span><span lang="en-GB">fine through room (originally two rooms), open fireplace with basket grate, built in cupboard with ancient stripped pine door, rear outlook over courtyard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Study dual aspect, radiator, stripped timber floor, built in full height double cupboard to alcove.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining room </span><span lang="en-GB">excellent family room being dual aspect with slate tiled floor, radiator, door to rear cobbled courtyard, wide arch to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Farmhouse style family kitchen/breakfast room </span><span lang="en-GB">range of base units comprising eight base cupboards some with drawers over, drawer pack, wine rack, beech work tops with inset five ring gas hob, double oven under and brushed stainless steel cooker hood over, twin bowl vitreous enamel sink, space and plumbing for washing machine, dishwasher and tumble dryer, tall cupboard, five wall cupboards, continuation of slate tiled floor from dining room, half glazed back door to cobbled courtyard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rear porch/boot room </span><span lang="en-GB">with half glazed door.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Elegant turning staircase to long </span><span lang="en-GB">landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> with window having views to Blackdown Hills and distant Sidmouth Gap.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1 </span><span lang="en-GB">radiator, views to Blackdowns, door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4 </span><span lang="en-GB">(we are currently unable to enter this room as it has been securely locked by the owner during the period of the tenancy) approached only from bedroom 1 and ideal for creation of ensuite and/or dressing room.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2 </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect, radiator, views to Blackdown Hills.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3 radiator, views towards parish church over Grand Western Canal.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom with WC suite and wash basin.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Inner landing with walk in linen cupboard with slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Large bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">with suite in white comprising panelled bath, close coupled WC, wash basin, separate shower with Mira mains mixer, window, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p>Outside</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="en-GB">Grassed front garden with four steps leading to front door.&nbsp; Awkward vehicular access suitable only for a small car leading to the cobbled rear courtyard and adjoining single storey outbuilding about 40&rsquo; x 12&rsquo; remarkably private large mostly walled garden with extensive lawn, neglected greenhouse, area of soft fruit, paved patio, adjoining the Grand Western Canal.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2558, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', '');
