(10593, 'No Prefix', 314500, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 4, 'Oasis', 'Jarmans Court, Cullompton', 'EX15 1JS', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>A great opportunity to acquire an individual modern detached family home, in a setting within one minutes walk of the facilities offered by Cullompton High Street. Accommodation includes 4 bedrooms, one with en suite, kitchen, lounge, dinning room, study and huge conservatory. Walled private garden.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Nestling at the end of the tiny cul-de-sac of Jarmans Court, Oasis, is as the name suggests a haven of tranquillity within a 100m level walk of Cullompton High Street.&nbsp; The town offers a range of high street shops, two supermarkets, two primary schools, two doctors surgeries, sports centre and the highly regarded Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centre.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural&nbsp; pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; Lovely walks are also to be enjoyed in the grounds of Knightshayes Court and Killerton House both of which are fine National Trusts country houses in their own spectacular gardens and grounds.&nbsp; The picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Canopy entrance porch to half glazed timber panelled front door to impressive entrance </span><span lang="en-GB">Hall</span><span lang="en-GB"> with elegant staircase to first floor, double cloaks cupboard with hanging rail and shelving, radiator, timber laminate flooring.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Cloakroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> with close couple WC, wash basin, radiator, window, extractor fan.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> fine dual aspect room with contemporary marble effect and stainless steel surround and hearth with inset gas log effect fire, two radiators, television point, two side windows with views towards parish church, sliding patio door to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Conservatory</span><span lang="en-GB"> impressive south east facing room with brick lower walls and hardwood double glazed picture windows and clear glass roof, ceramic tiled floor, two sliding patio doors, one to rear garden and the other the loggia.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with continuation of timber effect laminate flooring, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Study</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, outlook over front garden, continuation of timber effect laminate flooring.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen </span><span lang="en-GB">having range of mid oak units comprising eight base cupboards most with drawers over, integrated dishwasher, roll edged work tops with inset four ring electric hob with oven under and fold away cooker hood/extractor over, Asterite one and half bowl single drainer sink, six wall cupoards, radiator, half glazed door to</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Utility</span><span lang="en-GB"> work top with base cupboard under, space and plumbing for washing machine and condenser dryer, stainless steel sink, radiator, half glazed door to conservatory.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the First Floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Fine balustraded </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> well lit by flank window, access to loft, radiator, large airing cupboard with lagged hot water cylinder, slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> impressive dual aspect room enjoying outlooks over Glebe land to distant Blackdown Hill and parish church, radiator, double fitted wardrobe with hanging rail and shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Ensuite Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> with pastel coloured suite, comprising panelled bath with mixer tap/shower attachment over, shower screen, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, fully tiled walls, light/shaver fitment, extractor fan, window.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> through room with outlook to distant Blackdown Hills, radiator, fitted double wardrobe with hanging rail and shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, double fitted wardrobe with hanging rail and shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, far reaching views.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Approached&nbsp; by a private lane through double wrought iron gates and separate pedestrian gate to tarmac drive and double </span><span lang="en-GB">Garage</span><span lang="en-GB"> power operated double up and over door, wall mounted gas fired boiler, extensive loft storage, rear personal door.&nbsp; Largely hard landscaped front garden with paved and gravelled areas, raised shrub borders with assortment of established young trees and shrubs, twin timber gates providing pedestrian access on both sides of the house to generous astonishingly private rear garden mostly lawned with extensive paved patio and loggia, entirely walled and fenced providing a safe and secure environment for both children and pets.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2556, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10616, 'No Prefix', 399995, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 5, 'Albridge House', 'Stoneyford, Cullompton', 'EX15 1NU ', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>A spacious individual family home located towards the eastern outskirts of Cullompton. Much extended and improved by the present owners over the last thirty eight years</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Located towards the eastern outskirts of Cullompton, Albridge House is within about half a mile of High Street shops and supermarket.&nbsp; The country town of Cullompton also provides two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, sports centre, library, community centre and the popular Padbrook Park golf course and leisure centre. The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The stunning National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Upvc double glazed front door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Delightful semi-octagonal </span><span lang="en-GB">entrance porch </span><span lang="en-GB">with quarry tiled floor, panelled hardwood inner front door to </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&lsquo;L&rsquo; Shaped Hall </span><span lang="en-GB">unusually wide, elegant easy rising stairs to first floor, radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sitting Room&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">spacious dual aspect room (formerly two rooms), Villager cast iron &ldquo;log burning&rdquo; stove (gas fired), two radiators, walk in under-stair cupboard.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Spectacular drawing room </span><span lang="en-GB">triple aspect, three radiators, massive stone feature fireplace and hearth housing dual fuel burning stove, sliding patio doors, shelving for hi-fi etc</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&lsquo;Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> well appointed with extensive range of light oak units&nbsp; comprising eleven base cupboards, drawer pack, worktops with inset stainless steel twin bowl single drainer sink, central island unit with breakfast bar and base cupboards, wine rack, inset four ring halogen hob, built in double oven, fitted Scandinova deep freeze and refrigerator, open shelving, wall cupboards, extractor fan/cooker hood, spot lighting, down lighting, ceramic tiled floor, dishwasher, dual aspect</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rear Porch </span><span lang="en-GB">with quarry tiled floor, half glazed back door</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped shower room </span><span lang="en-GB">with W.C., washbasin, tiled shower cubicle with electric shower, washing machine and tumble dryer, continuation of quarry tiled floor, light/shaver point, just outside the back door lies the </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Boiler house with recently installed Vaillant gas-fired boiler for hot water and heating</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1 </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect, radiator, twin upvc French Doors to large &lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped balustrade balcony part of which has polycarbonate roofing to provide all weather sitting out area</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">L&rsquo; shaped landing </span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;walk in store/linen cupboard with shelving</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2 </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect, radiator, ensuite W.C with pedestal basin and W.C. suite, extractor fan</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3 </span><span lang="en-GB">presently used as a music room with sound proofing, ensuite W.C with washbasin and W.C. Suite and vanity unit,&nbsp; extractor fan</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 4 </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect, radiator, twin upvc doors to bulastraded balcony</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 5 </span><span lang="en-GB">dual aspect, ensuite W.C with pedestal basin and close couple W.C, extractor fan</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Family bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">stylishly refitted family bathroom having corner bath with mixer tap/shower attachment, bidet, close couple W.C, pedestal basin, pea shaped corner entry shower with mains mixer, ceramic tiled floor, part tiled walls, chrome leather style towel rail/radiator</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Airing cupboard </span><span lang="en-GB">with lagged hot water cylinder, slatted shelving</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Gravelled drive leads through twin brick pillars to extensive parking and turning area adjoining which lies the attached </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Double garage </span><span lang="en-GB">with twin up-and-over doors, light and power connected, inspection pit&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office </span><span lang="en-GB">with door immediately to outside making it ideal for consulting room or running a small business, rear personal door, covered area to the side ideal for barbeques and al fresco entertaining, a few steps lead through hedging to the </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Summer house </span><span lang="en-GB">with adjoining paved terrace and large ornamental fishpond with waterfall providing a remarkably private area for outdoor entertaining with built in barbeque. </span><span lang="en-GB">Lawns flanked by established hedges affording privacy.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2585, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10609, 'No Prefix', 205000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 3, '4 Wellands Close', 'Wellands Close, Uffculme', 'EX15 3DW', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Superbly located on the outskirts of popular Uffculme Village, this spacious semi-detached family home offers immense scope for some updating to provide an almost sem-rural home.</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Nestling in an almost semi-rural situation on the outskirts of a popular Uffculme village with its post office stores, mini market, doctors surgery, primary school, and highly regarded secondary school.&nbsp; A more extensive range of facilities are to be found in the nearby country town of Cullompton with its two supermarkets, high street shops, library, community centre, sports centre and golf course.&nbsp; The M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton, whilst the surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the Blackdown Hills providing glorious walking and being designated as an area of natural beauty.&nbsp; The stunning national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the ground floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Sliding door to enclosed entrance porch with tiled floor, part glazed UPVc inner front door to light and airy hallway, understair cupboard, radiator, recess with fitted cupboard, telephone point.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Lounge/Dining Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> a fine through room extending the full depth of the house enjoying glorious views to the front across the valley and over Uffculme Village with picture window to the rear with outlook over large mature garden and open fields and countryside beyond, tiled fireplace with inset coal effect electric fire, two radiators, television point, central heating thermostat, arched alcove with shelving and cupboard. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen/Breakfast Room</span><span lang="en-GB"> with timber effect unit comprising five base cupboards, drawer pack, stainless steel single drainer sink, four wall cupboards, two glazed, wall mounted Worcester LPG fired boiler for hot water and central heating, radiator, glorious country outlook, back door electric cooker with cookerhood/extractor over.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Shower Room </span><span lang="en-GB">having suite in white comprising corner entry shower with mains mixer, pedestal wash basin, WC plumbing for automatic washing machine.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Turning staircase to&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On the first floor</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">L-shaped </span><span lang="en-GB">Landing</span><span lang="en-GB"> with access to loft, airing cupboard housing lagged hot water cylinder, with immersion heater and slatted shelving.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 1</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, two doors to extensive boarded loft storage, lovely country views to distant Blackdown Hills</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 2</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, wonderful views across the valley and Uffculme Village.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bedroom 3</span><span lang="en-GB"> radiator, fitted double wardrobe with cupboards over, glorious country views. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom</span><span lang="en-GB"> white suite comprising panelled bath, pedestal wash basin, WC, radiator, window. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Lawned front garden with herbaceous boarder and drive leading to single </span><span lang="en-GB">garage</span><span lang="en-GB"> with light and power, up and over door 15&rsquo;9&rdquo; x 8&rsquo;.&nbsp; Wrought iron gate providing side pedestrian access to the large mature garden having irregularly shaped lawn, interspersed with well stocked borders with a variety of annual and perennial plants and many established shrubs, aluminium framed </span><span lang="en-GB">greenhouse </span><span lang="en-GB">and composting area, the whole backing onto open fields, giving the property a semi rural atmosphere.</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2582, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10460, 'No Prefix', 95, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Merrimead Farm', 'Merrimead, Five Bridges', 'EX15 1QP', '<ul>\r\n<li>Workshop/Storage Units 1,180 and 1,240 sq ft.</li>\r\n<li>Plus External space of about 0.15 acres</li>\r\n<li>The premises occupy a rural site just off the B3181 road at Five Bridges and approached from the road to Ash Thomas and Brithembottom via heavy security gate and by private drive.</li>\r\n<li>Cullompton and the M5 Motorway are 1.5 miles</li>\r\n<li>Willand 1.5 miles and Exeter 14 miles.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>TYPE OF PREMISES:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Two units in a range of 4 adjoining concrete block built workshops/stores with corrugated sheeted roofs and comprising:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT 2 59&rsquo; x 20&rsquo; with headroom of about 13&rsquo;9&rdquo;.&nbsp; Pair of heavy metal entrance doors, 16&rsquo;8&rdquo; x 15&rsquo;7&rdquo; high, overall.&nbsp; Loft over entire unit with substantially built floor but currently no stairs access.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT 3&nbsp;&nbsp; 59&rsquo;8&rdquo; x 21&rsquo; and between 9&rsquo;2&rdquo; and 13&rsquo; to undersides of roof timbers.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>OUTSIDE</strong>:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">There is an area of external space approximately 100 ft x 65 ft which is available, at a negotiated rent, for outside parking/storage in conjunction with the units.&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>SERVICES:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A portaloo is installed for use with the units.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main water and electricity are connected.&nbsp; There will be no charge for water if, as is anticipated, there is little demand.&nbsp; In the event that larger quantities are used then the landlord may sub meter it and charge tenants for amounts used.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Electricity, electrical installations of lights and power points are installed in the units and are separately metered or sub metered as appropriate.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The site is periodically monitored by an outside CCTV.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB"><strong>BUSINESS RATES:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rateable value;&nbsp; UNIT 2: &pound;3,250.&nbsp; UNIT 3: &pound;3,300.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Significant relief is available under the small business scheme and which may in certain circumstances reduce the rates payable to nil.&nbsp; Prospective tenants should make their own enquiries of Mid Devon District Council.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">RENT: </span><span lang="en-GB">Rents are sought as follows:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT 2&nbsp; &pound;105 per month.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT 3&nbsp; &pound;95 per month. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside Storage &pound;25 per week.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">AGREEMENT: </span><span lang="en-GB">The premises are available on flexible terms for periods anticipated to be 1-3 years.&nbsp; The&nbsp;&nbsp; tenant will be responsible for the cost of the tenancy agreement of &pound;275 plus VAT.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Combination of Units</span><span lang="en-GB"> - There are communicating pedestrian doors between units two and three and a prospective tenant is able to take a combination of units if required.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ENERGY PERFORMANCE CERTIFICATE:&nbsp; </span><span lang="en-GB">The energy performance asset rating of the units is G. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2649, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'to Â£105 pw', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10668, 'No Prefix', 17500, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Pickwicks', '43 Fore Street, Cullompton', 'EX15 1JT', '<ul>\r\n<li>Tea Room/Cafe/Restaurant as a going concern.</li>\r\n<li>A long established cafe/restaurant business with covers for 35.</li>\r\n<li>Occupying a double bow fronted premises it is located in the centre of Cullompton (population of about 9000 with large hinterland).</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">THE BUSINESS: </span><span lang="en-GB">Over the years it has had an excellent reputation in the town and a strong all year round following.&nbsp;&nbsp; Sales for the last two years have been in excess of &pound;70,000 with gross profit of 70% and we are advised that they are kept at this level in order to keep the turnover below the Value Added Tax.&nbsp;The business is well suited to a husband and wife team.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">HOURS: </span><span lang="en-GB">8am - 3pm Mondays to Saturdays.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">REASON FOR SALE: </span><span lang="en-GB">The proprietor is retiring owing to ill health.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PREMISES: </span><span lang="en-GB">The restaurant is located in a prime shopping position in the main street of the town in substantial premises with attractive appearance of double entrance doors flanked by small paned bow windows.&nbsp; A public car park is nearby.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ACCOMMODATION: </span><span lang="en-GB">The accommodation comprises:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Double fronted shop of internal width 8.4m (27&rsquo;6&rdquo;) narrowing to 3.35m (11&rsquo;) at the rear and a maximum depth of 9.75m (32&rsquo;).&nbsp; Rear coffee service bar.&nbsp; To one side is a very nicely fitted Preparation Room 4.69m x 3.55m (15&rsquo;5&rdquo; x 11&rsquo;7&rdquo;) with hygiene lined walls and modern tiled floor.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rear Lobby, Toilet.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">EQUIPMENT: </span><span lang="en-GB">With much recently acquired, the business is well equipped with good quality appliances almost all of stainless steel and including Kensington 5 ring ceramic hob/2 oven and grill electric cooker, tall freezer, chest freezer, extensive SS work surfaces, Bain Marie warming tray, Buffalo griddle, Buffalo double frier, 5 microwave ovens, vogue-double deep bowl SS sink, drainer cooker hood extract, racking, closed circuit TV monitor, larder fridge, carvery hot plate, soup pot, cooking utensils, 4 slice toaster.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">5 star Food Hygiene rating MDDC. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Restaurant - covers for 35 wheelback chairs and tables, ceiling fan, globe lights.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Coffee shop - Counter, stainless steel sink and drainer unit with cupboards, Expobar twin cup coffee machine, Cunill coffee grinder, Bravilo filter coffee machine on loan from coffee bean supplier, Ceado milk shake machine, Hotpoint fridge, hotwater boiler, Triton water heater 2, adjustable, Pendant down lighters, work surfaces.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">LEASE: </span><span lang="en-GB">The business is offered with the benefit of a 10 year lease of the premises and of which two years are unexpired.&nbsp; The rent is &pound;7,500 per annum.&nbsp; The purchaser will be asked to pay the landlords legal costs in connection with the assignment of the lease.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Alternatively it is understood that the landlord is prepared to consider the grant of a new lease. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PRICE: </span><span lang="en-GB">The business is available for purchase as a going concern including goodwill, equipment and the benefit of the lease in the sum of &pound;17,500 plus stock at valuation. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2650, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10634, 'No Prefix', 4750, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, '62 Fore Street', 'Fore Street, Cullompton', 'EX15 1LB', '<p><span lang="en-GB">LOCK-UP SHOP PREMISES</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Of about 45.5 square metres (490 square feet)</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">In a prime trading position practically opposite the Post Office; with frontage to the main street of this busy growing town (population 8,500 approximately), in which considerable residential and commercial development is planned.</span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">LOCK-UP SHOP PREMISES</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Of about 45.5 square metres (490 square feet)</span></p>\r\n<p>In a prime trading position practically opposite the Post Office; with frontage to the main street of this busy growing town (population 8,500 approximately), in which considerable residential and commercial development is planned.</p>\r\n<p>The town is conveniently located just off the M5 motorway at Junction 28, the City of Exeter is 13 miles and Taunton 19 miles, Tiverton is 6 miles.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">DESCRITPTION:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SHOP 5.48m x 4.61m deep with attractive black and white tessellated tile floor, very large display windows of almost full storey height and for full width of shop, side entrance door.&nbsp; Spot and fluorescent lights.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SECONDARY RETAIL AREA/ANTE ROOM 4.6m x 4.0m (_________ average).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">KITCHENETTE AREA with sink and water heater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WC</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PARKING:&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">For one (small) vehicle at the rear of the shop.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main water, electricity and drainage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Gas is nearby.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PLANNING: </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises have been used as a retail shop for many years.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">RATES:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On verbal enquiry made of the Mid Devon District Council we are advised that the Rateable Value of the premises is &pound;5,000.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">RATES PAYABLE 2014/15:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Assuming no other business premises are occupied elsewhere by the tenant and the tenant qualifies as a &ldquo;small business&rdquo; the rates payable for 2014/15 should be nil until 31st March 2014 (concessions after 31st March 2014 have not yet been announced). </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">LEASE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises are available at a rent of &pound;4,750 per annum.&nbsp; There will be three year rent reviews.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">VIEWING:</span><span lang="en-GB"> Interested parties may view the premises by appointment through the agents, Thorne &amp; Carter, 01884 33333.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">CONDITION OF PROPERTY:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kindly note that for sale purposes neither the seller nor Thorne + Carter have had a survey of the property carried out.&nbsp; Consequently no warranty can be either given or implied as to the condition thereof nor of any of the appliances, equipment, fixtures or fittings.&nbsp; Should assurance on condition be required a prospective buyer is advised to obtain verification from their own independent research and enquiry.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">MISREPRESENTATION DISCLAIMER:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Any representation made either by the seller or their Agents whether orally or in writing and whether made prior hereto or contained herein, is believed to be correct but its accuracy is not guaranteed.&nbsp; A buyer is deemed to have satisfied himself by inspection, measurement, search or otherwise that he has entered into this contract in reliance upon his own researches and not in reliance upon any such representation made by the seller or his Agents.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="en-GB">enquiries@thorneandcarter.co.uk</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2616, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', 'per annum', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
