r\n   </b:OplEcp>\r\n   <b:OplEcp type="OplEcp" priv="511">\r\n    <b:Color>16737792</b:Color>\r\n   </b:OplEcp>\r\n   <b:OplEcp type="OplEcp" priv="611">\r\n    <b:Color>13382502</b:Color>\r\n   </b:OplEcp>\r\n   <b:OplEcp type="OplEcp" priv="711">\r\n    <b:Color>16777215</b:Color>\r\n   </b:OplEcp>\r\n  </b:Rgecp>\r\n  <b:SzSchemeName priv="618">Bluebird</b:SzSchemeName>\r\n </b:ColorScheme>\r\n <![if pub11]>\r\n <![endif]>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if pub]><xml>\r\n <b:Page type="OplPd" oty="67" oh="265">\r\n  <b:PtlvOrigin type="OplPt" priv="511">\r\n   <b:Xl>22858575</b:Xl>\r\n   <b:Yl>22852950</b:Yl>\r\n  </b:PtlvOrigin>\r\n  <b:Oid priv="605">(`@`````````</b:Oid>\r\n  <b:OhoplWebPageProps priv="90E">266</b:OhoplWebPageProps>\r\n  <b:OhpdMaster priv="D0D">263</b:OhpdMaster>\r\n  <b:PgtType priv="1004">5</b:PgtType>\r\n  <b:PtlvOriginEx type="OplPt" priv="1111">\r\n   <b:Xl>110183775</b:Xl>\r\n   <b:Yl>110178150</b:Yl>\r\n  </b:PtlvOriginEx>\r\n </b:Page>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><span>A wonderful opportunity to buy one of these early Magnus built homes constructed to a particularly high standard. As is often the case in homes of this era the garden is particularly generous and private. The kitchen/breakfast room and bathroom are very up to date and create a great first purchase</span></p>', '<p>A wonderful opportunity to buy one of these early Magnus built homes constructed to a particularly high standard with solid internal walls and traditional wooden floors. As is often the case in homes of this era the garden is particularly generous and private. Both the kitchen/breakfast room and bathroom&nbsp; are very up to date and create a great first purchase or buy to let.<br /><br />Nestling in the small cul-de-sac of Lime Crescent in popular Willand with its One Stop shop, post office stores, primary school, doctors surgery and football club. A more extensive range of facilities is to be found in nearby Cullompton with its high street shops, two supermarkets, secondary school, sports centre and Padbrook Park golf and leisure centre. The nearby M5 facilitates commuting to both the cathedral city of Exeter to the south and the county town of Taunton to the north. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the Blackdown hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty.<br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Stylish semi detached Magnus home<br />Tucked away cul de sac setting<br />Two good Bedrooms<br />Refitted kitchen breakfast room<br />Refitted bathroom<br />Sitting room<br />Gas central heating, UPVc double glazing<br />Easy reach of Cullompton and M5<br />Large garden shed<br />Decked alfresco area<br />17 miles Exeter<br />4 miles Tiverton parkway<br />Mains electricity, gas, water and drainage<br /><br /><br /><br />On the ground floor<br />Roof tiled entrance porch with UPVc double glazed door leading to entrance hall.<br />Hall space to hang coats, stairs to first floor.<br />Sitting room lovely bright and airy room with a large UPVc window enjoying outlook over the front garden, telephone and television points, radiator.<br />Kitchen/ Breakfast room modern dark oak effect units comprising four base cupboards, 2 with drawers over, six wall mounted cupboards, marble effect roll edge worktop, inset stainless steel single drainer sink, inset gas hob with extractor over, electric oven, space and plumbing for washing machine, space for fridge, boiler, tile effect laminate flooring, space for table, access to useful under stairs storage. Delightful outlook over rear garden and door opening out onto the garden.<br /><br />On the first floor<br />Landing with access to loft, window and airing cupboard housing hot water tank.<br />Bedroom 1&nbsp; a double room, two built in wardrobes/cupboards providing excellent storage, radiator, large window making it a very light room, overlooking the front garden.<br />Bedroom 2&nbsp; Built in wardrobe/cupboard, recess with space for shelving and chest of drawers, radiator, outlook over rear garden.<br />Bathroom with white suite comprising of panel bath with glass shower screen and mains shower over, basin with storage cupboards under, WC, radiator, two fully tiled walls and frosted glass UPVc window.<br /><br />Outside <br />A tarmac drive with parking for two/three cars, good sized front lawn hedged on two sides for privacy access to large shed which also acts as a covered walk way to rear garden. The south facing rear garden is of a good size and is mainly lawned with borders around the perimeter, housing some well established shrubs. There is a fantastic decked area at the bottom of the garden, perfect for alfresco entertaining and the garden is fenced on both sides with a wall at the end. There is a substantial garden shed to the side of the property that provides a useful amount of storage as well as pedestrian access.<br /><br /></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2622, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10699, 'Auction guide', 300000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 3, 'Drews Farm', 'Drews Farm, Ashill', 'EX15 3NJ', '<p><span>FOR SALE BY PUBLIC AUCTION. A wonderful opportunity to acquire a grade II listed small thatched farmhouse for complete renovation with paddock and nestling in a rural setting on the outskirts of highly popular Ashill village.</span></p>', '<p>A wonderful opportunity to acquire a grade II listed small thatched farmhouse for complete renovation with paddock and nestling in a rural setting on the outskirts of highly popular Ashill village. At present, the accommodation offers two reception rooms and three bedrooms, but the adjoining barn offers opportunities for extension subject to planning consents. The overgrown gardens and three small paddocks extend to about 1.3 Acres and&nbsp;offer the opportunity for the &ldquo;the good life&rdquo; or the keeping of a child&rsquo;s pony. <br /> <br />FOR SALE BY PUBLIC AUCTION ON THURSDAY 16TH APRIL 2015 AT 3PM AT THE CULLOMPTON COMMUNITY CENTRE (UNLESS PREVIOUSLY SOLD) <br /> <br />Located on the outskirts of Ashill Village at the foot of the Blackdown Hills which offer lovely riding and walking and themselves being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty. The village offers a highly regarded public house whilst being within the catchment for Uffculme school. The nearby village of Uffculme offers a post office store and One Stop shop with a more extensive range of shopping facilities being available in both Cullompton and Wellington. The M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the spectacular national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all being within a modest car journey. <br /> <br /> <br />Grade II listed thatched farmhouse for complete renovation <br />Two reception <br />Three bedrooms <br />Dilapidated outbuildings <br />Gardens and three small paddocks <br />Refitted bathroom <br />Garage and parking <br />Delightful large walled rear garden <br />20 miles Exeter, 16 miles Taunton <br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 3.5 miles <br />Main electricity, water, and drainage <br /> <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />Entrance porch with slated roof, heavy timber panelled front door. <br />Hall opening out to wider staircase hall with back door to adjoining outbuilding, walk in larder. <br />Kitchen/Breakfast Room fireplace, housing solid fuel fired Rayburn providing hot water and cooking, mantel over, fitted cupboard to one side with likelihood of massive Inglenook to be revealed, ceiling beams, three base cupboards, stainless steel sink, understairs recess. <br />Sitting Room outlook to the front, Victorian cast iron fireplace with timber mantel and likelihood of massive Inglenook to be revealed, ceiling beam. <br />Side Hall with side door to rear garden. <br />Bathroom white bath with electric shower over, wash basin, WC, plumbing for washing machine. <br /> <br />On the first floor <br />Landing approached by cottage staircase. <br />Bedroom 1 two windows overlooking front garden with window seat, cruck beams, door to WC with wash basin and extractor fan. <br />Bedroom 2 dual aspect, country views, exposed beams. <br />Bedroom 3 outlook over front garden, exposed beams, airing cupboard with hot water cylinder. <br /> <br />Outside <br />Approached from the back door is a dilapidated outbuilding/workshop 30&rsquo; x 10&rsquo; max, large dilapidated former outbuilding principally of stone and cob construction offering great potential for conversion subject to consents, about 58&rsquo; x 27&rsquo; max &lsquo;L&rsquo; shaped, made principally of stone, cob, block and brick. <br /> <br />The cottage gardens to the front and rear are rather neglected with an abundance of established trees and shrubs. Former walled kitchen garden, greenhouse. Gateway through stonewall to goat paddock with several fine specimen trees and mature hedgerow, gate to two further small paddocks. Dilapidated small stone outbuilding. <br /> <br /> In all about 1.3&nbsp;Acres. <br />&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br /> <br />Sellers Solicitors: <br />Messrs Milford &amp; Dormer, 45 Fore Street, Chard, Somerset, TA20 1PT. Tel: 01460 61000 who will be pleased to answer enquiries of a legal nature.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2638, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', 'Auction Guide', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10657, 'No Prefix', 120000, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, '29 Flightway ', 'Dunkeswell Bus Park', 'EX14 4RJ', '<ul>\r\n<li>6 miles Honiton, 23 miles Exeter, 15 miles Taunton.</li>\r\n<li>Detached modern industrial unit of 163 sq m (1750 sq ft)</li>\r\n<li>On a site of 0.817 hectare (0.2 acre)</li>\r\n<li>Price &pound;12000 + VAT freehold or to rent &pound;6,600 + VAT pa (less initial discount), owner might divde.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">LOCATION</span><span lang="en-GB">:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On a well presented modern development of units of a similar type on the outskirts of the village of Dunkeswell and near the Dunkeswell air field.&nbsp; 6 miles from A30 and Honiton, 10 miles Cullompton and Wellington, 23 miles Exeter M5. (Both with Junctions on M5). </span></p>\r\n<p>BUILDING:</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT 21.17 metres x 7.72 metres x 3.8 metres eaves height.&nbsp; A detached unit of steel portal frame construction with insulated steel clad elevations with a clear span &ldquo;clean&rdquo; space with concrete floor, good natural lighting, roller shutter doors, 3.19 metres x 3.76 metres high at each end -&nbsp; one electrically powered, separate pedestrian entrance door (light, power and drainage connected but no fittings or toilet installed).&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Note: </span><span lang="en-GB">The premises lend themselves to being divided laterally to form two separate units, front and rear, each with their own individual roller shutter door access.</span></p>\r\n<p>OUTSIDE:</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The building is approached from an adopted hammerhead of the Flightway Estate Road adjoining which there is a grassed area, suitable subject to planning as a display area.</span></p>\r\n<p>A pair of wide double security gates and flanking galvanised iron palisade security fencing lead to a concreted forecourt, 6.4 metres in front of unit and with concrete drive running along the side of the unit to concrete pad, 5 metres deep along the rear of the unit and onto which the second roller shutter door opens.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At the rear of the site is a strip of land, 48 metres x 6.2 metres average approximately with boundary backing onto the Dunkeswell - Hemyock Road.&nbsp; Post and rail fencing around.</p>\r\n<p>SERVICES:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main water, electricity (3 phase) and drainage is available on site. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">BUSINESS RATES</span><span lang="en-GB">:</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rateable Value - &pound;10,250.</span></p>\r\n<p>PLANNING:</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The Unit was built with planning consent for B1, B2 and B8 use classes.</span></p>\r\n<p>SERVICE CHARGE:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">There is an annual service charge for maintenance of landscaped areas of the estate - currently &pound;300.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PRICE</span><span lang="en-GB">:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&pound;120,000 plus VAT freehold.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Or</span><span lang="en-GB"> alternatively the premises are available to let at a rent of &pound;6,600 per annum, on full repairing and insuring terms&mdash;A discount or &ldquo;moving in allowance&rdquo; is available for the first year.</span></p>\r\n<p>Owner might divide.</p>\r\n<p>A Portacabin (5.83 x 2.22 internally) sited within the unit is available for purchase by negotiation.</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ENERGY PERFORMANCE CERTIFICATE: </span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="text-align: justify;">Energy Performance Rating &mdash; an EPC has been applied for and will be available from Thorne and Carter.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2671, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'or Â£6,000 pa rent', 'N', 'N', 'N', 