(10624, 'No Prefix', 295000, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Viewing', 3, '13a Park Close', 'Park Close, Silverton', 'EX5 4JN', '<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span>Individual detached village home in popular Silverton being within easy commuting distance of the cathedral city of Exeter. The village offers an excellent range of facilities whilst the thriving city of Exeter provides a wonderful array of shops, restaurants and culture</span></p>', '<p>Pleasantly located towards the outskirts of this much sought after village with its useful shops, post office, doctors surgery and primary school. A more extensive range of shopping, schooling and transport facilities is to be found in the nearby cathedral city of Exeter. Exeter also boasts the Princesshay shopping mall and many opportunities for entertainment and culture. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the stunning National Trust estate at Killerton providing walks through the gardens, grounds and arboretum. The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks at Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey. <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />Half glazed UPVc front door to large Hall, radiator, stairs, timber effect flooring. <br />Ground Floor Bathroom having white suite comprising &rsquo;P&rsquo; shaped bath with Mira sport electric shower over, curved shower screen, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, extractor, down lighting, shelf storage, window. <br />Sitting room fine bright and airy dual aspect room with two radiators, downlighting. Kitchen/Breakfast room, well appointed with extensive range of light ash effect units, seven base cupboards, integrated dishwasher, marble effect work tops with inset one and a half bowl stainless steel single drainer sink, five wall cupboards, additional double tall cupboard providing six cupboards, radiator, Belling range cooker with five gas rings, double oven/grill, warming oven, brushed stainless steel cooker hood over, downlighting. <br />Utility Belfast sink with adjoining work tops, space and plumbing for washing machine and tumble dryer, shelving, Worcester gas fired boiler. <br />Study radiator, telephone point. <br />Bedroom 3 radiator, French door to garden. <br /> <br />On the first floor <br />L-shaped Landing access to loft. <br />Master Bedroom glorious dual aspect room, radiator, downlighting, ensuite shower, extra wide shower cubical with mains shower, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, shaver point, extractor, downlighting. <br />Bedroom 2 another fine double room, radiator, ensuite shower room with mains shower, close coupled WC, pedestal basin, radiator, eaves access, extractor, downlighting, shaver point. <br />Bedroom 3 radiator. <br />Bathroom having white suite comprising P-shaped bath with electric shower over, curved shower screen, close coupled WC, pedestal washbasin, radiator, electric shaver point, part tiled walls, extractor fan, window. <br /> <br />Outside <br />The property is approached over a long driveway leading to a parking area with adjoining detached garage, rendered and tiled construction matching the house with light and power connected, twin timber doors and presently divided into two sections, overall dimensions 21&rsquo;6&rdquo; x 11&rsquo;3&rdquo;. Personal door, extensive loft storage area, two areas brick paved, lawn the whole being fully fenced. Timber Garden Shed.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2630, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10693, 'No Prefix', 155000, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 2, '7 College Road', 'College Road, Cullompton', 'EX15 1TG', '<p>A delightful 2 bedroom home in a very convienient location close to the towns amenities, the proerty has been recently updated and boasts a generous south facing garden with a large workshop/shed.<a href="http://www.rightmove.co.uk/property-for-sale/property-51028169.html"><br /></a></p>', '<p>This well presented modern semi detached home enjoys a tucked away setting towards the end of this small cul-de-sac just off the high street.&nbsp; With well appointed kitchen, modern white bathroom and two good bedrooms combined with enclosed south facing rear garden the property is ideally suited as a first purchase or buy to let investment.<br /><br />Tucked away in a small cul-de-sac behind the doctors surgery and vets, with the high street shops and Tesco supermarket all being within a few minutes walk.&nbsp; Cullompton offers two doctors surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, sports centre, community centre, library and golf course with leisure centre.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the County Town of Taunton.&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The stunning National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; <br /><br /><br /><br />Modern semi detached home<br />Gas central heating and UPVc double glazing<br />Hall<br />Lounge/dining room<br />Fitted kitchen<br />Modern white bathroom<br />Two bedrooms<br />Driveway with parking <br />South facing enclosed rear garden<br />15 miles Exeter, 18 miles Taunton<br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles<br />Exeter International Airport 15 miles<br />Main electricity, water, gas and drainage<br /><br /><br /><br />On the ground floor<br />Canopy porch to panelled UPVc part glazed front door.<br />Hall timber effect laminate flooring, radiator.<br />Lounge/Dining Room bright and airy through room, two radiators, understair recess ideal for computer etc, twin UPVc French doors to south facing rear garden.<br />Kitchen well appointed with white shaker style units comprising four base cupboards, timber effect roll edged worktops, inset stainless steel single drainer sink, mixer tap, space for free standing cooker, four wall cupboards, spot light array, attractive stone tiled splashback, extractor, outlook over rear garden, space and plumbing for washing machine, space for fridge freezer, timber effect laminate flooring.<br /><br />On the first floor<br />Landing access to loft.<br />Bedroom 1 radiator, double fitted wardrobe with shelving and hanging rail, deep fitted wardrobe with radiator, fitted double cupboard over stairwell with shelving and aerial for television.<br />Bedroom 2 radiator, outlook over rear garden.<br />Bathroom suite in white comprising bath with mixer tap/shower attachment over, shower curtain and rail, fully tiled surround, pedestal basin, close coupled WC, ladder style towel rail/radiator, extractor, downlighting, window.<br /><br />Outside<br />Front garden, hard landscaped with drive providing parking for two vehicles, side pedestrian gate to south facing rear garden offering a surprising degree of privacy, extensive decking and hard landscaped area, specimen tree, substantial timber Workshop/Shed.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2672, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(102202, 'No Prefix', 210, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Unit 01, Langlands', 'Unit 01 Langlands Bus Park', 'EX15 3LJ', '<ul>\r\n<li>Workshop/Storage Unit of 2760 sq ft (841 sq m)</li>\r\n<li>With compound of about 0.6 acre</li>\r\n<li>A concrete block built building</li>\r\n<li>Two entrance doors</li>\r\n<li>Fluorescent lighting and power points</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">On a large rural estate of units of a similar type just outside the village of Uffculme and with excellent access with M5 junction 27 to the north with a branch to the north Devon link road 2 miles and junction 28 of the M5 motorway at Cullompton to the south 4.5 miles.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Approached over the main estate circulation area by two accesses, one to each entrance door. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TYPE:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A concrete block built building with refurbished lined and insulated roof with headroom&nbsp; of 8&rsquo;9&rdquo; (2.7m) to 14&rsquo; (4.26m) at ridge.&nbsp; Two entrance doors, 10&rsquo;9&rdquo; (3m) x 8&rsquo;9&rdquo; (2.7m) high, fluorescent lighting and power points.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Within the main area there is an OFFICE 9&rsquo;3&rdquo; (2.81m) x 9&rsquo;6&rdquo; (2.9m) and </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">STORE 9&rsquo;6&rdquo; (2.9m) x 5&rsquo;8&rdquo; (1.8m).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">OUTSIDE:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The unit has an exclusive and mainly concreted forecourt and parking area approximately 50ft x 45ft and, in addition, parking for further cars.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Estate Toilets - the occupiers will have the use of the communal toilets.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ENERGY PERFORMANCE:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; -ms-text-justify: inter-word; mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">The Energy Performance Certificate has been applied for. </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; -ms-text-justify: inter-word; mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main electricity (3 phase) and mains water.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Private drainage.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TERMS OF OCCUPATION:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Occupation of the unit will be on the basis of an agreement on negotiated flexible terms.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">VIEWING: </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; -ms-text-justify: inter-word; mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">By appointment please with Messrs Thorne &amp; Carter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="language: en-GB; mso-ligatures: none;" lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2673, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'per week', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
