pan><span lang="en-GB">radiator.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Bathroom </span><span lang="en-GB">a particular large room with white suite, comprising bath with mixer taps/shower attachment over, shower screen, pedestal wash basin, close coupled WC, radiator, deep fitted cupboard with twin doors.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Outside</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The maisonette is approached over a flight of stairs to an area of decking immediately adjoining the front door.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2629, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10662, 'No Prefix', 139500, 'Freehold', 'Flat', 'Viewing', 1, '18 Clarks Court', 'Clarks Court, Cullompton', 'EX15 1FB', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A particularly well appointed one bedroom flat in this popular McCarthy and Stone development with its tunstal on call assistance system. All rooms and the balcony enjoy an outlook over the grounds southwest towards the parish church.</p>', '<p>A particularly well appointed one bedroom flat in this popular McCarthy and Stone development with its Tunstall on call assistance system.&nbsp; All rooms and the balcony enjoy an outlook over the grounds southwest towards the parish church.&nbsp; The property lies within the gated development only a few yards from the town centre with its range of High Street shops and two supermarkets.&nbsp; The doctors surgery is within about 200 metres.&nbsp; An early inspection of this particularly bright and airy flat with balcony is strongly recommended.<br /><br /><br />Right in the heart of town, just back from the High Street in a gated community offering great convenience combined with privacy and security.&nbsp; The country town of Cullompton provides a useful range of everyday shopping, schooling and transport facilities including a bus service to Exeter every 20 minutes.&nbsp; The nearby M5 facilitates rapid commuting south to the cathedral city of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The property enjoys distant views towards the Blackdown Hills an area designated as Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; For those wishing to enjoy the delights of Devon the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines are all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; The stunning National Trust estate at Killerton with its fine country house, gardens, grounds and arboretum lies about five miles to the south.<br /><br /><br />On same floor as entrance door<br />Lounge/Diner<br />Fully fitted kitchen<br />Modern shower room<br />Generous double bedroom<br />Balcony<br />Residents lounge<br />Laundry room<br />Professionally maintained grounds.<br />Service charge &pound;45.66 per week<br />Residue of 125 year lease<br />15 miles Exeter, 19 miles Taunton<br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles<br />Main electricity, water and drainage<br /><br /><br />Heavy panelled front door to<br />Hall deep storage cupboard housing hot water system, shelving and hanging rail.<br />Sitting/Dining Room bright and airy south westerly facing room enjoying outlook over grounds towards the parish church, night storage heater and fitted cupboard, double glazed French door with side panel to balcony with balustrading and tiled floor overlooking the gardens.<br />Kitchen well appointed with extensive range of light ash effect units comprising base cupboards, integrated refrigerator, integrated deep freeze, granite effect work tops with inset four ring ceramic hob, inset stainless steel single drainer sink, eight wall cupboards, cooker hood, AEG electric oven, electric wall heater, lovely outlook over grounds towards the parish church.<br /><br />Bedroom again enjoying outlook towards the parish church, night storage heater, range of mirror fronted fitted wardrobes.<br />Shower Room with extra large shower, mains mixer, close coupled WC, vanity wash basin with cupboards beneath, fully tiled walls, extractor, electric wall heater, light/shaver point.<br /><br />Outside<br />The flat enjoys the use of extensive landscaped grounds which are professionally maintained within the maintenance charge and offer sweeping lawns, specimen trees, outside seating area and ornamental pond.&nbsp; There is also a storage and charging area for mobility scooters together with residence lounge, laundry room and visitors flat available to rent.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2644, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(9924, 'No Prefix', 65, 'Rental', 'Commercial', 'Let', 0, 'South View Unit', 'Higher Barn, Clyst Hydon', '', '<ul>\r\n<li>Rural workshop unit of 912 sq ft.</li>\r\n<li>9 miles Exeter, 4 miles Cullompton and the M5 Junction 28.</li>\r\n<li>Clear span building 36'' x 25''3".</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION: </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Amongst a group of similar units,just outside the village of Clyst Hydon with direct access to the adopted road, 9 miles Exeter, 4 miles Cullompton and the M5 junction 28.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Approached over a parking turning area with direct access from the village road.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TYPE: </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The unit is a clear span building 36&rsquo; x 25&rsquo;3&rdquo; with headroom 8&rsquo;3&rdquo; to 11&rsquo;6&rdquo;, of concrete block built construction with lined profiled steel sheet roof, pair of sheeted entrance doors to opening 11&rsquo;10&rdquo; wide.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Fluorescent lighting and ample power points. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">OUTSIDE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The unit has an enclosed forecourt/parking area in front estate.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TOILETS:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Occupiers will have the use of the communal toilets.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main electricity and mains water.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TERMS OF OCCUPATION:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Occupation of the unit can be on flexible terms.</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2645, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'per week', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10654, 'No Prefix', 135000, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, '31 Gold Street', 'Gold Street, Tiverton', 'EX16 6QB', '<ul>\r\n<li>Lock up shop premises 71 sq m (770 sq ft)</li>\r\n<li>In a busy retail street linking the town centre to Tesco supermarket and car park.</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SITUATION AND AMENITIES: (Please note that distances are approximate) </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Close to the centre of town on a busy link street of retail frontages between the town centre and Tesco&rsquo;s supermarket and free car park.&nbsp; Tiverton is a thriving rural town, population about 20,000 with a lively modernised market and a wide extensive catchment area.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">DESCRIPTION:</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The premises were previously two lock up shops which have been amalgamated by the partial removal of the dividing wall affording a great retail space with large practically full height shop windows.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Retail shop of overall frontage about 7.75m and with a depth of 7.2m, the shop is well presented and with maximum display area by virtue of the semi division.&nbsp; Immediately to the rear is a stock room 2.2 metres deep and with bay windows.&nbsp; It is screened from the retail area by a removable partition so enlargement of the retail floor to include it.&nbsp; Deep recessed entrance door.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Small office/kiosk 1.2m x 1.32m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WC with wash basin.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Main water, electricity and drainage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">BUSINESS RATES:&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Rateable value &pound;9,100</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ENERGY PERFORMANCE RATING: F</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">PLANNING:&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">The unit has been used in A1 retail use for many years.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TENURE:</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; -ms-text-justify: inter-word; mso-pagination: widow-orphan;"><span lang="en-GB">The property offered is the freehold interest of the entire building subject to the leasehold interests to others of the basement garden flat under the rear section of the shop and the first and second floor flats above, which are all let on long term leases of 999 years from 1992 at ground rents of &pound;30 per annum.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none;"><span style="language: en-GB; mso-ligatures: none;" lang="en-GB">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2661, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', 'F', '', '', ''),
(10677, 'Offers over', 194995, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Hidden', 3, '40 Swallow Way', 'Swallow Way Cullompton', 'EX15 1GE', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>VIEWING ESSENTIAL A superbly presented one year old home in a delightful location with outlook over an open green, stunning contemporary layout comprising two receptions, well appointed kitchen, three bedrooms (one ensuite), stylish bathroom, garage and landscaped south facing garden.</p>', '<p>This almost new family home was built just over a year ago by Messrs Barratt Homes and is presented in superb order.&nbsp; Far more spacious than usual the property boasts two reception rooms, cloakroom and superbly appointed kitchen.&nbsp; Whilst on the first floor a fine master bedroom with ensuite shower, two further bedrooms and family bathroom are to be found.&nbsp; Gas central heating, high levels of insulation and double glazing ensure an economically run family home.<br /><br />Delightfully situated over looking an open green conveniently placed for High Street shops and supermarkets.&nbsp; The country town of Cullompton also offers two doctor surgeries, two primary schools, secondary school, sports centre and Padbrook Golf Course and leisure centre.&nbsp; The M5 passes the town and facilitates rapid commuting south to the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the county town of Taunton.&nbsp; The nearby Blackdown Hills are designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty where glorious walks are to be found.&nbsp; The comparatively central mid Devon location places the picturesque National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; <br /><br />Exceptionally stylish contemporary semi detached home<br />Generous gas centrally heated accommodation<br />Hall with cloakroom<br />16ft Living room<br />Dining room with bay window<br />Well appointed Kitchen<br />Master bedroom with ensuite shower<br />Two further bedrooms<br />Family bathroom<br />Garage <br />Landscaped garden<br />15 miles Exeter, 18 miles Taunton<br />Tiverton Parkway Railway Station 6 miles<br />Exeter International Airport 15 miles<br />Main electricity, water, gas and drainage</p>\r\n<p>4 years left on Barratts warranty<br />10 year NHBC warranty<br /><br />On the ground floor<br />Canopy porch with tiled roof, heavy front door to<br />Hall radiator, coats cupboard, central heating thermostat.<br />Cloakroom having close coupled WC, basin and radiator.<br />Sitting Room lovely through room with open outlook to the front, radiator, French doors to rear garden.<br />Dining Room having bay window and radiator.<br />Kitchen superbly appointed with extensive range of base and wall units, worktops with inset stainless steel sink, mixer tap, inset four ring gas hob with oven beneath and extractor fan over, space and plumbing for washing machine, space for fridge-freezer, boiler cupboard with gas boiler, under stairs storage, radiator, door to rear garden.<br /><br />On the first floor<br />Landing having access to insulated loft, linen cupboard, radiator.<br />Bedroom 1 deep recess ideal for fitted wardrobe, radiator, door to <br />Ensuite Shower with shower unit, wash basin, close coupled WC, extractor.<br />Bedroom 2 fitted cupboard, radiator.<br />Bedroom 3 radiator.<br />Family Bathroom having bath, washbasin, close coupled WC, radiator, shaver point, part tiled walls<br /><br />Outside<br />Garage in nearby block having up and over door (held on a 999 year lease).&nbsp; South facing rear garden mostly hard landscaped with patio area ideal for alfresco entertaining, corner border, the whole being fenced, side access.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2646, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10674, 'No Prefix', 199500, 'Freehold', 'Semi', 'Sale Agreed', 3, '2 Higher Orchard', 'Higher Orchard, Cullompton', 'EX15 1AN', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A delightful light and airy 3 bedroom home in one of cullomptons most secluded spots, the property enjoys high levels of privacy as well as far reaching views over the town to the blackdown hills in the distance.</p>', '<p>This spacious and individual semi detached family home enjoys a tucked away non estate setting on the western outskirts of Cullompton. The centrally heated accommodation incorporates two reception rooms, a kitchen and utility on the ground floor together with three bedrooms and a bathroom on the first floor. The property enjoys a considerably larger than usual plot with particularly generous side and rear gardens. The property will surely appeal to those seeking an individual family home in an almost semi-rural setting whilst particularly well placed for commuting by the nearby M5. <br /> <br /> <br />Tucked away at the top of Higher Orchard a small cul-de-sac only about 200 yards from the High Street shops in Cullompton. The town also offers two supermarkets, two primjary schools, secondary schooling, sports centre and the Padbrook golf course and leisure centre. The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an area of outstanding natural beauty. The comparatively central Mid Devon location places the picturesque national parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with the north and south Devon Coastlines, all within the modest car journey. <br /> <br /> <br />Spacious semi detached home <br />Semi rural non estate setting <br />Only 1/4 mile from town centre <br />Gas central heating and UPVc double glazing <br />3 good bedrooms <br />Lounge with wood burning stove <br />Dining room <br />Generous gardens <br />Exeter 15 miles and Taunton 19 miles <br />Tiverton Parkway 6 miles <br />Mains gas, electricity, water and drainage <br /> <br /> <br /> <br />On the ground floor <br />Front door to entrance porch with space and power for tumble dryer, currently used as cloakroom/boot room. <br />UVPc door to Hall with oak floor, stairs to 1st floor, under stairs storage, radiator. <br />Sitting Room lovely bright and airy room with sliding doors opening onto patio and gardens, real oak flooring, multi fuel stove, ceiling mounted remote controlled fan and light fitting. <br />Dining Room family sized room with space for a large table and chairs, outlook onto rear garden, radiator. <br />Kitchen laminate slate tiled effect floor, solid wood fronted units with five base cupboards two with drawers over, 6 wall mounted cupboards, marble effect laminate worktop with inset stainless steel single drainer sink, free standing cooker with gas hob, space and plumbing for dishwasher, large larder cupboard, space for fridge and freezer under the worktop, outlook onto green space at the front of the property. <br />Utility Room Space and plumbing for washing machine, wall mounter boiler and access to rear garden. <br /> <br />On the first floor <br />Landing with loft access, Loft has pull down ladder and is mostly boarded out for storage, window with outlook over green space. <br />Bedroom 1 large double room with huge picture window with view of the rear garden and to the distant Blackdown Hills. Light wood effect laminate floor, Airing cupboard with hot water tank, radiator. <br />Bedroom 2 another double room with light wood effect laminate floor, another large window with super far reaching views to the Blackdown Hills, radiator. <br />Bedroom 3 good single room with wood effect laminate flooring, front outlook over green space, radiator. <br />Bathroom white suite comprising pedestal basin, bath with electric shower over and WC, mainly tiled walls with wood panelled lower portion, extractor fan, radiator. <br /> <br /> <br />Outside <br /> <br />At the front of the property there is a walled garden that is gravelled for easy maintenance. To the side of the property there is parking for about three cars and scope to erect a garage. There is a south facing rear garden on two tiers that is mainly lawned and fenced on all sides, a patio area that is perfect for alfresco entertaining, steps leading to the higher tier which has two sheds both of which have power.</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2647, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', '');
