(10679, 'No Prefix', 70000, 'Freehold', 'Commercial', 'Viewing', 0, 'Units 8 & 9 Beare Works', 'Beare Works, Broadclyst', 'EX5 3JX', '<ul>\r\n<li>Two Units 3,890 sq ft and 1064 sq ft and concrete yard - 0.36 acre in all.</li>\r\n<li>On a small well presented business park adjoining the M5 Motorway in a predominantly rural location with direct access off the B3181 road from Exeter to Cullompton.</li>\r\n<li>M5 Motorway junction 28 is 5.5 miles aqt Cullompton and M5 junction 30 at Exeter is 7 miles.</li>\r\n<li>Reburbished units with insulated profile steel sheet external elevations and roofs</li>\r\n</ul>', '<p><span lang="en-GB">Approached through security gates and wide concrete access road and turning area.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">ACCOMMODATION</span><span lang="en-GB">:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT 8</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Production/Storage Area</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">14m x 12.7m with entrance doors&mdash;1.94m x 2.12m eaves height of about 4.26m, extensive roof lights affording natural lighting, entrance door 1.94m x 2.12m (could be enlarged if required).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">A mezzanine approx 12.7m x 10.7m is currently fitted but could if required be removed.&nbsp; It has a fireboard soffit below leaving a headroom of 2.2m and minimum headroom above of 1.8m approx minimum at roof trusses but rising between.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office Accommodation </span><span lang="en-GB">Comprising:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 1&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.47m x 2.01m, double doors to production area.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 2&nbsp; 4.66m x 2.33 m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 3&nbsp; 4.38m x 2.89m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 4&nbsp; 2.81m x 2.79m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 5/store 4m x 3.07m.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchen 2.75m x 1.47 m with working surface, cupboards, stainless steel sink, water heater.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">WC suitable for disabled. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">UNIT 9</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Production/Storage Area&mdash;on the ground floor (11.9m x 6m)</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">With large roller shutter door, 4.3m wide.&nbsp; Pedestrian entrance and stairs to</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">First Floor with landing</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Office 6.2m x 3.2m</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Kitchenette 2.58m x 1.38m, sink.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">EXTERNALLY:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">From the wide concrete shared access is a concreted yard area offering open storage and parking and bringing the overall area to 0.36 acre.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">An area of about 0.07 acre (unit 10B) is currently divided off and used as open storage by Mr B Mason under agreement for storage or scaffold at a rent of &pound;2,080 per annum under a three year lease which commenced on 25th August 2012. </span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">SERVICES:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">3 phase electricity, water (metered), private drainage.</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">RATEABLE VALUES:</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Unit 8&nbsp; &pound;11,000</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Unit 9&nbsp; &pound;3,050</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Unit 10B &pound;1,950</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">Unit 10A &pound;2,425 (part of concreted yard previously let separately but now vacant).</span></p>\r\n<p><span lang="en-GB">TERMS:</span><span lang="en-GB">&nbsp; The premises are available for purchase at the price of &pound;235,000 freehold plus VAT with vacant possession of all except the scaffold storage area, alternatively the units may be purchased separately for &pound;160,000 + VAT (Unit 8) and 70,000 (Unit 9).</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: justify; -ms-text-justify: newspaper; -ms-text-kashida-space: 50%; mso-pagination: none;"><span lang="en-GB">VIEWING: </span><span lang="en-GB">By appointment through the sole joint agents -Thorne &amp; Carter 01884 33333 (Clive Madge, cmadge@thorneandcarter.co.uk) or Stratton Creber, 01392 202203 (Andrew Hoskin, Andrew@sccexeter.co.uk).</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="mso-pagination: none;">&nbsp;</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2662, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'Y', 'Y', 'and Â£165000', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
(10689, 'No Prefix', 429950, 'Freehold', 'Detached', 'Sale Agreed', 4, 'Lower Yarde', 'Clyst Hydon, Cullompton', 'EX15 2ND', '<p>An individual stylish conversion of a period barn, skillfully blending the contemporary interior with traditional character. Glorious rural edge of village setting with large well tended country gardens only 12 miles from exeter.</p>', '<p>Delightfully located on the rural outskirts of popular Clyst Hydon village with its thriving primary school, cricket club and renowned Five Bells public house.&nbsp; Every day shopping facilities are to be found in nearby Cullompton with its range of high street shops, two supermarkets, two doctors surgeries, secondary school, sports centre, library and golf course with leisure centre.&nbsp; The nearby M5 facilitates rapid commuting south the Cathedral City of Exeter and north to the County Town of Taunton and beyond.&nbsp; The Tiverton Parkway Railway Station provides a rapid link with London (Paddington).&nbsp; The surrounding countryside offers a wealth of rural pursuits with the nearby Blackdown Hills being designated as an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty.&nbsp; The spectacular National Parks of Dartmoor and Exmoor together with north and south Devon coastlines all within a modest car journey.&nbsp; <br /><br />Superbly appointed conversion of traditional stone barn<br />Rural location<br />Underfloor central heating and double glazing<br />Fine kitchen/family room<br />Sitting Room<br />Study<br />3/4 bedrooms<br />Shower room<br />Fabulous bathroom<br />Large country gardens<br />Double garage<br />13 miles Exeter, 26 miles Taunton<br />Mains water and electricity, private drainage<br /><br />On the ground floor<br />Glazed front door to<br />L-shaped Hall lovely porcelain tiled floor, cottage style turning staircase, beamed ceiling, downlighting.<br />Shower Room refitted with stylish white suite comprising curved corner shower with mains shower unit, wall hung WC with concealed cistern, basin in vanity surround with cupboards beneath, central heating boiler, porcelain floor tiling, fully tiled walls.<br />Sitting Room charming beamed room with oak flooring and brick feature fireplace incorporating log burning cassette stove, log store, shelving to alcove, twin double glazed French doors enjoying glorious country views, understairs cupboard, glazed door to <br />Study/Office charming dual aspect room, lovely country outlook, access to lower loft.<br />Fabulous Kitchen/Dining Room providing a social hub to the home with continuation of porcelain tiled floor and the kitchen section delightfully appointed with beech units comprising six base cupboards with drawers over, two drawer units, wide pan drawers, open ended shelving, full height sliding larder unit, tall unit housing integrated fridge and freezer, integrated dishwasher, solid beech work tops having inset Asterite one and half bowl single drainer sink, chrome mixer tap over, inset four ring ceramic hob with double oven/grill beneath and brushed stainless steel cooker hood/extractor over, the dining area with exposed brick wall, two full height picture windows and French door to rear garden, two further windows and stable side door to patio, beamed ceiling with down lighting, contemporary glass wall tiles.<br />Utility Room pine fronted base unit with worktop and inset stainless steel sink, three wall cupboards over, space and plumbing for washing machine, porcelain tiled floor, spotlighting.<br />On the first floor<br />Returning cottage stairs to delightful galleried Landing, airing cupboard with hot water cylinder and slatted shelving, spectacular vaulted ceiling with exposed roof timbers.<br />Bedroom 1 timber effect floor with range of fitted cupboards and drawers, vaulted ceiling with exposed roof timbers, long window enjoying panoramic country views, wide archway to <br />Dressing Room with two walls fitted with range of fitted wardrobes with hanging and shelving, continuation of timber effect floor, spotlight cluster and downlighting, country views (originally bedroom 4 and readily reinstated if required).<br />Bedroom 2 another lovely vaulted room with exposed roof timbers, fitted double wardrobe.<br />Bedroom 3 vaulted ceiling with exposed timbers, country views.<br />Spectacular contemporary Bathroom with white suite comprising bath with mains shower over, wall hung&nbsp; bidet, wall hung WC with concealed cistern, basin, dual aspect, down lighting, ceramic floor and fully tiled walls, chrome ladder style towel rail/radiator.<br /><br />Outside<br />The property is approached off the end of a no through country lane with gravel drive leading to the turning and parking area with room for 4 cars, adjoining double Garage with light and power, two double timber doors, stairs to Attic Room for storage.&nbsp; Glorious country garden with lawn flanked by well tended shrubberies and borders stocked with an abundance of choice trees and shrubs, perennial borders, two areas of paved terrace ideal for alfresco entertaining.&nbsp; Productive kitchen garden with raised beds served by gravelled paths with soft fruit section the whole being fully fenced and adjoining and overlooking open countryside.<br /><br />N.B. (1) Photos of the garden were taken during the summer of 2014.<br />N.B. (2) Planning permission exists for a single storey garden room extension to south side of the property (approximately 20 square metres)<br /><br /></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 2663, NULL, NULL, '0000-00-00', 'N', 'N', '', 'N', 'N', 'N', '', '', '', ''),
